<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev seadus kehtestab relvade ja nende laskemoona k&auml;itlemise, tsiviilk&auml;ibesse lubamise, tsiviilk&auml;ibes olemise ning tsiviilk&auml;ibest k&otilde;rvaldamise &otilde;iguslikud alused ja korra, n&otilde;uded lasketiirule ja laskepaigale ning nendes valdkondades riikliku j&auml;relevalve teostamise alused ja korra. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act establishes the legal bases and procedure for the handling of weapons and ammunition, the grant of permission for weapons and ammunition to be used for civilian purposes, the use of weapons and ammunition for civilian purposes and the removal of weapons and ammunition from civilian use, the requirements for firing ranges and field firing ranges, and the bases and procedure for the exercise of state supervision in such areas. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on relv seade v&otilde;i ese, mis on ette n&auml;htud elava v&otilde;i muu objekti kahjustamiseks v&otilde;i h&auml;vitamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, a weapon is a device or object which is intended to damage or destroy living or other objects. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relvade ja nende laskemoona k&auml;itlemise all m&otilde;istetakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses relvade ja laskemoona valmistamist, m&uuml;&uuml;ki, soetamist, omamist, valdamist, hoidmist, kandmist, edasitoimetamist, vedu, sissevedu, v&auml;ljavedu, transiiti, v&otilde;&otilde;randamist, p&auml;rimist, leidmist ja h&auml;vitamist ning relvade parandamist, &uuml;mbertegemist, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmist, lammutamist ja laenutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The handling of weapons and ammunition is defined in this Act as the manufacture, sale, acquisition, owning, possession, storage, carrying, conveying, transport, import, export, transit, transfer, succession, finding and destruction of weapons and ammunition, and the repair, conversion, dismantling and rental of weapons and the rendering of weapons incapable of firing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse kohaldamisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevat seadust ei kohaldata: </eesti>
<inglise>The following are excluded from the scope of this Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) esemele ja seadmele, mis ei ole relvaks konstrueeritud v&otilde;i kohandatud, kuid mida on v&otilde;imalik sellena kasutada; </eesti>
<inglise>1) objects and devices which are not constructed as or adapted to be weapons but which can be used as such; </inglise>
<eesti>2) enne 1890. aastat valmistatud tulirelvale; </eesti>
<inglise>2) firearms which were manufactured before the year 1890; </inglise>
<eesti>3) j&auml;&auml;davalt laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muudetud relvale; </eesti>
<inglise>3) weapons which have been rendered permanently incapable of firing; </inglise>
<eesti>4) p&uuml;rotehnilisele seadmele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) pyrotechnic devices; </inglise>
<eesti>5) terariistale (nuga, puss, kirves jt), mis on valmistatud kasutamiseks koduses majapidamises v&otilde;i olmes ja millel puuduvad &sect; 20 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 2 nimetatud eritunnused; </eesti>
<inglise>5) blade devices (knives, hunting knives, axes, etc.) which have been manufactured for household or everyday use and which lack the special characteristics indicated in clause 20 (2) 2); </inglise>
<eesti>6) riigi- ja munitsipaalmuuseumi relvakollektsioonile, v&auml;lja arvatud &sect; 25 l&otilde;ikes 10 s&auml;testatud juhul; </eesti>
<inglise>6) weapons collections of national and municipal museums, except in the case provided for in subsection 25 (10); </inglise>
<eesti>7) s&otilde;jav&auml;e- ja teenistusrelvadele ning nende laskemoonale, kui k&auml;esolev seadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>7) military and service weapons and ammunition therefor, unless otherwise provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;jav&auml;e-, teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvad </eesti>
<inglise>Military, service and civilian weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&otilde;hilise kasutusvaldkonna j&auml;rgi jagunevad relvad j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Weapons are divided according to their main field of application as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) s&otilde;jav&auml;erelv - relv, mis on p&otilde;hiliselt ette n&auml;htud kaitsej&otilde;ududele lahingutegevuseks ning kaitsej&otilde;ududele ja Kaitseministeeriumi valitsemisalas asuvatele asutustele teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) military weapons are weapons which, in general, are intended for the Defence Forces for military action and for the Defence Forces and agencies within the area of government of the Ministry of Defence to perform their service duties; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teenistusrelv - relv, mis on seadusega ette n&auml;htud avalikku v&otilde;imu teostavatele valitsusasutustele ja kohtutele teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise tagamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) service weapons are weapons which are prescribed by law to government agencies exercising public authority and to courts in order to ensure the performance of their service duties; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tsiviilrelv - relv, mis on p&otilde;hiliselt ette n&auml;htud jahipidamiseks, vastava spordialaga tegelemiseks v&otilde;i turvalisuse tagamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) civilian weapons are weapons which, in general, are intended for hunting, involvement in corresponding sports, or the ensurance of safety. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&otilde;jav&auml;erelvade k&auml;itlemise korra kehtestab kaitseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for the handling of military weapons shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Defence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&otilde;jav&auml;erelvad kantakse s&otilde;jav&auml;erelvade riiklikusse registrisse (edaspidi s&otilde;jav&auml;erelvade register), mille asutab ja p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus kaitseministri ettepanekul andmekogude seadusega (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77) kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Military weapons shall be entered in the state register of military weapons (hereinafter register of military weapons) which shall be established and the statutes of which shall be approved by the Government of the Republic on the proposal of the Minister of Defence pursuant to the procedure established by the Databases Act (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77). </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teenistusrelvade liigid ja nende k&auml;itlemise korra kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The types of and procedure for the handling of service weapons shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Teenistusrelvad kantakse teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade riiklikusse registrisse, mille asutab ja p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus siseministri ettepanekul andmekogude seadusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Service weapons shall be entered in the state register of service and civilian weapons which shall be established and the statutes of which shall be approved by the Government of the Republic on the proposal of the Minister of Internal Affairs pursuant to the procedure established by the Databases Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva kasutamine filmiv&otilde;tetel ja etendustel </eesti>
<inglise>Use of weapons during filming and in performances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laskek&otilde;lblikku tulirelva v&otilde;ib filmiv&otilde;tetel ja etendustel kasutada &uuml;ksnes Politseiameti &uuml;hekordse kirjaliku loa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Firearms which are capable of firing may be used during filming and in performances only on the basis of a single written permit granted by the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>Tulistada on lubatud ainult paukpadrunitega. </eesti>
<inglise>Only blank cartridges may be fired. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&uuml;lmrelva v&otilde;ib ohutust tagades kasutada filmiv&otilde;tetel, etendustel ja etenduste ettevalmistamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Cut-and-thrust weapons may be used during filming, in performances and preparation for performances provided that safety is ensured. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvaras olev relv ja laskemoon </eesti>
<inglise>Weapons and ammunition which form part of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik, kelle valdusse sattusid relv ja laskemoon omaniku surma t&otilde;ttu, on kohustatud need viivitamata &uuml;le andma politseiprefektuurile k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 44 l&otilde;igetega 3 ja 4 kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Persons who come into possession of weapons and ammunition due to the death of the owner thereof are required promptly to hand over the weapons and ammunition to a police prefecture pursuant to the procedure established by subsections 44 (3) and (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Alates p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmise p&auml;evast on p&auml;rijal &otilde;igus &uuml;he kuu jooksul esitada avaldus relvaloa saamiseks p&auml;ritud relva kohta v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randada p&auml;ritud relv ja laskemoon kolme kuu jooksul k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A successor to a weapon has the right to submit an application for a weapons permit for the bequeathed weapon within one month as of the date of acceptance of the succession or to transfer the bequeathed weapon and ammunition within three months as of the date of acceptance of the succession pursuant to the procedure provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui p&auml;rijale keeldutakse p&auml;ritud relva kohta relvaluba andmast, peab p&auml;rija v&otilde;&otilde;randama relva ja laskemoona kolme kuu jooksul, arvates relvaloa andmisest keeldumise otsuse k&auml;ttesaamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a successor is denied a weapons permit for a bequeathed weapon, the successor is required to transfer the weapon and ammunition within three months as of the date of receipt of the decision to deny the weapons permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) P&auml;randvaras olevat, tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud, kuid kollektsioneerida lubatud relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;ib v&otilde;&otilde;randada riigile v&otilde;i kollektsioneerimisluba omavale isikule k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Weapons and ammunition which form part of an estate and the use of which is prohibited for civilian purposes but the collection of which is permitted may be transferred, pursuant to the procedure established by this Act, to the state or a person holding a collection permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui omanik ei ole relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;&otilde;randanud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetega 2 ja 3 kehtestatud t&auml;htaja jooksul, kuuluvad relv ja laskemoon sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the owner has not transferred a weapon and ammunition within the term established by subsection (2) or (3) of this section, the weapon and ammunition are subject to expropriation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamine </eesti>
<inglise>Expropriation of weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamise all m&otilde;istetakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;tmist riigi omandisse k&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Expropriation is defined in this Act as the taking into state ownership of weapons and ammunition in the cases prescribed by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relv ja laskemoon sundv&otilde;&otilde;randatakse &otilde;iglase ja kohese h&uuml;vitise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Weapons and ammunition shall be expropriated for fair and immediate compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitis makstakse sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamisele kuuluva relva v&otilde;i laskemoona omanikule, valdajale v&otilde;i p&auml;rijale. </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation shall be paid to the owner or possessor of or the successor to the weapon or ammunition subject to expropriation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamine vormistatakse politseiprefekti otsusega, milles n&auml;idatakse sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamise alus, v&auml;ljamaksmisele kuuluva h&uuml;vitise suurus ja h&uuml;vitise saaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Expropriation shall be formulated by a resolution of a police prefect which indicates the basis for expropriation, the amount of compensation payable and the recipient of the compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus tehakse teatavaks h&uuml;vitise saajale. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision shall be made known to the recipient of the compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamisele kuuluva relva ja laskemoona eest v&auml;ljamakstava h&uuml;vitise arvestamise ja maksmise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The procedure for the calculation and payment of compensation payable for weapons and ammunition subject to expropriation shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Sundv&otilde;&otilde;randatud relva ja laskemoona realiseerimise ja h&auml;vitamise korra kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The procedure for the sale and destruction of expropriated weapons and ammunition shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hisomandis olev relv ja laskemoon </eesti>
<inglise>Weapons and ammunition in joint ownership </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui abikaasade &uuml;hisomandi jagamisel j&auml;&auml;b &uuml;hele neist teise nimele registreeritud relv ja laskemoon, on ta kohustatud need viivitamata &uuml;le andma politseiprefektuurile k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 44 l&otilde;igetega 3 ja 4 kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If, upon the division of the joint property of spouses, one of spouses retains a weapon or ammunition which is registered in the name of the other spouse, he or she is required promptly to hand over the weapon or ammunition to a police prefecture pursuant to the procedure established by subsections 44 (3) and (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Alates jagatud varale omandi&otilde;iguse tekkimisest on omanikul &otilde;igus &uuml;he kuu jooksul esitada avaldus relvaloa saamiseks omandatud relva kohta v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randada relv ja laskemoon kolme kuu jooksul k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An owner has the right to submit an application for a weapons permit for an acquired weapon within one month as of the creation of the right of ownership to the divided property or to transfer the weapon and ammunition within three months pursuant to the procedure established by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juhul kui relvaloa andmisest keeldutakse, tuleb relv ja laskemoon v&otilde;&otilde;randada kolme kuu jooksul, arvates keeldumise otsuse k&auml;ttesaamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a weapons permit is denied, the weapon and ammunition shall be transferred within three months as of the date of refusal to issue the weapons permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui omanik ei ole relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;&otilde;randanud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikega 2 v&otilde;i 3 kehtestatud t&auml;htaja jooksul, kuuluvad relv ja laskemoon sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the owner has not transferred a weapon and ammunition within the term established by subsection (2) or (3) of this section, the weapon and ammunition are subject to expropriation. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud isikul on paralleelrelvaluba sama relva kohta ning tal on k&auml;esoleva seaduse kohased tingimused relva hoidmiseks, v&otilde;ib ta relva ja laskemoona k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 etten&auml;htud toimingute ajal oma k&auml;es hoida. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a person specified in subsection (1) of this section holds a parallel weapons permit for the same weapon and he or she has conditions for the storage of the weapon which comply with this Act, he or she may keep the weapon and ammunition during the performance of the acts prescribed in subsections (2) and (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Pankrotivaras olev relv ja laskemoon </eesti>
<inglise>Weapons and ammunition which form part of bankruptcy estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pankroti korral peab pankrotihaldur tagama pankrotivaras oleva relva ja laskemoona hoidmise k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras ja tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the event of bankruptcy, the trustee in bankruptcy shall ensure that weapons and ammunition which form part of the bankruptcy estate are stored pursuant to the procedure and under the conditions established by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pankrotivaras olevat relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;ib v&otilde;&otilde;randada k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Weapons and ammunition which form part of a bankruptcy estate may be transferred under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva v&otilde;&otilde;randamise luba v&auml;ljastatakse pankrotihalduri taotluse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>A weapon transfer permit shall be issued on the basis of an application by the trustee in bankruptcy. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui pankrotivaras olevat relva ja laskemoona ei &otilde;nnestu v&otilde;&otilde;randada kuue kuu jooksul p&auml;rast pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamist, h&auml;vitatakse need k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 83 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If weapons or ammunition which form part of a bankruptcy estate cannot be transferred within six months after the declaration of bankruptcy, the weapons and ammunition shall be destroyed pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 83 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona leid </eesti>
<inglise>Finding of weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik, kes on leidnud kaotatud, maetud, peidetud v&otilde;i mahaj&auml;etud relva ja laskemoona ning need oma valdusse v&otilde;tnud, peab sellest viivitamata teatama asukohaj&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile ning andma talle leiu &uuml;le k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 44 l&otilde;igetega 3 ja 4 kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who has found lost, buried, hidden or discarded weapons or ammunition and who has taken possession thereof shall promptly inform the police prefecture of his or her residence of the finding and shall hand over the weapons or ammunition to the police prefecture pursuant to the procedure established by subsections 44 (3) and (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiprefektuur teatab leitud relvast ja laskemoonast &uuml;leriigilise levikuga ajalehes seitsme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates leitud relva ja laskemoona temale &uuml;leandmise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The police prefecture shall announce the finding of the weapon or ammunition in a national daily newspaper within seven days as of the date following the date on which the weapon or ammunition found is handed over to the police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui leitud relva v&otilde;i laskemoona omanik v&otilde;i valdaja ei ole kuue kuu m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel ajalehes kuulutuse avaldamisest selgunud, on leidjal &otilde;igus leitud relv ja laskemoon omandada juhul, kui ei ole tuvastatud relva eelnevat kasutamist seadusvastastes toimingutes. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the owner of a found weapon or found ammunition has not been determined within six months after publication of the announcement regarding the finding in a newspaper, the finder has the right to gain acquisition of the found weapon or ammunition unless it is established that the weapon has previously been used in any illegal activities. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Alates leitud varale omandi&otilde;iguse tekkimisest on omanikul &otilde;igus &uuml;he kuu jooksul esitada taotlus relvaloa saamiseks omandatud relva kohta v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randada relv ja laskemoon kolme kuu jooksul k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An owner has the right to submit an application for a weapons permit for an acquired weapon within one month as of the creation of the right of ownership with regard to the found property or to transfer the weapon and ammunition within three months, pursuant to the procedure established by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui leidjale keeldutakse leitud relva kohta relvaluba andmast, tuleb relv ja laskemoon v&otilde;&otilde;randada kolme kuu jooksul, arvates keeldumise otsuse k&auml;ttesaamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a person is denied a weapons permit for a found weapon, the weapon and ammunition shall be transferred within three months as of the date of receipt of the decision to refuse to grant a permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Leitud, tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud, kuid kollektsioneerida lubatud relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;ib v&otilde;&otilde;randada riigile v&otilde;i kollektsioneerimisluba omavale isikule k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Found weapons and ammunition the use of which is prohibited for civilian purposes but the collection of which is permitted may be transferred, pursuant to the procedure established by this Act, to the state or a person holding a collection permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui leidja ei ole relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;&otilde;randanud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikega 4 v&otilde;i 5 kehtestatud t&auml;htaja jooksul, kuuluvad need sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If the finder of a weapon or ammunition has not transferred the weapon or ammunition within the term established by subsection (4) or (5) of this section, the weapon and ammunition are subject to expropriation. </inglise>
