<eesti>Relvade liigitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Classification of weapons </inglise>
<eesti>Relvad liigitatakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>Weapons are classified as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tulirelv - relv, mis on ette n&auml;htud objekti h&auml;vitamiseks v&otilde;i kahjustamiseks lendkehaga, mille suunatud v&auml;ljalaskmiseks kasutatakse p&uuml;ssirohu- v&otilde;i muud laengut; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a firearm is a weapon intended to destroy or damage objects by way of a projectile where a charge of propellant or another charge is used for the directed discharge thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) gaasirelv - relv, mis on ette n&auml;htud elava objekti l&uuml;hiajaliseks kahjustamiseks &auml;rritava toimega gaasiga; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a gas weapon is a weapon intended to cause short-term damage to living objects by means of irritant gases; </inglise>
<eesti>3) pneumorelv - relv, milles lendkeha saab suunatud liikumise suru&otilde;hu v&otilde;i muu surugaasi energiast; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a pneumatic weapon is a weapon where the projectile receives an impulse for directed movement from the energy provided by compressed air or other compressed gases; </inglise>
<eesti>4) k&uuml;lmrelv - relv, mis on ette n&auml;htud objekti kahjustamiseks lihasj&otilde;u abil vahetus kontaktis kahjustatava objektiga; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a cut-and-thrust weapon is a weapon intended to damage objects by means of muscular energy and in direct contact with the object to be damaged; </inglise>
<eesti>5) heitrelv - relv, milles lendkeha saab suunatud liikumise inimese kehalise j&otilde;u v&otilde;i mehaanilise seadise abil; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a projectile weapon is a weapon where the projectile receives an impulse for directed movement from human bodily energy or by means of a mechanical device; </inglise>
<eesti>6) elektri&scaron;okirelv - relv, mille toime p&otilde;hineb elektrienergia kasutamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>6) an electric shock weapon is a weapon the effect of which is based on the use of electric energy. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Tulirelvade liigitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Classification of firearms </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tulirelvade liigid pikkuse ja relvaraua pikkuse j&auml;rgi on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Firearms are classified on the basis of their length and the length of their barrels as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&uuml;ss - tulirelv, mille &uuml;ldpikkus on &uuml;le 600 mm ja relvaraua (relvaraudade) pikkus &uuml;le 300 mm; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a gun is a firearm with an overall length of over 600 mm and a barrel length of over 300 mm; </inglise>
<eesti>2) p&uuml;stol - tulirelv, mille &uuml;ldpikkus on kuni 600 mm (kaasa arvatud) ja relvaraua pikkus kuni 300 mm (kaasa arvatud) ning mille padrunid v&otilde;ivad padrunisalves paikneda &uuml;hes v&otilde;i mitmes reas; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a pistol is a firearm with an overall length of up to 600 mm (inclusive) and a barrel length of up to 300 mm (inclusive) and in which cartridges may be located in the magazine in one or more rows; </inglise>
<eesti>3) revolver - trumliga tulirelv, mille &uuml;ldpikkus on kuni 600 mm (kaasa arvatud) ja relvaraua pikkus kuni 300 mm (kaasa arvatud) ning mille trummel on nii padrunisalveks kui ka padrunipesaks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a revolver is a firearm with a cylinder and with an overall length of up to 600 mm (inclusive) and a barrel length of up to 300 mm (inclusive), and in which the cylinder simultaneously serves as a magazine and a chamber. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tulirelvade liigid kaliibri ja kasutatava padruni j&auml;rgi on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Firearms are classified on the basis of their calibre and the cartridges used as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&auml;iskaliibriline - tulirelv, mille laskemoonaks on kesktulepadrun; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a full-calibre firearm is a firearm where centre-fire cartridges are used as ammunition; </inglise>
<eesti>2) v&auml;ikesekaliibriline - tulirelv, mille kaliiber on.22 v&otilde;i 5,6 mm ja mille laskemoonaks on &auml;&auml;retulepadrun. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a rimfire firearm is a.22 or 5.6 mm calibre firearm where rimfire cartridges are used as ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tulirelvade liigid relvaraua &otilde;&otilde;ne j&auml;rgi on: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Firearms are classified by the characteristics of their bore as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) sileraudne - tulirelv, mille relvaraua &otilde;&otilde;s on sile, ilma vintsoonteta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a firearm with a smoothbore barrel is a firearm with a smooth bore without rifling; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vintraudne - tulirelv, mille relvaraua &otilde;&otilde;nes on vintsooned; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a firearm with a rifled barrel is a firearm with a bore with rifling; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kombineeritud - sile- ja vintraudade kombinatsiooniga tulirelv. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a combination rifle-shotgun is a firearm with a combination of smoothbore and rifled barrels. </inglise>
