<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud relvad ja laskemoon </eesti>
<inglise>Weapons and ammunition prohibited for civilian purposes </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud tulirelvad on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The use of the following firearms is prohibited for civilian purposes: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tulirelv, mis imiteerib m&otilde;ne muu eseme kuju; </eesti>
<inglise>1) firearms disguised as other objects; </inglise>
<eesti>2) sileraudne p&uuml;ss, mille &uuml;ldpikkus on alla 840 mm v&otilde;i mille iga raua pikkus on alla 450 mm; </eesti>
<inglise>2) smoothbore guns with an overall length of less than 840 mm or where the length of each barrel is less than 450 mm; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tulirelv, mida on v&otilde;imalik antud relvaliigile tavalist m&auml;&auml;ra &uuml;letavalt kokku panna (l&uuml;kata) v&otilde;i l&uuml;hendada; </eesti>
<inglise>3) firearms which can be folded (collapsed) or shortened to a greater extent than generally permitted for such type of weapon; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tulirelv, mis lahtiv&otilde;etuna v&otilde;imaldab lasu sooritamist; </eesti>
<inglise>4) firearms which can be fired when disassembled; </inglise>
<eesti>5) automaattulirelv, millest &uuml;hekordsel p&auml;&auml;stikule vajutamisel saab sooritada valangu; </eesti>
<inglise>5) automatic firearms which can produce full automatic fire with a single pull on the trigger; </inglise>
<eesti>6) tulirelv, millel puudub valmistaja markeering; </eesti>
<inglise>6) firearms which do not have the manufacturer's marking; </inglise>
<eesti>7) eriti tugevaj&otilde;uline, tavaliselt s&otilde;jav&auml;erelvana kasutatav tulirelv. </eesti>
<inglise>7) particularly powerful firearms which are generally used as military weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud k&uuml;lmrelvad on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The use of the following cut-and thrust weapons is prohibited for civilian purposes: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kasteet, kasteetnuga, torket&auml;&auml;k, teraspiits, samuti muu spetsiaalselt kehavigastuse tekitamiseks valmistatud ese; </eesti>
<inglise>1) brass knuckles, knuckle knives, bayonets, chain maces, and also other objects specifically intended to cause bodily injuries; </inglise>
<eesti>2) l&otilde;ike-, torke- v&otilde;i l&ouml;&ouml;girelv, mis imiteerib m&otilde;ne muu eseme kuju v&otilde;i on peidetud selle sisse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) cutting, thrusting and striking weapons which are disguised as other objects or hidden within other objects; </inglise>
<eesti>3) vedru- v&otilde;i raskusj&otilde;ul v&auml;ljaviskuva ja seej&auml;rel j&auml;igalt kinnituva teraga nuga, mille tera pikkus on &uuml;le 8,5 cm v&otilde;i mille tera on kahelt poolt teritatud. </eesti>
<inglise>3) knives with a blade which is ejected by the force of a spring or gravity and which is then locked, and with a blade length of over 8.5 cm or a double-edged blade. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tsiviilk&auml;ibes on keelatud elektri&scaron;okirelv. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The use of electric shock weapons for civilian purposes is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud laskemoon on: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The use of the following ammunition is prohibited for civilian purposes: </inglise>
<eesti>1) gaasip&uuml;stoli- ja -revolvripadrun, mis sisaldab n&auml;rviparal&uuml;&uuml;tilist, nahakahjustust tekitavat, &uuml;ldm&uuml;rgitava ja l&auml;mmatava toimega ainet, mis v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hjustada sellise tervisekahjustuse, mille k&otilde;rvaldamiseks on vaja arstiabi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) gas pistol and gas revolver cartridges containing neuroparalytic substances or substances which induce skin damage, general intoxication or choking and which may cause damage to health to the extent where medical attention is required to eliminate the consequences of exposure; </inglise>
<eesti>2) soomustl&auml;biv laskemoon - tulirelva padrun, mille kuulil on soomustl&auml;bistav k&otilde;vas&uuml;damik; </eesti>
<inglise>2) armour-piercing ammunition, which means a firearm cartridge the bullet of which has an armour-piercing hard core; </inglise>
<eesti>3) l&otilde;hke-laskemoon - tulirelva padrun, mille kuul sisaldab laengut, mis kokkup&otilde;rkel takistusega l&otilde;hkeb (plahvatab); </eesti>
<inglise>3) ammunition with explosive projectiles, which means a firearm cartridge the bullet of which contains a charge which explodes upon impact with an obstruction; </inglise>
<eesti>4) s&uuml;&uuml;te-laskemoon - tulirelva padrun, mille kuul sisaldab ainet, mis kokkup&otilde;rkel takistusega s&uuml;ttib p&otilde;lema; </eesti>
<inglise>4) ammunition with incendiary projectiles, which means a firearm cartridge the bullet of which contains a substance which ignites upon impact with an obstruction; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &otilde;&otilde;nsaotsalise kuuliga p&uuml;stoli- ja revolvripadrun; </eesti>
<inglise>5) pistol or revolver cartridges with a hollow-pointed bullet; </inglise>
<eesti>6) eriti ohtlik, tavaliselt s&otilde;jav&auml;erelvades kasutatav laskemoon. </eesti>
<inglise>6) particularly dangerous ammunition which is generally used in military weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud, eriti tugevaj&otilde;uliste tavaliselt s&otilde;jav&auml;erelvana kasutatavate tulirelvamudelite ja eriti ohtliku tavaliselt s&otilde;jav&auml;erelvades kasutatava laskemoona liikide loetelu kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The list of models of particularly powerful firearms generally used as military weapons and prohibited for civilian purposes and of types of particularly dangerous ammunition generally used in military weapons and prohibited for civilian purposes shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Tulirelva olulised osad </eesti>
<inglise>Essential components of firearms </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tulirelva olulised osad on relvaraud, lukk, padrunipesa ja revolvritrummel, samuti nende toorikud, kui neid saab l&otilde;puni viimistleda &uuml;ldkasutatavate t&ouml;&ouml;riistadega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The essential components of a firearm are the barrel, breech block, chamber and revolver cylinder, and also the blanks thereof if they can be finished with the aid of commonly used tools. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tulirelva olulise osa k&auml;itlemisele laieneb sama kord, mis k&auml;esoleva seadusega on kehtestatud seda liiki relva k&auml;itlemisele, kui seadus otseselt ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for the handling of any given type of firearm as established by this Act also applies to the handling of the essential components of such firearms unless this Act provides directly otherwise. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Tulirelva lisaseadised </eesti>
<inglise>Firearm accessories </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev seadus eristab tulirelvale paigaldamiseks etten&auml;htud lisaseadiseid vastavalt nende otstarbele j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act distinguishes between the accessories intended to be installed on firearms according to their purpose as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) lasersihik - tulirelvale sihtimiseks etten&auml;htud seadis, kus sihtimiseks kasutatakse laserikiirt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a laser sight is a device intended to be installed on firearms where a laser beam is used for sighting; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &ouml;&ouml;sihik - puudulikus valguses sihtimiseks etten&auml;htud seadis, millel on kujutise muundur v&otilde;i elektrooniline v&otilde;imendus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a night sight is a device intended to be used for sighting in insufficient light which has an image converter or electronic amplifier; </inglise>
<eesti>3) helisummuti - tulirelvaga tulistamisel tekkiva heli summutamiseks etten&auml;htud seadis; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a silencer is a device intended to silence sound created by the discharge of a firearm; </inglise>
<eesti>4) adapter - tulirelva relvarauda paigutatav relvaraud v&otilde;i vahetatav mehhanism, mis v&otilde;imaldab kasutada v&auml;iksema kaliibriga laskemoona. </eesti>
<inglise>4) an adapter is a barrel or changeable mechanism installed within the barrel of a firearm which enables smaller calibre ammunition to be used. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lasersihiku ja adapteri soetamiseks on n&otilde;utav Politseiameti kirjalik luba. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Written authorisation is required from the Police Board to acquire a laser sight or adapter. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lasersihik ja adapter tuleb registreerida elu- v&otilde;i asukohaj&auml;rgses politseiprefektuuris n&auml;dala jooksul p&auml;rast selle soetamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A laser sight or adapter shall be registered at the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the acquirer within one week after its acquisition. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lasersihiku ja adapteri registreerimisel v&auml;ljastab politseiprefektuur relvaomanikule v&otilde;i -valdajale uue relvaloa, millele kannab soetatud lasersihiku ja adapteri andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon the registration of a laser sight or adapter, the police prefecture shall issue a new weapons permit to the owner or possessor of the weapon setting out information concerning the laser sight or adapter. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvaluba, millele on kantud lasersihiku ja adapteri andmed, on lasersihiku ja adapteri omamist, kandmist ja edasitoimetamist &otilde;igustavaks dokumendiks. </eesti>
<inglise>A weapons permit in which information concerning a laser sight or adapter has been entered is the document which is the basis for owning, carrying and conveying the laser sight or adapter. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Ouml;&ouml;sihik ja helisummuti on tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The use of night sights and adapters for civilian purposes is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitus. </eesti>
<inglise>Type Approval of Weapons and Ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>Tsiviilrelvade arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of Civilian Weapons </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitus </eesti>
<inglise>Type approval of weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva ja laskemoona t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitus (edaspidi t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitus) on toiming, mille k&auml;igus otsustatakse relva- v&otilde;i padrunimudeli kuuluvus tsiviilk&auml;ibesse lubatud relvade ja nende padrunite hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Type approval of weapons and ammunition (hereinafter type approval) is an act by which it is determined whether a particular model of weapon or cartridge is included in the list of weapons and ammunition permitted to be used for civilian purposes. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitusele kuuluvad Eestis k&auml;ibes olevad, Eestis valmistatud ja Eestisse sissetoodavad relva- ja padrunimudelid ning nende modifikatsioonid, samuti Eestis &uuml;mberehitatud relvamudelid ja nende modifikatsioonid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Models of weapons and cartridges in commerce in Estonia, manufactured in Estonia and imported into Estonia and their modifications, as well as models of weapons converted in Estonia and their modifications are subject to type approval. </inglise>
<eesti>T&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitusele ei kuulu kumminuiad ega piiramata tsiviilk&auml;ibega relvad. </eesti>
<inglise>Truncheons and weapons in unrestricted commerce are not subject to type approval. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitusel m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks relva- v&otilde;i padrunimudeli v&otilde;i selle modifikatsiooni tsiviilk&auml;ibesse lubatavus ning selle liigitus, l&auml;htudes k&auml;esoleva seaduse 2. peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) During type approval, a decision is taken as to whether a particular model of weapon or cartridge or its modification is permitted in commerce, and its classification is determined on the basis of the provisions of Chapter 2 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust teostab Vabariigi Valitsuse volitatud asutus (edaspidi kinnitusasutus). </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Type approval shall be performed by agencies authorised by the Government of the Republic (hereinafter approval authorities). </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitus toimub relva v&otilde;i padruni valmistaja v&otilde;i relva &uuml;mbertegija, samuti Eestisse sissetooja avalduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Type approval shall be performed on the basis of an application by the person who manufactured the weapon or cartridge, converted the weapon or imported the weapon or cartridge to Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Tsiviilk&auml;ibes olevate relvade t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust teostab kinnitusasutus vastava tehnilise dokumentatsiooni ja tehnilise kirjanduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An approval authority shall perform type approval of weapons in commerce on the basis of corresponding documentation and technical literature. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) T&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse saanud relva- ja padrunimudel ning nende modifikatsioon kantakse teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registrisse. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A model of weapon or cartridge or a modification thereof which has been type approved shall be entered in the register of service and civilian weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Tsiviilrelvade arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of civilian weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tsiviilk&auml;ibes olevad relvad ning k&otilde;ik relva- ja padrunikollektsiooni kuuluvad relvad kantakse teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registrisse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) All weapons the use of which is permitted for civilian purposes and all weapons in collections of weapons and cartridges shall be entered in the register of service and civilian weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registrisse ei kanta: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following shall not be entered in the register of service and civilian weapons: </inglise>
<eesti>1) piiramata tsiviilk&auml;ibega relva; </eesti>
<inglise>1) weapons in unrestricted commerce; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kumminuia; </eesti>
<inglise>2) truncheons; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ekspordiks valmistatud relva; </eesti>
<inglise>3) weapons manufactured for export; </inglise>
<eesti>4) transiitsaadetises olevat relva. </eesti>
<inglise>4) weapons in transit consignments. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relv kantakse teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registrisse Eestisse sisseveol, Eesti tootjalt Eesti tellijale &uuml;leandmisel ning relva igakordsel registreerimisel omaniku v&otilde;i valdaja nimele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A weapon shall be entered in the register of service and civilian weapons upon its import into Estonia or its delivery from its Estonian producer to the person in Estonia who ordered the weapon and upon each registration of the weapon in the name of the owner or possessor thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade kollektsioneerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Collection of Weapons </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva- ja padrunikollektsioon </eesti>
<inglise>Collections of weapons and cartridges </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva- ja padrunikollektsioon (edaspidi kollektsioon) on ajaloo- v&otilde;i kultuuriv&auml;&auml;rtusega relvade ja padrunite korrastatud kogum, mida kasutatakse v&otilde;i mida on v&otilde;imalik kasutada v&auml;ljapanekuks v&otilde;i uurimist&ouml;&ouml;ks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A collection of weapons and cartridges (hereinafter collection) is an organised set of weapons and cartridges with historical or cultural value which is used or which it is possible to use as an exhibition or for research. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kollektsiooni v&otilde;ib asutada ja pidada Eesti kodanik v&otilde;i Eestis registreeritud juriidiline isik Politseiameti antud relva- ja padrunikollektsioneerimisloa (edaspidi kollektsioneerimisluba) alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A collection may be founded and maintained by a citizen of Estonia or a legal person registered in Estonia on the basis of a collection permit for weapons and cartridges (hereinafter collection permit) granted by the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kollektsioneerida on lubatud k&otilde;iki, sealhulgas s&otilde;jav&auml;erelvade hulka arvatud ja muid tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud tulirelvi, k&uuml;lmrelvi ja padruneid, samuti tulirelva olulisi osi ja lisaseadiseid, v&auml;lja arvatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) All firearms, cut-and-thrust weapons, cartridges, essential components of firearms and firearm accessories may be collected, including weapons classified as military weapons or weapons the use of which for civilian purposes is prohibited and with the exception of the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kasteet, kasteetnuga, teraspiits, samuti muu spetsiaalselt kehavigastuse tekitamiseks valmistatud ese; </eesti>
<inglise>1) brass knuckles, knuckle knives, bayonets, and also other objects specifically intended to cause bodily injuries; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>2) relv, mille m&otilde;ju p&otilde;hineb elektrienergia, radioaktiivse kiirguse v&otilde;i bioloogilise faktori kasutamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) weapons the effect of which is based on the use of electric energy, radioactive emissions or biological factors; </inglise>
<eesti>3) l&otilde;hke-laskemoon, s&uuml;&uuml;te-laskemoon, eriti ohtlik tavaliselt s&otilde;jav&auml;erelvades kasutatav laskemoon ning n&auml;rviparal&uuml;&uuml;tilist, nahakahjustust tekitavat, &uuml;ldm&uuml;rgitava ja l&auml;mmatava toimega ainet sisaldav laskemoon. </eesti>
<inglise>3) ammunition with explosive projectiles, ammunition with incendiary projectiles, particularly dangerous ammunition generally used in military weapons and ammunition containing neuroparalytic substances or substances which induce skin damage, general intoxication or choking. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kollektsiooni kuuluvad relvad tuleb registreerida elu- v&otilde;i asukohaj&auml;rgses politseiprefektuuris k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 33 kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Weapons which are part of a collection shall be registered in the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the collector pursuant to the procedure established in &sect; 33 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Andmed registreeritud relvade kohta kantakse kollektsioneerimisloale. </eesti>
<inglise>Information concerning the registered weapons shall be entered in the collection permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kollektsiooni kuuluva relva kandmine on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) It is prohibited to carry a weapon which is part of a collection. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kollektsiooni kuuluvate relvade ja padrunite hoidmine, edasitoimetamine, v&otilde;&otilde;randamine ja vedu peab toimuma k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Weapons and cartridges which are part of a collection shall be stored, conveyed, transferred and transported under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kollektsiooni kuuluvaid relvi ja padruneid tuleb hoida k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 46 s&auml;testatud relvahoidlas. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Weapons and cartridges which are part of a collection shall be stored in a weapons storage room provided for in &sect; 46 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Kollektsiooni kuuluvaid relvi ja padruneid v&otilde;ib eksponeerida relvahoidlas. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Weapons and cartridges which are part of a collection may be exhibited in a weapons storage room. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;ljaspool relvahoidlat v&otilde;ib kollektsiooni kuuluvaid relvi ja padruneid eksponeerida Politseiameti &uuml;hekordsel kirjalikul loal, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse ka tingimused relvade ja padrunite eksponeerimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Outside a weapons storage room, weapons and cartridges which are part of a collection may be exhibited on the basis of a single written permit granted by the Police Board which also sets out the conditions for the exhibition of the weapons and cartridges. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Eksponeeritavad relvad peavad asuma lukustatud v&otilde;i mehaaniliste vahenditega suletud vitriinides v&otilde;i olema kindlalt kinnitatud p&otilde;randa, seina v&otilde;i muu ehituskonstruktsiooni k&uuml;lge. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Exhibited weapons shall be located in locked showcases or showcases which are closed mechanically or they shall be securely attached to the floor, a wall or another structural member of the building. </inglise>
<eesti>Eksponeeritavad padrunid peavad asuma lukustatud v&otilde;i mehaaniliste vahenditega suletud vitriinides. </eesti>
<inglise>Exhibited cartridges shall be located in locked showcases or showcases which are closed mechanically. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Riigi- ja munitsipaalmuuseumi relvakollektsiooni pidamise korra kehtestab kultuuriminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) The procedure for the maintenance of weapons collections by state and municipal museums shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Culture. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Kollektsioneerimisluba </eesti>
<inglise>Collection permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kollektsiooni asutada ja pidada sooviv f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik esitab vastava avalduse Politseiametile oma elu- v&otilde;i asukoha j&auml;rgse politseiprefektuuri kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A natural or legal person who wishes to found or maintain a collection shall submit a corresponding application to the Police Board through the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduses n&auml;idatakse kollektsioneerimise eesm&auml;rk, kollektsioneeritavate relvade ja padrunite liik ning nende hoiutingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>The application shall set out the aim of the collection, the type of weapons and cartridges to be collected and the conditions in which they will be stored. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaldusele lisab f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 35 l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 2-5, juriidiline isik aga k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 37 l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 2-5 nimetatud dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>A natural person shall annex the documents specified in clauses 35 (2) 2) -5) of this Act to the application and a legal person shall annex the documents specified in clauses 37 (2) 2) -5) of this Act to the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Enne kollektsioneerimisloa saamist peab seda taotlev f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik sooritama elukohaj&auml;rgses politseiprefektuuris k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 35 l&otilde;ikes 5 etten&auml;htud relvatundmise eksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Before a collection permit is granted to a natural person, the applicant shall pass an examination on his or her knowledge regarding weapons as prescribed in subsection 35 (5) of this Act at the police prefecture of his or her residence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taotlus vaadatakse l&auml;bi hiljemalt kahe kuu jooksul, arvates k&otilde;igi n&otilde;utavate dokumentide esitamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An application shall be reviewed not later than within two months as of the date on which all the required documents are submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kollektsioneerimisloa andmise v&otilde;i andmisest keeldumise otsus vormistatakse kirjalikult, keeldumise puhul n&auml;idatakse keeldumise alus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The decision to grant or to refuse to grant a collection permit shall be prepared in writing and, in the event of the permit being refused, the basis for refusal shall be indicated. </inglise>
<eesti>Kollektsioneerimisloa andmisest f&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule v&otilde;idakse keelduda, kui esineb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud asjaolu, v&auml;lja arvatud sama l&otilde;ike punktis 3 s&auml;testatu. </eesti>
<inglise>An application by a natural person for a collection permit may be denied if any of the circumstances provided for in subsection 36 (1) of this Act exist, except for that provided for in clause 3) of the same subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>Kollektsioneerimisloa andmisest juriidilisele isikule v&otilde;idakse keelduda, kui esineb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 40 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud asjaolu. </eesti>
<inglise>An application by a legal person for a collection permit may be denied if any of the circumstances provided for in subsection 40 (1) of this Act exist. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kollektsioneerimisloal n&auml;idatakse kollektsioonis s&auml;ilitamiseks lubatud relvade ja padrunite liigid, samuti kollektsiooni kuuluvad politseiprefektuuris registreeritud relvad. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A collection permit shall set out the types of weapons and cartridges permitted to be collected and also the weapons which are part of the collection and which have been registered at the police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kollektsioneerimisluba antakse t&auml;htajaga k&uuml;mme aastat, misj&auml;rel seda v&otilde;idakse pikendada samaks t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A collection permit shall be granted for a term of ten years after which it may be extended for a further similar term. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Politseiamet tunnistab kollektsioneerimisloa kehtetuks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The Police Board may revoke a collection permit if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) seda taotleb relvakollektsiooni omanik; </eesti>
<inglise>1) so requested by the owner of the weapons collection; </inglise>
<eesti>2) relvakollektsiooni omanik ei vasta enam k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the owner of the weapons collection no longer complies with the requirements provided for in this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) relvakollektsiooni omanik on surnud, surnuks v&otilde;i teadmata kadunuks tunnistatud v&otilde;i kuulutatud tagaotsitavaks kohtu v&otilde;i kohtueelse uurimise asutuse poolt; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the owner of the weapons collection is deceased, declared to be dead or missing, or declared a fugitive by a court or a pre-trial investigation authority; </inglise>
<eesti>4) juriidiline isik on l&otilde;ppenud; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the legal person is dissolved; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kollektsioneerimisluba on kaotatud; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the collection permit has been lost; </inglise>
<eesti>6) relvakollektsiooni omanik on v&auml;hemalt kaks korda viimase kolme aasta jooksul rikkunud k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusakti n&otilde;udeid, mida ta peab t&auml;itma, v&otilde;i ei ole t&auml;itnud temale tehtud ettekirjutuse n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the owner of the weapons collection has, on at least two occasions within the last three years, violated the requirements of this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof with which the owner is required to comply, or has failed to comply with the requirements of a precept issued to the owner. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Kollektsioneerimisloa kehtetuks tunnistamine vormistatakse Politseiameti otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The revocation of a collection permit shall be formalised by a decision of the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuses peab olema n&auml;idatud kehtetuks tunnistamise alus viitega seaduse vastavale s&auml;ttele. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision shall set out the basis for revocation with a reference to the corresponding provision of law. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuse &auml;rakiri saadetakse viivitamata kollektsioneerimisloa omajale. </eesti>
<inglise>A copy of the decision shall be sent promptly to the holder of the collection permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Kollektsioneerimisloa kehtivuse l&otilde;ppemisel v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamisel rakenduvad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 44 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uded, kusjuures politseiprefektuurile &uuml;leantavad relvad ja padrunid v&otilde;ib j&auml;tta hoiule politseiprefektuuri poolt pitseeritud kollektsiooniomaniku relvahoidlasse. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Upon the expiry or revocation of a collection permit, the requirements of &sect; 44 of this Act apply, whereupon the weapons and cartridges to be handed over to a police prefecture may be deposited in a weapons storage room of the owner of the collection which shall be sealed by the police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Kollektsioneerimisloa vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) The standard format for collection permits shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva soetamine kollektsiooni jaoks </eesti>
<inglise>Acquisition of weapons for collection </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva soetamine kollektsiooni jaoks toimub k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 32 s&auml;testatud soetamisloa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Weapons shall be acquired for collections on the basis of an acquisition permit provided for in &sect; 32 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetamisloa v&auml;ljastamise aluseks on kollektsioneerimisluba. </eesti>
<inglise>An acquisition permit is issued on the basis of a collection permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Padruni soetamine kollektsiooni jaoks toimub kollektsioneerimisloa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Cartridges shall be acquired for a collection on the basis of a collection permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Soetamisloa taotlemise avaldus esitatakse elu- v&otilde;i asukohaj&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An application for an acquisition permit shall be submitted to the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduses n&auml;idatakse soetatava relva liik ja mark ning registreeritud relva korral ka selle markeering. </eesti>
<inglise>The application shall set out the type and mark of the weapon to be acquired and, in the case of a registered weapon, also its marking. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaldusele lisatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>The following shall be appended to the application: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kollektsioneerimisluba, mis tagastatakse loa omajale; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a collection permit, which shall be returned to the holder of the permit; </inglise>
<eesti>2) riigil&otilde;ivu tasumist t&otilde;endav dokument. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a document certifying payment of the state fee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kollektsiooni jaoks soetatava relva soetamisloa taotlemisele ei laiene k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-dega 35 ja 37 kehtestatud kord. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure established by &sect;&sect; 35 and 37 of this Act does not extend to application for an acquisition permit for a weapon to be acquired for a collection. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Relva v&otilde;i laskemoona sissevedu relvakollektsiooni jaoks toimub k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 60 l&otilde;ikega 3 kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The import of weapons and ammunition for a weapons collection shall take place pursuant to the procedure established by subsection 60 (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona soetamine, omamine ja valdamine </eesti>
<inglise>Acquisition, Owning and Possession of Weapons and Ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>F&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule lubatud relvade otstarve </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of weapons permitted for natural persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;&uuml;siline isik v&otilde;ib relva soetada, omada ja vallata j&auml;rgmisel otstarbel: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A natural person may acquire, own or possess a weapon for the following purposes: </inglise>
<eesti>1) jahipidamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) hunting; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vastava spordialaga tegelemiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) engaging in corresponding sports; </inglise>
<eesti>3) turvalisuse tagamiseks (enese ja vara kaitseks); </eesti>
<inglise>3) ensuring safety (protecting himself or herself and his or her property); </inglise>
<eesti>4) kutsealal tegutsemiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) pursuing a profession; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kollektsioneerimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>5) collecting. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relva kasutamisel ei tohi rikkuda teiste isikute &otilde;igusi ega avalikku korda. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The use of a weapon shall not violate the rights of other persons or public order. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Eesti kodanikule lubatud relvade liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Types of weapons permitted for Estonian citizens </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eesti kodanik v&otilde;ib soetada ja omada j&auml;rgmisi relvi: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An Estonian citizen may acquire and own the following types of weapons: </inglise>
<eesti>1) v&auml;hemalt 18-aastane - v&auml;ikesekaliibrilist sporditulirelva, pneumo- ja gaasirelva, ambu ja sileraudset p&uuml;ssi. </eesti>
<inglise>1) a person who is at least 18 years of age may own a rimfire sporting firearm, pneumatic or gas weapon, crossbow or smoothbore gun. </inglise>
<eesti>Vintraudset ja kombineeritud jahip&uuml;ssi v&otilde;ib ta soetada ja omada tingimusel, et tal on jahitunnistus; </eesti>
<inglise>Such person may acquire and own a hunting gun with a rifled barrel or a combination hunting gun on the condition that he or she holds a hunting certificate; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ajateenistuskohustuse (v&auml;lja arvatud asendusteenistus) t&auml;itnud v&otilde;i v&auml;hemalt 21-aastane - k&otilde;iki tsiviilk&auml;ibesse lubatud relvi, v&auml;lja arvatud kumminui. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a person who has performed his conscript service obligation (except for alternative service) or a person of at least 21 years of age may acquire and own all weapons which are permitted to be used for civilian purposes, except for truncheons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Sporditulirelv on rahvusvaheliselt tunnustatud, laskmisega seotud spordiala harrastamiseks etten&auml;htud tulirelv. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A sporting firearm is a firearm intended to be used in internationally recognised sports involving shooting. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Jahip&uuml;ss on p&otilde;hiliselt jahipidamiseks etten&auml;htud sile- ja vintraudne ning kombineeritud p&uuml;ss. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A hunting gun is a gun with a smoothbore or rifled barrel or a combination gun intended mainly for hunting. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lismaalasele lubatud relvade liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Types of weapons permitted for aliens </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&auml;lismaalane, kes viibib Eestis alalise elamisloa alusel ja on v&auml;hemalt 18-aastane, v&otilde;ib soetada ja omada pneumo- ja gaasirelva ning sileraudset p&uuml;ssi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An alien who is at least 18 years of age who is staying in Estonia on the basis of a permanent residence permit may acquire and own pneumatic weapons, gas weapons and guns with a smoothbore barrel. </inglise>
<eesti>Vintraudset sporditulirelva ning vintraudset ja kombineeritud jahip&uuml;ssi v&otilde;ib ta omada tingimusel, et neid hoitakse jahindus- v&otilde;i spordiorganisatsiooni v&otilde;i vastavat tegevusluba omava isiku relvahoidlas. </eesti>
<inglise>An alien may own sporting firearms with a rifled barrel and combination hunting guns on the condition that such weapons are stored in a weapons storage room of a hunting or sports organisation or of a person who holds a corresponding activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&auml;lismaalane, kes viibib Eestis t&auml;htajalise elamisloa ja t&ouml;&ouml;loa alusel, v&otilde;ib soetada ja omada jahipidamise v&otilde;i vastava spordialaga tegelemise eesm&auml;rgil jahip&uuml;ssi ja sporditulirelva k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras tingimusel, et tal on alalise elukoha j&auml;rgse riigi p&auml;deva asutuse poolt seda liiki relva kohta antud relvaluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An alien who is staying in Estonia on the basis of a temporary residence permit and a work permit may acquire and own a hunting gun or sporting firearm for hunting or engaging in a corresponding sport pursuant to the procedure established by this Act on the condition that the alien holds a weapons permit for such type of weapon which has been granted by a competent authority of the state of the alien's permanent residence. </inglise>
<eesti>Vintraudset tulirelva tuleb sellisel juhul hoida jahindus- v&otilde;i spordiorganisatsiooni v&otilde;i vastavat tegevusluba omava isikurelvahoidlas. </eesti>
<inglise>In such cases, firearms with rifled barrels shall be stored in a weapons storage room of a hunting or sports organisation or of a person who holds a corresponding activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eestis seaduslikult viibiv v&auml;lismaalane, keda ei ole nimetatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 ning kes on v&auml;hemalt 18-aastane, v&otilde;ib Politseiameti antud soetamisloa alusel soetada Eestist v&auml;ljaviimiseks relva ja laskemoona tingimusel, et tal on alalise elukoha j&auml;rgse riigi p&auml;deva asutuse poolt v&auml;ljastatud luba seda liiki relva ja laskemoona soetamiseks ning ta kohustub soetatava relva ja laskemoona Eestist lahkumisel v&auml;lja viima. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An alien who is staying legally in Estonia, who is not listed in subsections (1) or (2) of this section and who is at least 18 years of age may, on the basis of an acquisition permit issued by the Police Board, acquire a weapon and ammunition for the purposes of taking the weapon or ammunition out of Estonia on the condition that he or she holds a permit issued by a competent authority of the state of his or her permanent residence for the acquisition of such type of weapon or ammunition and that he or she assumes the obligation to take the weapon or ammunition with him or her upon departure from Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Eestis spordiv&otilde;istlusel, &otilde;ppusel v&otilde;i jahil viibiv v&auml;lismaalane v&otilde;ib soetada laskemoona teda kutsunud isiku v&otilde;i asutuse kirjalikul taotlusel relva ajutise sisseveo loa esitamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An alien who is staying in Estonia for a sports event, exercises or hunting may acquire ammunition on the basis of a written application made by the person who or agency which invited him or her and upon submission of a temporary weapons import permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetatava laskemoona &uuml;hekordne kogus ei tohi &uuml;letada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 46 l&otilde;ikes 4 n&auml;idatud kogust. </eesti>
<inglise>The quantity of ammunition acquired on any single occasion shall not exceed the quantity indicated in subsection 46 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) V&auml;lisriigi diplomaatilise v&otilde;i konsulaaresinduse t&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes on v&auml;lisriigi kodanik, v&otilde;ib soetada ja vallata relva, v&auml;lja arvatud kumminui, k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras V&auml;lisministeeriumi taotlusel oma elukoha j&auml;rgse politseiprefektuuri antud loa alusel tingimusel, et tal on kodakondsusj&auml;rgse riigi relvaluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An employee of a diplomatic or consular representation of a foreign state who is a foreign citizen may acquire and possess a weapon, except a truncheon, pursuant to the procedure provided by this Act, on the application of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and on the basis of a permit granted by the police prefecture of his or her residence on the condition that he or she holds a weapons permit of the state of his or her citizenship. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilisele isikule lubatud relvade otstarve, liigid ja hulk </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose, types and quantity of weapons permitted for legal persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juriidiline isik v&otilde;ib soetada, omada v&otilde;i vallata relvi j&auml;rgmisel otstarbel: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A legal person may acquire, own or possess a weapon for the following purposes: </inglise>
<eesti>1) sisevalveks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) internal guarding; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vastava spordiala v&otilde;i jahindusega tegelemiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) engaging in corresponding sports or in hunting; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &otilde;ppet&ouml;&ouml;ks relvadega seonduvates &otilde;ppeainetes; </eesti>
<inglise>3) studying subjects related to weapons; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kollektsioneerimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) collecting; </inglise>
<eesti>5) turvateenuse osutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>5) providing security services. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seadusega juriidilisele isikule antud &otilde;igused ja temale pandud kohustused laienevad f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjale ning riigi- ja kohaliku omavalitsuse asutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The rights granted to and the duties imposed on legal persons by this Act also apply to sole proprietors and state and local government agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Turvateenuse osutamiseks v&otilde;i sisevalveks v&otilde;ib omada v&otilde;i vallata j&auml;rgmisi relvi: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following weapons may be owned or possessed for the provision of security services or for internal guarding: </inglise>
<eesti>1) sileraudne p&uuml;ss; </eesti>
<inglise>1) guns with a smoothbore barrel; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vintraudne p&uuml;ss; </eesti>
<inglise>2) guns with a rifled barrel; </inglise>
<eesti>3) p&uuml;stol; </eesti>
<inglise>3) pistols; </inglise>
<eesti>4) revolver; </eesti>
<inglise>4) revolvers; </inglise>
<eesti>5) gaasip&uuml;stol; </eesti>
<inglise>5) gas pistols; </inglise>
<eesti>6) gaasirevolver; </eesti>
<inglise>6) gas revolvers; </inglise>
<eesti>7) kumminui. </eesti>
<inglise>7) truncheons. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Turvateenuse osutamiseks ja sisevalveks lubatud relvade kogused liikide j&auml;rgi m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks asukohaj&auml;rgne politseiprefektuur kirjaliku taotluse alusel, arvestades valvatavate ja kaitstavate objektide iseloomu ning ohustatuse astet ning tulirelvade hoiutingimusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The quantities of weapons, by type of weapon, permitted for the provision of security services and for internal guarding shall be determined by the police prefecture of the seat of the legal person on the basis of a written application, taking into account the nature of the guarded and protected objects, the degree of threat and the storage conditions for firearms. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui valvatav ja kaitstav objekt asub teise politseiprefektuuri teenistuspiirkonnas, koosk&otilde;lastab taotluse selle esitaja objekti asukoha j&auml;rgse politseiprefektuuriga. </eesti>
<inglise>If a guarded or protected object is located in the service area of another police prefecture, the applicant shall obtain authorisation for the application from the police prefecture of the location of the object. </inglise>
<eesti>Turvateenuse osutamiseks ja sisevalveks etten&auml;htud tulirelvade ja gaasirelvade arv kokku ning kumminuiade arv v&otilde;ib olla 10% suurem objekte vahetult valvavate v&otilde;i kaitsvate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate arvust. </eesti>
<inglise>The total number of firearms and gas weapons and the number of truncheons intended for the provision of security services shall not be greater than 10 per cent of the number of employees directly engaged in the guarding and protection of the object. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Laskmisega seotud spordialaga tegelemiseks v&otilde;ib omada v&otilde;i vallata mitte &uuml;le 200 sporditulirelva, pneumorelva ja ammu. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) For the purposes of engaging in sports involving shooting, the number of sporting firearms, pneumatic weapons and crossbows owned or possessed shall not exceed 200. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Jahindusega tegelemiseks v&otilde;ib omada v&otilde;i vallata kahte jahip&uuml;ssi iga jahindusega tegeleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) For the purposes of hunting, two hunting guns may be owned or possessed per employee involved in hunting. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) &Otilde;ppet&ouml;&ouml;ks relvadega seonduvates &otilde;ppeainetes v&otilde;ib omada v&otilde;i vallata kokku mitte &uuml;le 50 p&uuml;ssi, p&uuml;stoli ja revolvri. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) For the purposes of studying subjects related to weapons, the number of guns, pistols and revolvers owned or possessed shall not exceed 50. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvasoetamisluba </eesti>
<inglise>Acquisition permit for weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 19 nimetatud relvade ja laskemoona soetamiseks, v&auml;lja arvatud &sect;-des 5 ja 7 ning &sect; 9 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud juhtudel, on vajalik relvasoetamisluba (edaspidi soetamisluba). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to acquire weapons and ammunition specified in &sect; 19 of this Act, an acquisition permit for weapons (hereinafter acquisition permit) is required, except in the cases provided for in &sect;&sect; 5 and 7 and subsection 9 (3). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Soetamisluba annab selles n&auml;idatud isikule &otilde;iguse loal m&auml;rgitud relvaliigi hulka kuuluva relva soetamiseks, selle j&auml;rgnevaks hoidmiseks ja edasitoimetamiseks kuni relva registreerimiseni, samuti vastava laskemoona soetamiseks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 46 l&otilde;ikes 4 n&auml;idatud koguses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An acquisition permit grants the person indicated therein the right to acquire a weapon of the type set out in the permit, and subsequently to store and convey the weapon until it is registered, and also to acquire corresponding ammunition in the quantity indicated in subsection 46 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Soetamisloa v&auml;ljastab relva soetamist taotlevale isikule tema elu- v&otilde;i asukoha j&auml;rgne politseiprefektuur, k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 30 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud juhul aga Politseiamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An acquisition permit shall be issued to a person who applies for permission to acquire a weapon by the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the person or, in the case provided for in subsection 30 (3) of this Act, by the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Soetamisluba antakse ainult seda liiki relva soetamiseks, mis vastab otstarbele, milleks relva taotletakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An acquisition permit is granted only for the acquisition of a type of weapon which corresponds to the purpose for which permission to acquire a weapon is applied for. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Soetamisluba koosneb A-, B-, C- ja D-osast, millel on j&auml;rgmine otstarve: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An acquisition permit consists of Parts A, B, C and D, which have the following purpose: </inglise>
<eesti>1) A-osa j&auml;&auml;b relva m&uuml;&uuml;jale; </eesti>
<inglise>1) part A remains with the seller of the weapon; </inglise>
<eesti>2) B-osa on relva registreerimise ja relvaloa v&auml;ljastamise alusdokumendiks ja j&auml;&auml;b relva registreerinud politseiprefektuurile; </eesti>
<inglise>2) part B is the source document for the registration of the weapon and issue of a weapons permit and shall remain with the police prefecture which registers the weapon; </inglise>
<eesti>3) C-osa j&auml;&auml;b soetamisloa v&auml;ljastanud politseiasutusele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) part C remains with the police prefecture which issues the acquisition permit; </inglise>
<eesti>4) D-osa j&auml;&auml;b relvaomanikule ja annab &otilde;iguse sellele m&auml;rgitud relva edasitoimetamiseks soetamiskohast politseiprefektuuri ja hoiukohta ning relva hoidmiseks kuni relvaloa v&otilde;i relva Eestist v&auml;ljaviimise eriloa saamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>4) part D remains with the owner of the weapon and gives the owner the right to convey the weapon from the place of its acquisition to a police prefecture and the place of its storage and for the storage of the weapon until a weapons permit or special permission to take the weapon out of Estonia is obtained. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetamisloa D-osa tagastatakse politseiasutusele relvaloa v&otilde;i relva Eestist v&auml;ljaviimise eriloa saamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>Part D of an acquisition permit shall be returned to the police authorities when a weapons permit or special permission to take the weapon out of Estonia has been obtained. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Loa igale osale kannab soetamisloa v&auml;ljastaja andmed relva soetaja ja soetada lubatud relva liigi ja arvu kohta, samuti soetamisloa v&auml;ljastanud politseiasutuse ja politseiametniku nime. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) On each part of an acquisition permit, the issuer of the permit shall enter information concerning the acquirer of the weapon, the type of weapon and the number of weapons and also the name of the police authority and police officer which issued the acquisition permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetamisloa A-, B- ja D-osale kannab relva m&uuml;&uuml;ja andmed m&uuml;&uuml;dud relva ja selle m&uuml;&uuml;ja kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>On Parts A, B and D of the acquisition permit, the seller of the weapon shall enter information concerning the weapon being sold and the seller of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Soetamisluba on kehtiv kolme kuu jooksul, arvates loa v&auml;ljastamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) An acquisition permit is valid for three months as of its date of issue. </inglise>
<eesti>Luba v&otilde;idakse pikendada kolme kuu v&otilde;rra, kui pikendamise taotlus on esitatud enne soetamisloa kehtivusaja l&otilde;ppu. </eesti>
<inglise>A permit may be extended for three months if an application for extension is submitted before the expiry of the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetamisloa kehtivusaja l&otilde;ppemisel tuleb taotleda uus soetamisluba. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the expiry of the period of validity of an acquisition permit, a new acquisition permit shall be applied for. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Soetamisloa h&auml;vimisest v&otilde;i kadumisest on loa omaja kohustatud viivitamata teatama loa v&auml;ljastajale v&otilde;i oma elu- v&otilde;i asukoha j&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The holder of an acquisition permit is required to notify the issuer of the permit or the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the holder promptly if the permit is destroyed or lost. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Soetamisloa vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) The standard format for acquisition permits shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva registreerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva soetanud isik on kohustatud seitsme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates relva soetamise p&auml;evast, v&auml;lisriigist soetamise puhul aga relva Eestisse saabumise p&auml;evast, registreerima selle elu- v&otilde;i asukohaj&auml;rgses politseiprefektuuris. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who has acquired a weapon is required to register the weapon at the police prefecture of the residence or location of the person within seven working days as of the date on which the weapon was acquired or, if the weapon was acquired in a foreign state, as of the date of the weapon entering Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relv esitatakse registreerimiseks koos soetamisloaga, millele relva m&uuml;&uuml;ja on kandnud andmed m&uuml;&uuml;dud relva kohta, kui relv on ostetud relvade m&uuml;&uuml;gi tegevusluba omavalt isikult. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A weapon shall be presented for registration together with an acquisition permit in which the seller of the weapon has entered information concerning the weapon being sold if the weapon has been purchased from a person who holds an activity licence for the sale of weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui relv on soetatud muul k&auml;esoleva seadusega lubatud viisil, esitatakse selle registreerimiseks soetamisluba ning soetamise seaduslikkust t&otilde;endav dokument. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a weapon is acquired in any other manner permitted by this Act, the acquisition permit and a document in proof of the legality of the acquisition shall be presented for registration of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetamisluba ei n&otilde;uta p&auml;ritud, leitud v&otilde;i &uuml;hisomandis oleva relva, samuti k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 34 l&otilde;ikes 9 nimetatud nimelise tulirelva registreerimisel. </eesti>
<inglise>An acquisition permit is not required for the registration of a weapon which is succeeded to, found, in joint ownership, or specified in subsection 34 (9) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Relva registreerimisel kontrollitakse selle vastavust soetamisloale v&otilde;i relva soetamise seaduslikkust t&otilde;endavale muule dokumendile kantud andmetega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon the registration of a weapon, it shall be verified that the information entered on the acquisition permit or other document in proof of the legality of its acquisition corresponds to the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Relva registreerimisel vormistatakse iga relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja kohta toimik (edaspidi relvatoimik). </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon the registration of a weapon, a register book shall be prepared concerning each owner or possessor of the weapon (hereinafter weapon register book). </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Relvatoimikut peetakse relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja elu- v&otilde;i asukoha j&auml;rgses politseiprefektuuris. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A weapon register book shall be maintained at the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the owner or possessor of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui relvad asuvad teise politseiprefektuuri teenistuspiirkonnas olevas relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja tegutsemiskohas, peetakse relvatoimikut ka tegutsemiskohaj&auml;rgses politseiprefektuuris. </eesti>
<inglise>If the weapons are located at the place of business of the owner or possessor of the weapon and if the place of business is located in the service area of another police prefecture, a weapon register book shall also be maintained at the police prefecture of the place of business of the owner or possessor. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Relvatoimikusse pannakse k&otilde;ik soetamisloa ja relvaloa taotlemise, v&auml;ljastamise, v&auml;ljastamisest keeldumise, kehtivuse pikendamise ja peatamise ning kehtetuks tunnistamisega seotud dokumendid, samuti dokumendid relva soetamise, &uuml;mbertegemise ja v&otilde;&otilde;randamise ning relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele vastavuse ja relva hoidmise tingimuste kontrollimise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) All documents concerning application for, issue of, refusal to issue, extension, suspension and revocation of the acquisition permit and weapons permit, shall be entered in the weapon register book, as well as documentation concerning the acquisition, conversion and transfer of the weapon, verification that the owner or possessor of the weapon meets the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof and inspection of the storage conditions for the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Relva registreerimise ajaks v&otilde;ib relvaomanik v&otilde;i -valdaja anda selle hoiule politseiprefektuuri v&otilde;i hoida seda oma elu- v&otilde;i asukohas k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras ja tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) During the time a weapon is being registered, the owner or possessor of the weapon may deposit the weapon at a police prefecture or store the weapon at the residence or seat of the person pursuant to the procedure and under the conditions established by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvaluba </eesti>
<inglise>Weapons permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva registreerimisel v&auml;ljastab politseiprefektuur relvaomanikule v&otilde;i -valdajale relvaloa. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the registration of a weapon, the police prefecture shall issue a weapons permit to the owner or possessor of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvaloa v&auml;ljastamise aluseks on politseiprefektuuri juhi kirjalik otsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The basis for the issue of a weapons permit is a written decision made by the head of a police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) F&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku relvaluba annab selle omanikule &otilde;iguse relva ja selle laskemoona hoidmiseks, kandmiseks ja edasitoimetamiseks k&auml;esoleva seaduse ning selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras, samuti relvamudelile vastava laskemoona soetamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A weapons permit held by a natural person grants the holder of the permit the right to store, carry and convey a weapon and ammunition therefor pursuant to the procedure and under the conditions provided for in this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof, and also the right to acquire ammunition which corresponds to the model of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetatava laskemoona &uuml;hekordne kogus ei tohi &uuml;letada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 46 l&otilde;ikes 4 n&auml;idatud kogust. </eesti>
<inglise>The quantity of ammunition purchased on any single occasion shall not exceed the quantity indicated in subsection 46 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) F&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule kuuluva relva kohta v&otilde;idakse v&auml;ljastada mitu relvaluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Several weapons permits may be issued for a weapon belonging to a natural person. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvaluba, mis on v&auml;ljastatud f&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule, kes ei ole relva omanik, nimetatakse paralleelrelvaloaks. </eesti>
<inglise>A weapons permit issued to a natural person who is not the owner of the weapon is called a parallel weapons permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Paralleelrelvaluba antakse &uuml;hele v&otilde;i kahele f&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule juhul, kui relvaomanik on andnud kirjaliku n&otilde;usoleku temale kuuluva relva kasutamiseks konkreetselt n&auml;idatud isiku v&otilde;i isikute poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A parallel weapons permit shall be granted to one or two natural persons if the owner of the weapon has granted written authorisation for the person or persons specified to use the weapon belonging to the owner. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Relva andmisel paralleelrelvaloa omaja valdusse koostatakse akt relva &uuml;leandmise-vastuv&otilde;tmise kohta, n&auml;idates selles relva vastuv&otilde;tmise koha, kuup&auml;eva ja kellaaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon the delivery of a weapon into the possession of a holder of a parallel weapons permit, an instrument of delivery and receipt shall be prepared concerning the weapon which sets out the place, date and time of receipt of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Akt koostatakse kahes eksemplaris, millest &uuml;ks j&auml;&auml;b relva &uuml;leandjale, teine vastuv&otilde;tjale. </eesti>
<inglise>The instrument shall be prepared in two original copies of which one shall be retained by the deliverer and the other by the recipient of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva tagastamisel omanikule koostatakse analoogne akt. </eesti>
<inglise>An identical instrument shall be prepared upon the return of the weapon to the owner. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Juriidilise isiku relvaluba annab selle omajale &otilde;iguse vastava laskemoona soetamiseks, relva ja laskemoona hoidmiseks ja edasitoimetamiseks (veoks) ning &otilde;iguse anda relva ja laskemoona oma t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele kandmiseks k&auml;esoleva seaduse ning selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud korras ja tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A weapons permit held by a legal person grants the holder of the permit the right to acquire corresponding ammunition, to store and convey (transport) the weapon and ammunition, and to issue the weapon and ammunition to its employees pursuant to the procedure and under the conditions provided for in this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Relvaloa kehtivus on viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The duration of a weapons permit is five years. </inglise>
<eesti>Paralleelrelvaloa kehtivus on piiratud relvaomaniku relvaloa kehtivusega ja paralleelrelvaluba kaotab kehtivuse relvaomaniku relvaloa kehtetuks tunnistamise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>The duration of a parallel weapons permit is limited by the duration of the weapons permit held by the owner of the weapon, and a parallel weapons permit becomes invalid upon revocation of the weapons permit held by the owner of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Relvaluba antakse v&auml;lja l&uuml;hemaks t&auml;htajaks: </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A weapons permit shall be issued for a shorter period: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kui taotleja seda soovib; </eesti>
<inglise>1) if so requested by the applicant; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isikule, kes viibib riigis v&auml;hem kui viis aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to a person who is staying in Estonia for less than five years; </inglise>
<eesti>3) juriidilisele isikule, kelle tegevuse m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaeg on l&uuml;hem kui viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to a legal person whose specified term of activity is less than five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Isikule, keda siseminister v&otilde;i kaitseminister on seaduses s&auml;testatud korras autasustanud nimelise tulirelvaga, antakse nimelise relva relvaluba ilma kehtivusaega m&auml;&auml;ramata. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) A person who has been awarded a weapon registered in his or her own name by the Minister of Internal Affairs or the Minister of Defence pursuant to the procedure provided by law shall be granted a weapons permit for the weapon without a specified term. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Relvaloa h&auml;vimisest v&otilde;i kadumisest on selle omaja kohustatud viivitamata kirjalikult teatama loa v&auml;ljastanud v&otilde;i oma elu- v&otilde;i asukoha j&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) The holder of a weapons permit is required to notify the issuer of the permit or the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the holder promptly in writing if the permit is destroyed or lost. </inglise>
<eesti>(11) Relvaloa, sealhulgas paralleelrelvaloa vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(11) The standard format for weapons permits, including the standard format for parallel weapons permits, shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetamisloa ja relvaloa taotlemine f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku poolt </eesti>
<inglise>Application by natural person for acquisition permit or weapons permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku taotluse soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa saamiseks vaatab l&auml;bi elukohaj&auml;rgne politseiprefektuur, k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 30 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud juhul aga Politseiamet, hiljemalt kahe kuu jooksul, arvates k&otilde;igi n&otilde;utavate dokumentide esitamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An application submitted by a natural person for an acquisition permit or a weapons permit shall be reviewed by the police prefecture of the residence of the person or, in the case provided for in subsection 30 (3) of this Act, by the Police Board not later than within two months as of the date of submission of all required documents. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa saamiseks on taotleja kohustatud esitama: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to obtain an acquisition permit or a weapons permit, an applicant is required to submit: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kirjaliku avalduse, n&auml;idates selles soetada soovitava relva otstarbe, margi v&otilde;i liigi v&otilde;i konkreetse relva ja ka selle omaniku, kui tegemist on paralleelrelvaloa taotlemisega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a written application which sets out the purpose and the mark or type of weapon or the specific weapon which the applicant wishes to acquire and, in the case of an application for a parallel weapons permit, also the owner; </inglise>
<eesti>2) dokumendid, mis t&otilde;endavad tema vastavust k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 29 v&otilde;i 30 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) documents which certify that the applicant meets the requirements provided for in &sect; 29 or 30 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) arstliku l&auml;bivaatuse alusel tehtud j&auml;reldusotsuse; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a conclusion prepared on the basis of the results of a medical examination; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kaks fotot m&otilde;&otilde;tmetega 3&times;4 cm; </eesti>
<inglise>4) two photographs measuring 3&times;4 cm; </inglise>
<eesti>5) riigil&otilde;ivu tasumist t&otilde;endava dokumendi. </eesti>
<inglise>5) a document certifying payment of the state fee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa taotleja arstliku l&auml;bivaatuse ja j&auml;reldusotsuse vormistamise korra kehtestab sotsiaalminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for performing the medical examination of an applicant for an acquisition permit or a weapons permit and for formalising the results thereof shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Paralleelrelvaloa taotleja peab esitama ka relvaomaniku kirjaliku n&otilde;usoleku tema relva kasutamiseks paralleelrelvaloa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An applicant for a parallel weapons permit shall also submit the written consent of the owner of the weapon for the applicant to use the owner's weapon on the basis of a parallel weapons permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Soetamisluba v&otilde;i relvaluba v&otilde;ib taotleda isik, kes on sooritanud relva soetamist, registreerimist, hoidmist, kandmist, v&otilde;&otilde;randamist ja seaduslikku kasutamist reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete tundmise eksami ning laskevigastuse korral kannatanule esmaabi andmise eksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Any person who has passed an examination on his or her knowledge of the requirements of legislation regulating the acquisition, registration, storage, carrying, transfer and legal use of weapons and of the provision of first aid to a victim with a shooting injury may apply for an acquisition permit or a weapons permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Tulirelva relvaloa taotlemise korral tuleb sooritada eksami k&auml;igus tulirelva tundmise test ning tulirelva k&auml;sitsemise katse. </eesti>
<inglise>If an application is made for a weapons permit for firearms, the applicant shall, as part of the examination, pass a test on his or her knowledge of firearms and a practical test on handling firearms. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 nimetatud eksami korra kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The procedure for the examination specified in subsection (5) of this section shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 3 ja l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uded ei laiene politseiametnikule ja lepingulises tegevteenistuses olevale kaitsev&auml;elasele, samuti k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 30 l&otilde;igetes 2, 3 ja 5 nimetatud isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The requirements provided for in clauses (2) 3) and 5) of this section do not apply to police officers, to members of the Defence Forces who are in contractual active service and to persons specified in subsections 30 (2), (3) and (5) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Relvaloa omaja ei pea relvaloa kehtivuse ajal teise ja iga j&auml;rgmise sama liiki relva soetamisel l&auml;bima arstlikku l&auml;bivaatust ega sooritama uut eksamit. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) If a holder of a weapons permit wishes to acquire a weapon of the same type as the weapon indicated in the weapons permit during the term of the weapons permit, the holder is not required to undergo a new medical examination or retake the examination. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>F&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule soetamisloa ja relvaloa andmist v&auml;listavad asjaolud </eesti>
<inglise>Circumstances precluding grant of acquisition permit or weapons permit to natural person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Soetamisluba ega relvaluba ei anta f&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule, kes: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An acquisition permit or a weapons permit shall not be granted to a natural person who: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on narkootiliste ja ps&uuml;hhotroopsete ainete kasutamisest tingitud ps&uuml;&uuml;hika- v&otilde;i k&auml;itumish&auml;irega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) suffers from a mental or behavioural disorder caused by the use of narcotic or psychotropic substances; </inglise>
<eesti>2) on raskekujulise ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) suffers from a severe mental disorder; </inglise>
<eesti>3) on f&uuml;&uuml;silise puudega, mis takistab tema poolt taotletava relva &otilde;iget k&auml;sitsemist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) suffers from a physical disability which prevents him or her from handling the weapon applied for by him or her adequately; </inglise>
<eesti>4) hoidub k&otilde;rvale kaitsev&auml;eteenistusest; </eesti>
<inglise>4) evades service in the Defence Forces; </inglise>
<eesti>5) on tunnistatud teov&otilde;imetuks v&otilde;i kelle teov&otilde;imet on piiratud; </eesti>
<inglise>5) is divested of active legal capacity or whose active legal capacity is restricted; </inglise>
<eesti>6) on kriminaalkorras karistatud; </eesti>
<inglise>6) has been punished under criminal procedure; </inglise>
<eesti>7) on halduskorras karistatud relva ja laskemoona soetamist, hoidmist, kandmist, vedu v&otilde;i kasutamist reguleeriva &otilde;igusaktiga s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uete rikkumise eest v&otilde;i jahipidamise eest ilma jahitunnistuseta. </eesti>
<inglise>7) has been punished under administrative procedure for violating requirements provided by legislation regulating the acquisition, storage, carrying, transport or use of weapons and ammunition, or for hunting without a hunting certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>8) on kriminaalmenetlusest tulenevatel alustel kuulutatud tagaotsitavaks, tunnistatud kahtlustatavaks, v&otilde;etud vastutusele s&uuml;&uuml;distatavana v&otilde;i antud kohtu alla; </eesti>
<inglise>8) on grounds arising from criminal proceedings, is declared to be a fugitive or suspect or is brought to justice as the accused or accused at trial; </inglise>
<eesti>9) on soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa taotlemisel tahtlikult esitanud valeandmeid, millel on oluline t&auml;htsus loa andmise k&uuml;simuse otsustamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>9) upon application for an acquisition permit or weapons permit, has knowingly submitted incorrect information which is of material importance to the decision on whether to issue a permit; </inglise>
<eesti>10) ei oma k&auml;esoleva seadusega etten&auml;htud tingimusi relva ja laskemoona hoidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>10) lacks the conditions prescribed by this Act for the storage of weapons and ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 6 ja 7 s&auml;testatud keeld ei laiene isikule, kelle karistusandmed on kustutatud karistusregistrist karistusregistri seaduse (RT I 1997, 87, 1467; 1998, 111, 1830; 2001, 93, 565) kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The prohibition provided for in clauses (1) 6) and 7) of this section does not apply to a person if information concerning his or her punishment has been expunged from the punishment register pursuant to the Punishment Register Act (RT I 1997, 87, 1467; 1998, 111, 1830; 2001, 93, 565). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1, 2 ja 3 nimetatud ps&uuml;&uuml;hika- ja k&auml;itumish&auml;irete ning f&uuml;&uuml;siliste puuete loetelu kehtestab sotsiaalminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The list of mental or behavioural disorders and physical disabilities specified in clauses (1) 1), 2) and 3) of this section shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Peale k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud aluste v&otilde;ib loa andja keelduda soetamisloa ja relvaloa andmisest: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In addition to the bases for refusal indicated in subsection (1) of this section, an issuer of permits may refuse to grant an acquisition permit or a weapons permit: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isikule, kellele varem v&auml;ljastatud relvaloa kehtetuks tunnistamisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud v&auml;hem kui viis aastat ja loa kehtetuks tunnistamine oli tingitud relva kaotsiminekust v&otilde;i relva ja laskemoona hoidmist, kandmist v&otilde;i kasutamist reguleerivas &otilde;igusaktis s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uete rikkumisest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to a person if less than five years have passed since the revocation of a weapons permit previously issued to the person and if the revocation of the permit was due to the loss of the weapon or a violation of the requirements provided for in legislation regulating the storage, carrying or use of weapons and ammunition; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isikule, kellele soetamisloa andmisest on varem keeldutud, kusjuures sellest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud v&auml;hem kui kaks aastat ja keeldumine oli tingitud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 8-10 nimetatud asjaoludest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to a person to whom the issue of an acquisition permit has previously been refused if less than two years have passed since the refusal and if the refusal was due to the circumstances specified in clauses (1) 8) -10) of this section; </inglise>
<eesti>3) isikule, kes enda v&otilde;i teise isiku turvalisust ohustava eluviisi v&otilde;i k&auml;itumise t&otilde;ttu on sobimatu antud liiki relva soetama ja omama. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to a person who is not suitable to acquire or own a weapon due to his or her lifestyle or behaviour which jeopardises the security of himself or herself or other persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa andmise v&otilde;i andmisest keeldumise otsus vormistatakse kirjalikult, n&auml;idates keeldumise puhul keeldumise p&otilde;hjuse &uuml;hes viitega keeldumise aluseks oleva seaduse s&auml;ttele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A decision to issue or to refuse to issue an acquisition permit or a weapons permit shall be prepared in writing and, if the decision is one of refusal, shall set out the reason for refusal together with a reference to the provision of law on the basis of which the issue of a permit was refused. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus tehakse teatavaks v&otilde;i saadetakse taotluse esitajale k&uuml;mne p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision shall be communicated or sent to the applicant within ten days as of the date on which the decision is made. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetamisloa ja relvaloa taotlemine juriidilise isiku poolt </eesti>
<inglise>Application by legal person for acquisition permit or weapons permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juriidilise isiku taotluse soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa saamiseks v&otilde;tab vastu asukohaj&auml;rgne politseiprefektuur ja vaatab selle l&auml;bi hiljemalt kahe kuu jooksul, arvates k&otilde;igi n&otilde;utavate dokumentide esitamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An application submitted by a legal person for an acquisition permit or a weapons permit shall be received by the police prefecture of the seat of the legal person and reviewed not later than within two months as of the date of submission of all required documents. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa taotleja on kohustatud esitama: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An applicant for an acquisition permit or a weapons permit is required to submit: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kirjaliku avalduse, p&otilde;hjendades selles relvade vajalikkust ja n&auml;idates soetada soovitavate relvade otstarbe, margi v&otilde;i liigi ja koguse; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a written application which sets out the reasons as to why the weapons are needed and indicates the purpose, mark or type and number of weapons which the applicant wishes to acquire; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &auml;rakirja juriidilise isiku otsusest juriidilise isiku relvade ja laskemoona eest vastutava isiku ja tema asendaja m&auml;&auml;ramise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a copy of a decision made by the legal person concerning the appointment of a person responsible for weapons and ammunition and of his or her substitute; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &otilde;iendi, milles on vastutava isiku ja tema asendaja ees- ja perekonnanimi, isikukood, elukoht, ametikoht ja telefoninumber, andmed eksami sooritamise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a certificate setting out the given name, surname, personal identification code, residence, office and telephone number of the person responsible and of his or her substitute, and information regarding the examination having been passed by such persons; </inglise>
<eesti>4) juriidilise isiku p&otilde;hikirja (-m&auml;&auml;ruse) ja &auml;riregistri kandeotsuse koopia; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a copy of the articles of association (statutes) of the legal person and a copy of the judgment on its entry in the commercial register; </inglise>
<eesti>5) riigil&otilde;ivu tasumist t&otilde;endava dokumendi; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a document certifying payment of the state fee; </inglise>
<eesti>6) relva kandma hakkavate, k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 51 l&otilde;ikes 1 kehtestatud n&otilde;udele vastavate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate nimekirja, milles on n&auml;idatud nende ees- ja perekonnanimi, isikukood ja elukoht; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a list setting out the given names, surnames, personal identification codes and residences of the persons who are to carry the weapons and who comply with the requirement established by subsection 51 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>7) valvatavate objektide nimekirja, milles on n&auml;idatud nende aadressid, kontaktisikud ja telefoninumbrid, kui relva taotletakse turvateenuse osutamiseks v&otilde;i sisevalveks; </eesti>
<inglise>7) a list of guarded objects which sets out the addresses, contact persons and telephone numbers of the objects if the weapon is applied for in order to provide security services or internal guarding; </inglise>
<eesti>8) relvade hoiukoha ja -tingimuste kirjelduse; </eesti>
<inglise>8) a description of the place of storage and the storage conditions of the weapons; </inglise>
<eesti>9) relvade asukoha j&auml;rgse politseiprefektuuri &otilde;iendi relvade hoiukoha ja -tingimuste n&otilde;uetekohasuse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>9) a certificate issued by the police prefecture of the location of the weapons confirming that the place of storage and the storage conditions of the weapons meet the requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku relvade ja laskemoona eest vastutav isik </eesti>
<inglise>Persons responsible for weapons and ammunition of legal person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juriidilise isiku relvade ja laskemoona eest vastutav isik (edaspidi vastutav isik) vastutab selle eest, et juriidilise isiku relvade ja laskemoona k&auml;itlemine toimuks k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt ning vastaks vastavas loas etten&auml;htud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person responsible for the weapons and ammunition of a legal person (hereinafter person responsible) shall ensure that the weapons and ammunition of the legal person are handled according to this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof and that the handling complies with the conditions set out in the corresponding permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vastutavaks isikuks v&otilde;i tema asendajaks v&otilde;ib olla v&auml;hemalt 21-aastane alaliselt Eestis elav Eesti kodanik, kelle suhtes ei esine k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 4 loetletud asjaolusid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Any citizen of Estonia who is permanently resident in Estonia, who is at least 21 years of age and to whom the circumstances specified in subsections 36 (1) and (4) of this Act do not apply may be a person responsible or a substitute therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vastutavaks isikuks v&otilde;i tema asendajaks v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata isiku, kes on sooritanud vastutava isiku eksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person who has passed the examination for a person responsible may be appointed as a person responsible or a substitute therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) N&otilde;uded vastutava isiku teadmistele ja tema eksamineerimise korra kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The requirements for the expertise of persons responsible and the procedure for their examination shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutava isiku m&auml;&auml;ramine ja tema volituste l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment of person responsible and termination of his or her authority </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vastutav isik m&auml;&auml;ratakse juriidilise isiku kirjaliku otsusega (otsus, korraldus, k&auml;skkiri). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person responsible shall be appointed by a written decision of the legal person (resolution, order, directive). </inglise>
<eesti>Kui juriidilisel isikul on struktuuri&uuml;ksus teises haldus&uuml;ksuses, tuleb vastava otsusega m&auml;&auml;rata ka struktuuri&uuml;ksuse relvade ja laskemoona eest vastutav isik, kellele laienevad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 38 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uded. </eesti>
<inglise>If the legal person has a structural unit within another administrative unit, a person responsible shall also be appointed for weapons and ammunition in the structural unit and the requirements provided for in subsections 38 (2) and (3) of this Act apply to the person. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuse &auml;rakiri saadetakse kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul juriidilise isiku ning struktuuri&uuml;ksuse asukoha j&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>A copy of the decision shall be sent to the police prefecture of the seat of the legal person and its structural unit within three working days. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vastutava isiku volitused l&otilde;pevad tema t&ouml;&ouml;lt vabastamisega v&otilde;i l&otilde;petatakse, kui ta ei vasta enam k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 38 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i on rikkunud k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The authority of a person responsible terminates upon his or her release from work or shall be terminated if the person no longer meets the requirements provided for in subsections 38 (2) and (3) of this Act or has violated the requirements of this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Teade volituste l&otilde;ppemise kohta saadetakse kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul vastavale politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of the termination of authority shall be sent to the corresponding police prefecture within three working days. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vastutava isiku volituste l&otilde;ppemisel m&auml;&auml;ratakse viivitamata vastutava isiku kohuset&auml;itjaks tema asendaja ning tehakse relvade ja laskemoona inventuur. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the termination of the authority of a person responsible, his or her substitute shall be promptly appointed as an acting person responsible and an inventory of weapons and ammunition shall be conducted. </inglise>
<eesti>Hiljemalt kahe kuu jooksul, arvates volituste l&otilde;ppemisest, m&auml;&auml;ratakse uus vastutav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>A new person responsible shall be appointed not later than within two months as of the termination of the authority of the former person responsible. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vastutava isiku m&auml;&auml;ramine ei vabasta juriidilise isiku juhatust v&otilde;i seda asendavat organit vastutusest selle eest, et relvade ja laskemoonaga seotud tegevus vastaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja muude &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The appointment of a person responsible does not release the managing board or body substituting for the management board of the legal person from the responsibility of ensuring that weapons and ammunition related activities comply with this Act and other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilisele isikule soetamisloa ja relvaloa andmist v&auml;listavad asjaolud </eesti>
<inglise>Circumstances precluding grant of acquisition permit or weapons permit to legal person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Soetamisluba ega relvaluba ei anta juriidilisele isikule: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An acquisition permit or a weapons permit shall not be granted to a legal person which: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kes on loa taotlemisel esitanud valeandmeid, millel on oluline t&auml;htsus loa v&auml;ljastamise k&uuml;simuse otsustamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) upon application for a permit, has knowingly submitted incorrect information which is of material importance to the decision on whether to issue a permit; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kellel ei ole k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud tingimusi relva ja laskemoona hoidmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) lacks the conditions prescribed by this Act for the storage of weapons and ammunition; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kes on viimase kolme aasta jooksul v&auml;hemalt kaks korda rikkunud relva v&otilde;i laskemoona hoidmise, veo v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randamise v&otilde;i relva registreerimise v&otilde;i relva kanda andmise korda; </eesti>
<inglise>3) on at least two occasions during the last three years, has violated the procedure for the storage, transport or transfer of weapons or ammunition or the procedure for the issue of weapons for carrying; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kes ei ole t&auml;itnud j&auml;relevalveorgani ettekirjutust k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusakti n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>4) has not complied with a precept issued by a supervisory body concerning compliance with the requirements of this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juriidilisele isikule soetamisloa ja relvaloa andmise v&otilde;i andmisest keeldumise otsus vormistatakse kirjalikult, n&auml;idates keeldumise puhul keeldumise p&otilde;hjuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A decision to issue or to refuse to issue an acquisition permit to a legal person shall be prepared in writing and, if the decision is one of refusal, shall set out the reason for refusal. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus tehakse teatavaks v&otilde;i saadetakse taotluse esitajale k&uuml;mne p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision shall be communicated or sent to the applicant within ten days as of the decision being made. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvaloa vahetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Replacement of weapons permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relvaluba vahetatakse selle omaja avalduse p&otilde;hjal relvaloa kehtivuse l&otilde;ppemisel, k&otilde;lbmatuks muutumisel v&otilde;i relva v&otilde;i relvaloa omaja andmete muutumisel, samuti relvahoidla asukoha muutumisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A weapons permit shall be replaced on the basis of an application submitted by the holder of the permit upon the expiry of the weapons permit, if the weapons permit becomes unusable, upon amendment of the data concerning the owner of the weapon or the holder of the weapons permit, or upon a change in the location of the weapons storage room. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relvaloa vahetamiseks tuleb elu- v&otilde;i asukohaj&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile esitada: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order for a weapons permit to be replaced, the following shall be submitted to the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the applicant: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kirjalik avaldus, milles n&auml;idatakse vahetamise p&otilde;hjus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a written application which sets out the reasons for replacement; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vahetamisele kuuluv relvaluba; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the weapons permit to be replaced; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riigil&otilde;ivu tasumist t&otilde;endav dokument; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a document certifying payment of the state fee; </inglise>
<eesti>4) foto m&otilde;&otilde;tmetega 3&times;4 cm. </eesti>
<inglise>4) a photograph measuring 3&times;4 cm; </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud dokumendid tuleb politseiprefektuurile esitada seoses: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The documents specified in subsection (2) of this section shall be submitted to the police prefecture at the following times: </inglise>
<eesti>1) relvaloa kehtivuse l&otilde;ppemisega - v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kuu enne kehtivuse l&otilde;ppemist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) upon expiry of the weapons permit - at least one month prior to expiry; </inglise>
<eesti>2) relvaloa k&otilde;lbmatuks muutumisega - vahetult p&auml;rast k&otilde;lbmatuks muutumist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) if the weapons permit becomes unusable - directly after the permit becomes unusable; </inglise>
<eesti>3) relva v&otilde;i relvaloa omaja andmete v&otilde;i relvahoidla asukoha muutumisega - seitsme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates andmete v&otilde;i asukoha muutumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>3) if the data concerning the owner of the weapon or the holder of the weapons permit is amended or the location of the weapons storage room is changed - within seven working days as of the amendment of the data or the change of location. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Paralleelrelvaloa vahetamisel tuleb esitada ka relvaomaniku kirjalik n&otilde;usolek tema relva kasutamiseks paralleelrelvaloa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon replacement of a parallel weapons permit, the applicant shall also submit the written consent of the owner of the weapon for the holder of the permit to use the owner's weapon on the basis of a parallel weapons permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Uus relvaluba v&auml;ljastatakse, kui ei esine k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 36 v&otilde;i 40 s&auml;testatud loa andmist v&auml;listavaid asjaolusid. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A new weapons permit shall be issued if none of the circumstances provided for in &sect; 36 or &sect; 40 of this Act precluding the issue of the permit exist. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Endine relvaluba s&auml;ilitatakse relvatoimikus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The former weapons permit shall be preserved in the weapon register book. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudatuste vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalisation of amendments and changes </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiprefektuuris tuleb vormistada: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following shall be formalised at a police prefecture: </inglise>
<eesti>1) relva &uuml;mbertegemisest tingitud muudatused relvaandmetes (liik, mark, kaliiber, markeering). </eesti>
<inglise>1) amendments to the data concerning a weapon (type, mark, calibre, marking) caused by the conversion of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva &uuml;mbertegemiseks peab olema politseiprefektuuri eelnev luba; </eesti>
<inglise>Prior permission for the conversion of a weapon is required from a police prefecture; </inglise>
<eesti>2) relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja nime muutumisega, elu- v&otilde;i asukoha vahetamisega teise haldus&uuml;ksusesse, relvahoidla asukoha muutumisega seotud muudatused; </eesti>
<inglise>2) amendments relating to the change of name of the owner or possessor of the weapon, change of residence or seat due to resettlement to another administrative unit, or change of location of the weapons storage room; </inglise>
<eesti>3) muudatused muudes teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registrisse kantavates andmetes. </eesti>
<inglise>3) amendments to other data subject to entry in the register of service and civilian weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Muudatuste vormistamiseks tuleb esitada politseiprefektuurile k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 41 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The documents provided for in subsection 41 (2) of this Act shall be submitted to a police prefecture for the formalisation of the amendments and changes. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduses tuleb m&auml;rkida uued relvaandmed, relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja uus nimi, elu- v&otilde;i asukoht, relva hoiukoha uus aadress ja muud muutunud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>The application shall set out the new data concerning the weapon, the new name and residence or seat of the owner or possessor of the weapon, the new address of the place of storage of the weapon and any other amended or changed data. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiprefektuur teeb vastavad kanded relvatoimikusse ja teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registrisse ning v&auml;ljastab uue relvaloa. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The police prefecture shall make corresponding entries in the weapon register book and the register of service and civilian weapons and shall issue a new weapons permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja asumise korral teise politseiprefektuuri teenistuspiirkonda tehakse relvatoimikusse vastav m&auml;rge ja toimik edastatakse koos k&otilde;igi selles sisalduvate materjalidega relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja uue elu- v&otilde;i asukoha j&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the owner or possessor of a weapon resettles to the service area of another police prefecture, a corresponding notice shall be made in the weapon register book and the register book together with all materials included therein shall be forwarded to the police prefecture of the new residence or seat of the owner or possessor of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja uue elu- v&otilde;i asukoha j&auml;rgne politseiprefektuur teeb vajalikud kanded relvatoimikusse ja teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registrisse ning teatab sellest kohe kirjalikult politseiprefektuurile, kus relv oli registreeritud. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The police prefecture of the new residence or seat of the owner or possessor of the weapon shall make the necessary entries in the weapon register book and the register of service and civilian weapons and promptly notify the police prefecture where the weapon was registered in writing of the entries made. </inglise>
<eesti>Teate saanud politseiprefektuur kustutab relva ja relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja oma arvestusest. </eesti>
<inglise>A police prefecture which receives such notice shall delete the weapon and its owner or possessor from its records. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa kehtivuse peatamine ja kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension and revocation of acquisition permit or weapons permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuur peatab loa kehtivuse, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The police prefecture which issued an acquisition permit or a weapons permit shall suspend the permit: </inglise>
<eesti>1) loa omajat on halduskorras karistatud mootors&otilde;iduki, raudteeveeremi v&otilde;i &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki juhtimise eest alkoholi, narkootilise, ps&uuml;hhotroopse v&otilde;i ps&uuml;hhotoksilise aine tarvitamise korral - &uuml;heks aastaks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for one year if the holder of the permit has been punished under administrative procedure for driving a motor vehicle or rail vehicle or flying an aircraft under the influence of alcohol or narcotic, psychotropic or psychotoxic substances; </inglise>
<eesti>2) loa omaja on kriminaalmenetlusest tulenevatel asjaoludel tunnistatud kahtlustatavaks, v&otilde;etud vastutusele s&uuml;&uuml;distatavana v&otilde;i antud kohtu alla; </eesti>
<inglise>2) if the holder of the permit is declared to be a suspect on grounds arising from criminal proceedings or is brought to justice as an accused or accused at trial; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kontrollimisel on tuvastatud, et loa omajal ei ole k&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud tingimusi relva ja laskemoona hoidmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) if it is established in the course of inspection that the holder of the permit lacks the conditions prescribed by this Act for the storage of weapons and ammunition; </inglise>
<eesti>4) juriidiline isik on p&otilde;hjendamatult j&auml;tnud t&auml;itmata j&auml;relevalveorgani ettekirjutuse k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>4) if the legal person has failed to comply with a precept issued by a supervisory body concerning compliance with the requirements of this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof without good reason thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa kehtivuse peatatus l&otilde;petatakse peatamise aluseks olnud asjaolude &auml;ralangemisel v&otilde;i loa kehtetuks tunnistamisel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The suspension of an acquisition permit or a weapons permit is be terminated after elimination of the circumstances which were the basis for suspension or upon revocation of the permit pursuant to the procedure provided for in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuur tunnistab loa kehtetuks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The police prefecture which issued an acquisition permit or a weapons permit shall revoke the permit if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) seda taotleb loa omaja; </eesti>
<inglise>1) so requested by the holder of the permit; </inglise>
<eesti>2) loa omaja ei vasta enam k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the holder of the permit no longer meets the requirements established by this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) relv kuulub erikonfiskeerimisele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the weapon is subject to seizure; </inglise>
<eesti>4) loa omaja on surnud v&otilde;i teadmata kadunuks tunnistatud; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the holder of the permit dies or is declared missing; </inglise>
<eesti>5) relv on kaotsi l&auml;inud v&otilde;i h&auml;vinud; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the weapon is lost or destroyed; </inglise>
<eesti>6) relv on muutunud kasutamisk&otilde;lbmatuks m&auml;&auml;ral, mis ei v&otilde;imalda selle taastamist, v&otilde;i kui relvaomanik v&otilde;i -valdaja ei soovi relva taastada; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the weapon has become unusable to an extent which does not enable it to be restored, or if the owner or possessor of the weapon does not wish the weapon to be restored; </inglise>
<eesti>7) soetamisluba v&otilde;i relvaluba on kaotsi l&auml;inud v&otilde;i h&auml;vinud; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the acquisition permit or weapons permit is destroyed or lost; </inglise>
<eesti>8) juriidiline isik on l&otilde;ppenud v&otilde;i asutus on likvideeritud; </eesti>
<inglise>8) the legal person is dissolved or the agency is liquidated; </inglise>
<eesti>9) relvaomanik v&otilde;i -valdaja on v&auml;hemalt kaks korda viimase kolme aasta jooksul rikkunud k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusakti n&otilde;udeid v&otilde;i on j&auml;tnud t&auml;itmata temale tehtud ettekirjutuse n&otilde;uded. </eesti>
<inglise>9) the owner or possessor of the weapon has, on at least two occasions within the last three years, violated the requirements of this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof or has failed to comply with the requirements of a precept issued to the owner or possessor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Paralleelrelvaluba kaotab kehtivuse v&otilde;i selle kehtivus peatub vastavalt relvaloa kehtetuks tunnistamisel v&otilde;i kehtivuse peatamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A parallel weapons permit shall be revoked or suspended upon the revocation or suspension of the corresponding weapons permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Paralleelrelvaluba v&otilde;idakse tunnistada kehtetuks ka relvaomaniku avalduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>A parallel weapons permit may also be revoked on the basis of an application by the owner of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa kehtivuse peatamine, kehtivuse peatatuse l&otilde;petamine v&otilde;i loa kehtetuks tunnistamine vormistatakse politseiprefektuuri otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Suspension, termination of suspension or revocation of an acquisition permit or a weapons permit shall be formalised by a decision of a police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuses peab olema n&auml;idatud loa kehtivuse peatamise, kehtivuse peatatuse l&otilde;petamise v&otilde;i loa kehtetuks tunnistamise alus viitega seaduse vastavale s&auml;ttele. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision shall also set out the basis for suspension, termination of suspension or revocation with a reference to a corresponding provision of law. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuse koopia saadetakse viivitamata loa omajale. </eesti>
<inglise>A copy of the decision shall promptly be sent to the holder of the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa kehtivuse l&otilde;ppemise, peatamise v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamise tagaj&auml;rjed </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of expiry, suspension or revocation of acquisition permit or weapons permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rast soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa kehtivuse l&otilde;ppemist, peatamist v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamist on loa omaja, vastava relva omanik, valdaja v&otilde;i muu isik, kelle valduses on vastav luba ja relv ning selle laskemoon, kohustatud need loa kehtivuse viimasel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval, kehtetuks tunnistamise v&otilde;i kehtivuse peatamise otsuse k&auml;ttesaamisele j&auml;rgneval t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval &uuml;le andma loa v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuurile ja kui see ei ole v&otilde;imalik, siis relva asukoha j&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) After the expiry, suspension or revocation of an acquisition permit or a weapons permit, the holder of the permit, the owner or possessor of the corresponding weapon or another person who is in possession of the corresponding permit, weapon and ammunition therefor is required to hand them over to the police prefecture which issued the permit or, if this is not possible, to the police prefecture of the location of the weapon, on the last working day on which the permit is valid or on the working day following the date of receipt of the decision of revocation or suspension. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;ib j&auml;tta politseiprefektuuri poolt pitseeritud juriidilise isiku relvahoidlasse. </eesti>
<inglise>A weapon and ammunition of a legal person may be deposited in the weapons storage room of the legal person which has been sealed by the police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Paralleelrelvaloa kehtivuse l&otilde;ppemisel, peatamisel v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamisel peab paralleelrelvaloa omaja k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul tagastama relva ja laskemoona selle omanikule ning paralleelrelvaloa selle v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuurile ja kui see ei ole v&otilde;imalik, siis elukohaj&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the expiry, suspension or revocation of a parallel weapons permit, the holder of the parallel weapons permit shall return the weapon and ammunition to the owner thereof and shall return the parallel weapons permit to the police prefecture which issued the permit or, if this is not possible, to the police prefecture of his or her residence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Loa, relva ja laskemoona &uuml;leandmine v&otilde;ib toimuda nende asukohas v&otilde;i politseiprefektuuris. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A permit, weapon and ammunition may be handed over at its location or at a police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona &uuml;leandmine peab toimuma nende asukohas juhul, kui need annab &uuml;le isik, kes k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&auml;rgi ei olnud nende omanik v&otilde;i valdaja enne soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa kehtetuks tunnistamist ja kes on teatanud politseiprefektuurile enda valduses olevast relvast v&otilde;i laskemoonast. </eesti>
<inglise>A weapon or ammunition shall be handed over at its location if it is handed over before the revocation of the acquisition permit or weapons permit by a person who, pursuant to this Act, is not the owner or possessor and who has informed the police prefecture of the weapon or ammunition which is in his or her possession. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Relva ja laskemoona, samuti kehtivuse kaotanud loa v&otilde;i loa, mille kehtivus on peatatud, &uuml;leandmine-vastuv&otilde;tmine vormistatakse aktiga, milles on kirjas andmed &uuml;leantud relva, laskemoona ja loa kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The handing over and receipt of a weapon and ammunition, and also of an expired or suspended permit, shall be formalised by an instrument of delivery and receipt which sets out the data concerning the weapon, ammunition or permit handed over. </inglise>
<eesti>Akti vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The standard format for such instruments shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>Akt koostatakse kahes eksemplaris ja sellele kirjutavad alla relva, laskemoona v&otilde;i loa &uuml;leandja ja politseiprefektuuri esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>The instrument shall be prepared in two original copies and shall be signed by the person who hands over the weapon, ammunition or permit and by a representative of the police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ks eksemplar aktist j&auml;&auml;b politseiprefektuurile, teine &uuml;leandjale. </eesti>
<inglise>One original copy of the instrument shall be retained by the police prefecture and the other by the person who hands over the weapon, ammunition or permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Politseiprefektuur on kohustatud tagama vastuv&otilde;etud relva ja laskemoona s&auml;ilimise ja seisundi, milles need &uuml;leandmise-vastuv&otilde;tmise aktis fikseeriti. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The police prefecture is required to ensure that the received weapon and ammunition are kept in the same condition as recorded in the instrument of delivery and receipt. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) &Uuml;leandmise p&auml;evast alates on relva- ja laskemoonaomanikul v&otilde;i -valdajal &otilde;igus relv ja laskemoon v&otilde;&otilde;randada kolme kuu jooksul k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras ja tingimustel, v&auml;lja arvatud erikonfiskeerimise otsuse alusel &uuml;leantud relv ja laskemoon. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The owner of the weapon or ammunition handed over has the right to transfer the weapon and ammunition within three months as of the date of delivery pursuant to the procedure and under the conditions provided by this Act, except in the case of weapons and ammunition handed over on the basis of a decision of seizure. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Juhul kui soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa kehtetuks tunnistamise v&otilde;i kehtivuse peatamise otsuse peale esitati kaebus kohtule ja kohus v&otilde;i politseiprefektuur tunnistas loa kehtetuks tunnistamise v&otilde;i kehtivuse peatamise seadusega vastuolus olevaks, on vastava loa, relva ja laskemoona hoiule v&otilde;tnud politseiprefektuur kohustatud need p&auml;rast loa kehtivuse peatatuse l&otilde;petamist v&otilde;i kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumist viivitamata tagastama omanikule v&otilde;i valdajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If a complaint is filed with a court against a decision to revoke or suspend an acquisition permit or a weapons permit and if the court or a police prefecture has declared the revocation or suspension of the permit to be in conflict with the law, the police prefecture which took the corresponding permit, weapon or ammunition into storage shall promptly return the weapon or ammunition to the owner or possessor thereof after termination of the suspension of the permit or entry into force of the judgment. </inglise>
<eesti>Soetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa kehtetuks tunnistamise v&otilde;i kehtivuse peatamise otsuse j&otilde;ussej&auml;&auml;mise korral on relva- ja laskemoonaomanikul v&otilde;i -valdajal &otilde;igus need v&otilde;&otilde;randada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 6 kehtestatud korras alates otsuse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>If the decision to revoke or suspend an acquisition permit or a weapons permit remains in force, the owner or possessor of the weapon or ammunition has the right to transfer the weapon or ammunition pursuant to the procedure established by subsection (6) of this section after the date on which the decision enters into force. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Juhul kui v&otilde;&otilde;randamisele kuuluvat relva ja laskemoona ei ole nende omanik v&otilde;i valdaja k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 6 etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaja jooksul v&otilde;&otilde;randanud, kuulub hoiule antud relv v&otilde;i laskemoon sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) If the owner or possessor of a weapon and ammunition which is subject to transfer has not transferred the weapon and ammunition within the term established by subsection (6) of this section, the weapon and ammunition which have been taken into storage are subject to expropriation. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Laskek&otilde;lbmatuna &uuml;leantud relv ja laskemoon h&auml;vitatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 83 kehtestatud korras </eesti>
<inglise>(9) A weapon or ammunition which is handed over in a condition incapable of firing shall be destroyed pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 83 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona hoidmine </eesti>
<inglise>Storage of Weapons and Ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona hoidmise &uuml;ldn&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>General requirements for storage of weapons or ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;ib hoida isik, kellel on relvaluba v&otilde;i tegevusluba relvade v&otilde;i laskemoona valmistamiseks, m&uuml;&uuml;giks, parandamiseks, &uuml;mbertegemiseks v&otilde;i hoidmiseks teenusena. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Weapons and ammunition may be stored by a person who holds a weapons permit or an activity licence for the manufacture, sale, repair, conversion or storage of weapons and ammunition as a service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relva ja laskemoona tuleb hoida tingimustes, mis tagavad nende s&auml;ilimise ja ohutuse &uuml;mbrusele ning v&auml;listavad neile k&otilde;rvaliste isikute juurdep&auml;&auml;su. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Weapons and ammunition shall be stored in conditions which ensure their preservation and that they do not pose a danger to the surroundings and which preclude access by unauthorised persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tulirelvi v&otilde;ib hoida ainult t&uuml;hjaks laetuna. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Firearms may be stored only in an unloaded state. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Relvi ja laskemoona v&otilde;ib hoida f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku elukohas, juriidilisele isikule kuuluvas v&otilde;i renditud relvahoidlas v&otilde;i anda need hoiule isikule, kellel on tegevusluba relvade v&otilde;i laskemoona hoidmiseks teenusena. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Weapons and ammunition may be stored at the residence of a natural person, in a weapons storage room belonging to or hired by a legal person or deposited for storage with a person who holds an activity licence for the storage of weapons or ammunition as a service. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Relvade ja laskemoona hoiuleandmine teisele isikule vormistatakse &uuml;leandmise-vastuv&otilde;tmise aktiga, mis koostatakse kolmes eksemplaris, millest esimene saadetakse politseiprefektuurile s&auml;ilitamiseks relvatoimikus, teine j&auml;&auml;b hoiuleandjale ja kolmas hoiulev&otilde;tjale. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The deposit of weapons and ammunition with another person shall be formalised by an instrument of delivery and receipt prepared in three original copies of which the first shall be sent to the police prefecture in order to be preserved in the weapon register book, the second shall be retained by the depositor and the third shall be retained by the depositary. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Relvaomanik v&otilde;i -valdaja on kohustatud igast relva kaotsimineku v&otilde;i h&auml;vimise juhtumist viivitamata teatama oma elu- v&otilde;i asukoha j&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Owners or possessors of weapons are required promptly to notify the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the owner or possessor of each case of loss or destruction of a weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>F&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku relvade ja laskemoona hoidmine </eesti>
<inglise>Storage of weapons and ammunition of natural persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;&uuml;siline isik peab temale kuuluvaid v&otilde;i tema valduses olevaid tulirelvi hoidma selleks kohandatud ja p&otilde;randa, seina v&otilde;i ehituskonstruktsiooni k&uuml;lge statsionaarselt kinnitatud raudkapis (edaspidi relvakapp). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A natural person shall store the firearms in his or her ownership or possession in a steel cabinet adapted therefor and permanently attached to the floor, a wall or another structural member of the building (hereinafter weapons safe). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;le kaheksa tulirelva hoidmiseks peab olema selleks spetsiaalselt kohandatud ruum (edaspidi relvahoidla). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A specially adapted room is required for the storage of more than eight firearms (hereinafter weapons storage room). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relvakapp ei ole n&otilde;utav &uuml;he tulirelva puhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The existence of a weapons safe is not required in the case of one firearm. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul tuleb relva ja selle laskemoona hoida k&otilde;rvalisele isikule raskesti avastatavas ja k&auml;ttesaadavas kohas. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case the weapon and ammunition therefor shall be stored in a place which cannot be easily detected or accessed by unauthorised persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) F&uuml;&uuml;siline isik v&otilde;ib hoida laskemoona j&auml;rgmistes kogustes: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A natural person is permitted to store ammunition in the following quantities: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kuni 100 p&uuml;stoli- v&otilde;i revolvripadrunit; </eesti>
<inglise>1) up to 100 pistol or revolver cartridges; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kuni 100 gaasirelvapadrunit; </eesti>
<inglise>2) up to 100 gas weapon cartridges; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kuni 100 padrunit iga vintraudse jahip&uuml;ssi kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) up to 100 cartridges per hunting gun with a rifled barrel; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kuni 300 padrunit iga sileraudse jahip&uuml;ssi kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) up to 300 cartridges per hunting gun with a smoothbore barrel; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kuni 1000 padrunit iga sporditulirelva kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) up to 1000 cartridges per sporting firearm; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kuni 1 kg p&uuml;ssirohtu iga tulirelva kohta, kuid kokku mitte &uuml;le 5 kg; </eesti>
<inglise>6) up to 1 kilogram of propellant per firearm, but not more than 5 kilograms in total; </inglise>
<eesti>7) kuni 1000 s&uuml;tikut. </eesti>
<inglise>7) up to 1000 primers. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Padruneid, p&uuml;ssirohtu ja s&uuml;tikuid v&otilde;ib hoida koos relvadega samas relvakapis, selle eraldi lukustatavas osas v&otilde;i eraldi asuvas lukustatavas raudkapis. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Cartridges, propellant and primers may be stored in the same weapons safe as the weapons, in a separately lockable compartment or in a lockable steel cabinet located separately. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Gaasirelva v&otilde;ib hoida lukustatavas sahtlis v&otilde;i laekas. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Gas weapons shall be stored in a lockable drawer or locker. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) N&otilde;uded relvahoidlale, relvakapile ning p&uuml;ssirohu ja s&uuml;tiku hoidmisele kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The requirements for weapons storage rooms, weapons safes and the storage of propellant and primers shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku relvade ja laskemoona hoidmine </eesti>
<inglise>Storage of weapons and ammunition of legal persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juriidilisel isikul peab tulirelvade ja laskemoona hoidmiseks olema relvahoidla. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A legal person shall have a weapons storage room for the storage of weapons and ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relvi tuleb relvahoidlas hoida relvakappides, mille uste sisek&uuml;lgedel peab olema relvakapis hoitavate relvade nimekiri. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In a weapons storage room, weapons shall be stored in weapons safes which contain a list of the weapons stored in the safe on the inside of the safe door. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Laskemoona hoitakse relvadest eraldi asuvas raudkapis v&otilde;i relvakapi eraldi lukustatavas osas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Ammunition shall be stored in a steel cabinet located separately from the weapons or in a separate lockable compartment of a weapons safe. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Gaasirelvi v&otilde;ib hoida relvakapis v&otilde;i lukustatavas sahtlis v&otilde;i laekas. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Gas weapon shall be stored in a weapons safe, a lockable drawer or a locker. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kuni kaheksa (kaasa arvatud) tulirelva hoidmiseks ei ole relvahoidla n&otilde;utav. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A weapons storage room is not required for the storage of up to eight weapons (inclusive). </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul peab relvakapp asuma ruumis, kus on elektrooniline valveseade, mis l&uuml;litatakse sisse ajal, kui ruumis ei viibi vastutavat isikut. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the weapons safe shall be located in a room equipped with an electronic security device which is switched on when the person responsible is not in the room. </inglise>
<eesti>Ruumi uks peab olema terasplekist v&otilde;i plekiga &uuml;le l&ouml;&ouml;dud ning sellel peab olema v&auml;hemalt kaks lukku. </eesti>
<inglise>The door of the room shall be made of sheet steel or covered with sheet metal and it shall have at least two locks. </inglise>
<eesti>Ruumi aknad peavad olema trellitatud v&otilde;i valmistatud purunemiskindlast klaasist. </eesti>
<inglise>The windows of the room shall be fitted with bars or made of safety glass. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Politseiprefektuurid kontrollivad v&auml;hemalt kaks korda aastas relvade ja laskemoona hoidmise n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmist juriidilise isiku poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Police prefectures shall inspect the compliance of legal persons with the storage requirements for weapons and ammunition at least twice a year. </inglise>
<eesti>Kontrollimise tulemuse kohta koostatakse akt kahes eksemplaris, millest &uuml;ks antakse kontrollitavale isikule ja teine pannakse relvatoimikusse. </eesti>
<inglise>A report concerning the results of inspection shall be prepared in two original copies of which one shall be given to the inspected person and the other shall be annexed to the weapon register book. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona hoidmine spordiv&otilde;istlusel ja treeningul </eesti>
<inglise>Storage of weapons and ammunition during sports events and training </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Spordiv&otilde;istlusele ja treeningule toodud relva ja laskemoona hoitakse lasketiiru relvahoidlas juhul, kui see on olemas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Weapons and ammunition brought to a sports event or to training shall be stored in the weapons storage room of the firing range, if there is a weapons storage room. </inglise>
<eesti>Lasketiiru relvahoidlas hoitava relva ja laskemoona eest vastutab lasketiiru omanik v&otilde;i valdaja. </eesti>
<inglise>The owner or possessor of the firing range is responsible for weapons and ammunition stored in the weapons storage room of the firing range. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&otilde;imaluse kasutada relvahoidlat relvade ja laskemoona hoidmiseks v&otilde;istluse ja treeningu ajal tagab &uuml;rituse korraldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) During a sports event or training, the organiser of the event shall ensure that it is possible to use a storage room to store weapons and ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvahoidla puudumise korral tagab relvade hoidmise ja valve v&otilde;istluse ja treeningu ajal &uuml;rituse korraldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>If no weapons storage room exists, the organiser of the event shall ensure the storage and guarding of weapons during the sports event or training. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relvahoidlast v&otilde;ib laskma minnes kaasa v&otilde;tta vaid selleks korraks vajalikud relvad ning vajaliku koguse laskemoona. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person who goes shooting shall take only such weapons and such quantity of ammunition from a weapons storage room as he or she needs for this occasion. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Laskepaigas ei ole relvahoidla olemasolu kohustuslik. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The existence of a weapons storage room is not mandatory at a field firing range. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona hoidmise eest laskepaigas vastutab relva valdaja. </eesti>
<inglise>The possessor of a weapon is liable for the storage of weapons and ammunition at a field firing range. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona kandmine ja edasitoimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Carrying and Conveyance of Weapons and Ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvakandmine </eesti>
<inglise>Carrying of weapons </inglise>
<eesti>Relvakandmise all m&otilde;istetakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses relva endaga kaasaskandmist v&auml;ljaspool hoiukohta. </eesti>
<inglise>The carrying of a weapon is defined in this Act as the carrying of a weapon on one's person outside a storage room. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona kandmise &uuml;ldine kord </eesti>
<inglise>General procedure for carrying of weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;ib kanda koos vastava relvaloa v&otilde;i relvakandmisloaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Weapons and ammunition shall be carried together with a corresponding weapons permit or permit to carry a weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relva ja laskemoona tuleb kanda varjatult ning viisil, mis v&auml;listab nende kadumise v&otilde;i sattumise teise isiku valdusse, samuti juhusliku kahju tekitamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Weapons and ammunition shall be carried in a concealed manner which precludes their being lost, falling into the hands of other persons or causing accidental damage. </inglise>
<eesti>Kantava tulirelva, v&auml;lja arvatud revolvri padrunipesas ei tohi olla padrunit. </eesti>
<inglise>The chamber of a carried firearm, except for the chamber of a revolver, shall be empty of cartridges. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relva ja laskemoona on keelatud kanda: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) It is prohibited to carry weapons or ammunition: </inglise>
<eesti>1) alkoholijoobes, narkootilise, ps&uuml;hhotroopse v&otilde;i ps&uuml;hhotoksilise aine m&otilde;ju all; </eesti>
<inglise>1) while intoxicated or under the influence of narcotic, psychotropic or psychotoxic substances; </inglise>
<eesti>2) koosolekul, meeleavaldusel, piketil, pidustusel ja teistel avalikel &uuml;ritustel, v&auml;lja arvatud nimetatud avalikel &uuml;ritustel teenistus- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannet t&auml;itval isikul. </eesti>
<inglise>2) at meetings, demonstrations, pickets, festivities and other public events, except for persons performing their functions or duties at such public events. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Minister v&otilde;ib oma k&auml;skkirjaga piirata relvakandmist ministeeriumis, ministeeriumi valitsemisalas olevates valitsusasutustes ja hallatavates riigiasutustes ning nende valduses olevatel objektidel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A Minister may, by a directive, restrict the carrying of weapons in the ministry, in government agencies within the area of government of the ministry, in state agencies administered by the ministry and at facilities in the possession of such government agencies or state agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Auml;ri&uuml;hingu v&otilde;i mittetulundus&uuml;hingu juhtorgan v&otilde;i juht, samuti f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;ib oma aktiga piirata relvakandmist oma asukohas ja teistel tema omandis v&otilde;i valduses olevatel objektidel, kui selleks on antud objekti asukoha j&auml;rgse politseiprefektuuri n&otilde;usolek. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A directing body or head of a company or non-profit association or a sole proprietor may, by an order, restrict the carrying of weapons in its seat and at other facilities in its ownership or possession if the police prefecture of the location of the facility has granted its consent therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Jahirelva kandmist jahil reguleerib jahikorralduse seadus (RT I 1994, 30, 465; 83, 1449; 1996, 49, 953; 1997, 86, 1460; 1999, 54, 583; 95, 843) ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktid. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The carrying of hunting weapons while hunting is regulated by the Hunting Act (RT I 1994, 30, 465; 83, 1449; 1996, 49, 953; 1997, 86, 1460; 1999, 54, 583; 95, 843) and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku nimele registreeritud relva kandmine </eesti>
<inglise>Carrying of weapons registered in name of legal person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juriidiline isik v&otilde;ib anda tema nimele registreeritud relva kanda oma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kellel on relvakandmisluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A legal person may give a weapon registered in its name to an employee to carry if the employee holds a permit to carry a weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relv antakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale kanda t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks vastava juriidilise isiku juhi otsuse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employee is given a weapon to carry for the conduct of his or her functions or duties on the basis of a decision made by the head of the corresponding legal person. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relv v&auml;ljastatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks &uuml;ldjuhul t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaks v&otilde;i valvekorraks, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui relva pikemaajalise kandmise vajadus on tingitud ametikohustuste iseloomust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Generally, an employee shall be issued with a weapon to conduct his or her functions or duties for the duration of a working day or a shift, except in cases where the need to carry a weapon for a longer period of time arises from the nature of the employee's occupational commitments. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametikohtade loetelu, kus selliseid kohustusi tuleb t&auml;ita, kehtestatakse juriidilise isiku otsusega, mis on eelnevalt koosk&otilde;lastatud asukohaj&auml;rgse politseiprefektuuriga. </eesti>
<inglise>A list of positions in which the performance of such duties is required shall be established by a decision of the legal person which has been approved beforehand by the police prefecture of the seat of the legal person. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Relvakandmis&otilde;igust omaval t&ouml;&ouml;tajal on keelatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employee with the right to carry a weapon is prohibited to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kanda relva t&ouml;&ouml;v&auml;lisel ajal, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui sellekohane luba on vormistatud juriidilise isiku otsusega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) carry a weapon outside working time unless such authorisation is formalised by a decision of the legal person; </inglise>
<eesti>2) anda relva v&otilde;i relvakandmisluba k&otilde;rvalisele isikule; </eesti>
<inglise>2) give a weapon or a permit to carry a weapon to an unauthorised person; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kanda relva teise juriidilise isiku huvides v&otilde;i selle t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel. </eesti>
<inglise>3) carry a weapon in the interests of another legal person or upon the conduct of the duties or functions thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Relva kaotamisest, h&auml;vimisest v&otilde;i muul viisil valdusest v&auml;ljaminekust on relva kandev t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustatud viivitamata teatama s&uuml;ndmuskohaj&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile v&otilde;i -jaoskonnale ja relva v&auml;ljastanud isikule v&otilde;i asutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a weapon carried by an employee is lost or destroyed or leaves his or her possession in any other manner, the employee is required promptly to inform the police prefecture or police station of the location of the event and the person or agency who issued the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku nimele registreeritud relva v&auml;ljastamine t&ouml;&ouml;tajale ja selle tagastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Issue of weapon registered in name of legal person to employee and return thereof </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva ja laskemoona v&auml;ljastav isik on enne relva v&auml;ljastamist kohustatud kontrollima relvakandmisloa olemasolu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who issues weapons and ammunition is required to verify that the person to whom the weapon or ammunition is to be issued holds a permit to carry a weapon before issuing the weapon or ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relva ja laskemoona v&auml;ljastamine fikseeritakse n&ouml;&ouml;ritud ja politseiprefektuuri pitseriga kinnitatud relvade ja laskemoona arvestusraamatus (edaspidi relvaraamat) allkirja vastu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The issue of a weapon or ammunition shall be documented, against a signature, in a ledger for the recording of weapons and ammunition which is bound with string and sealed with the seal of the police prefecture (hereinafter weapons ledger). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relvaraamatusse kantakse relva v&auml;ljastamise ja tagastamise kuup&auml;ev ning kellaaeg, relva liik, mark, kaliiber ja markeering, padrunite arv, relva saanud ja relva v&auml;ljastanud t&ouml;&ouml;taja ees- ja perekonnanimi ning ametikoht. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The date and time of the issue and return of a weapon, the type, mark, calibre and marking of a weapon, the number of cartridges, and the given name, surname and position of the employee to whom the weapon is given and of the employee who issues the weapon shall be entered in the weapons ledger. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) P&auml;rast t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i teenistus&uuml;lesande t&auml;itmist peab t&ouml;&ouml;taja relva ja laskemoona tagastama. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The employee is required to return the weapon and ammunition after the conduct of his or her duties or functions. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona vastuv&otilde;tnud isik teeb relvaraamatusse m&auml;rke relva ja laskemoona vastuv&otilde;tmise kohta ning kinnitab seda oma allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>The person who receives the weapon or ammunition shall make a notation concerning the receipt of the weapon or ammunition in the weapons ledger and shall confirm the entry with his or her signature. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Juhul kui t&ouml;&ouml;tajal on kaasas isiklik tulirelv, tuleb see juriidilise isiku relva kandmise ajaks anda hoiule juriidilise isiku relvahoidlasse v&otilde;i -kappi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If an employee carries a personal firearm, this shall be deposited in a weapons storage room or weapons safe of the legal person for the time that the employee carries the weapon of the legal person. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikliku tulirelva hoiulev&otilde;tmine ja tagastamine peab olema kantud relvaraamatusse. </eesti>
<inglise>The deposit and return of personal firearms shall be entered in the weapons ledger. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Relvaraamatut s&auml;ilitatakse viis aastat viimase sissekande tegemise kuup&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Weapons ledgers shall be preserved for five years after the date on which the last entry is made in the ledger. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Relvaraamatu vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The standard format for weapons ledgers shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku relvakandmisluba </eesti>
<inglise>Permit to carry weapon of legal person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juriidilise isiku relvakandmisloa (edaspidi relvakandmisluba) v&auml;ljastab t&ouml;&ouml;tajale tema elukoha j&auml;rgne politseiprefektuur juriidilise isiku taotlusel, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on sooritanud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 35 l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatud relvatundmise ja -k&auml;sitsemise eksami ning kui tema suhtes ei esine asjaolusid, mis v&auml;listavad relvaloa saamise f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee of a legal person shall be issued with a permit to carry a weapon of the legal person (hereinafter permit to carry a weapon) by the police prefecture of the residence of the employee on the application of the legal person after the person has passed the examination on his or her knowledge and handling of weapons and unless circumstances exist with respect to him or her which preclude the grant of a weapon to the natural person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relvakandmisloa v&auml;ljastamise taotluses m&auml;rgitakse t&ouml;&ouml;taja ees- ja perekonnanimi, ametikoht, isikukood ja elukoht ning selle relva liik ja mark, mille kandmiseks luba taotletakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An application for a permit to carry a weapon shall set out the given name, surname, position, personal identification code and residence of the employee and the type and mark of the weapon for which the permit is applied. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taotlusele lisatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 35 l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 2 ja 3 nimetatud dokumendid, kaks fotot m&otilde;&otilde;tmetega 3&times;4 cm ning sama paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 nimetatud eksami sooritamist t&otilde;endav dokument. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The documents specified in clauses 35 (2) 2) and 3) of this Act, two photographs measuring 3&times;4 cm and a document certifying that the examination specified in subsection 35 (5) has been passed shall be annexed to the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Politseiprefektuur vaatab taotluse l&auml;bi hiljemalt kahe kuu jooksul k&otilde;igi n&otilde;utavate dokumentide esitamise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The police prefecture shall review the application not later than within two months as of the date of submission of all required documents. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Taotluse rahuldamise korral v&auml;ljastatakse relvakandmisluba ning selle omaja kohta avatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 33 s&auml;testatud korras relvatoimik. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If an application is satisfied, a permit to carry a weapon shall be issued and a weapon register book provided for in &sect; 33 of this Act shall be opened regarding the holder of the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Relvakandmisloa kehtivus on viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The duration of a permit to carry a weapon is five years. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvakandmisluba kaotab kehtivuse t&ouml;&ouml;taja lahkumisel antud ametikohalt, samuti juriidilise isiku l&otilde;ppemisel. </eesti>
<inglise>A permit to carry a weapon becomes invalid if the employee leaves the given office or if the legal person is dissolved. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Relvakandmisloa vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The standard format for permits to carry a weapon shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Kehtivuse kaotanud relvakandmisluba tagastatakse selle v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) If a permit to carry a weapon has expired, the permit shall be returned to the police prefecture which issued the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona edasitoimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Conveyance of weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva ja laskemoona edasitoimetamise all m&otilde;istetakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses relva ja laskemoona endaga kaasaskandmist nende &uuml;hest kohast teise toimetamise vajaduse korral ilma relva vahepealse kasutamise eesm&auml;rgita ja s&otilde;ltumata asjaolust, kas sellega kaasneb s&otilde;iduki kasutamine v&otilde;i mitte. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, the conveyance of weapons and ammunition means the carrying of weapons on one's person if it is necessary to transport the weapons and ammunition from one location to another without the aim of using the weapon in the meantime, regardless of the fact of whether this involves the use of a vehicle or not. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juriidilise isiku nimele registreeritud relvade ja laskemoona, mis ei ole v&auml;ljastatud kandmiseks nende t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele, edasitoimetamine, kui sellega kaasneb transpordivahendi kasutamine, loetakse kohalikuks relvaveoks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The conveyance of weapons and ammunition registered in the name of a legal person which are not issued for carrying to employees thereof and where conveyance involves the use of a means of transport is deemed to be internal transport of weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relva ja laskemoona saatmine posti teel on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) It is prohibited to send weapons or ammunition by post. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona edasitoimetamine f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku poolt </eesti>
<inglise>Conveyance of weapons and ammunition by natural person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva ja laskemoona edasitoimetamise &otilde;igus on soetamisluba v&otilde;i relvaluba, samuti k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 80 nimetatud luba omaval f&uuml;&uuml;silisel isikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A natural person who holds an acquisition permit or a weapons permit or a permit specified in &sect; 80 of this Act has the right to convey weapons and ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Edasitoimetatav relv peab olema t&uuml;hjaks laetud ja lahti v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i pakitud viisil, mis ei v&otilde;imalda relva kohest kasutuselev&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A weapon which is conveyed shall be unloaded and disassembled or packed in a manner which precludes the immediate use of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relva v&otilde;i laskemoona edasitoimetamisel tuleb j&auml;rgida k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 50 l&otilde;igetes 1-3 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The requirements provided for in subsections 50 (1) -(3) of this Act shall be adhered to upon the conveyance of weapons and ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona vedu ja &uuml;le tollipiiri toimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Transport and Carriage of Weapons and Ammunition across Customs Frontier </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 56. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 56. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvaveo m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of transport of weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relvaveo all m&otilde;istetakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses relvade ja laskemoona kohalikku ja rahvusvahelist &otilde;hu-, raudtee-, vetel- v&otilde;i autovedu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In this Act, transport of weapons is defined as the internal and international carriage of weapons by air, rail, water or road. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohaliku relvaveo all m&otilde;istetakse relvade ja laskemoona vedu Eesti piires. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Internal transport of weapons is defined as the transport of weapons and ammunition within Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohalik relvavedu toimub autoveoseaduse (RT I 2000, 54, 346), lennundusseaduse (RT I 1999, 26, 376; 2001, 87, 525), kaubandusliku meres&otilde;idu koodeksi (RT 1991, 46-48, 577; RT I 1993, 65, 923; 1995, 54, 882; 1996, 78, 1380; 1997, 77, 1315; 1998, 2, 47; 23, 321; 30, 409; 2000, 35, 221; 2001, 21, 114; 93, 565; 2002, 1, 1) ja raudteeseaduse (RT I 1999, 29, 405; 2001, 31, 170; 93, 565) ning nende alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Internal transport of weapons shall be conducted pursuant to the Road Transport Act (RT I 2000, 54, 346), the Aviation Act (RT I 1999, 26, 376; 2001, 87, 525), the Merchant Shipping Code (RT 1991, 46-48, 577; RT I 1993, 65, 923; 1995, 54, 882; 1996, 78, 1380; 1997, 77, 1315; 1998, 2, 47; 23, 321; 30, 409; 2000, 35, 221; 2001, 21, 114; 93, 565; 2002, 1, 1) and the Railways Act (RT I 1999, 29, 405; 2001, 31, 170; 93, 565) and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rahvusvahelise relvaveo all m&otilde;istetakse relvade ja laskemoona vedu, millega kaasneb riigipiiri &uuml;letamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) International transport of weapons is defined as the transport of weapons and ammunition which involves the crossing of the state border. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Rahvusvaheline relvavedu toimub vastavas veoliigis kehtivate rahvusvaheliste veoeeskirjade kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) International transport of weapons shall be conducted pursuant to the international transport regulations which are in force concerning the corresponding mode of transport. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 57. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 57. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iendavad n&otilde;uded kohalikul relvaveol </eesti>
<inglise>Additional requirements upon internal transport of weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kohalikku relvavedu v&otilde;ib teostada f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik, kellel on relvaluba, soetamisluba v&otilde;i tegevusluba relvade valmistamiseks v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;giks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Natural persons and legal persons who hold a weapons permit, an acquisition permit or an activity licence for the manufacture or sale of weapons may engage in the internal transport of weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relvade ja laskemoona valve ja kaitse tagab nende veol omanik v&otilde;i valdaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The owner or possessor of weapons and ammunition shall ensure the guarding and security of the weapons and ammunition upon transport. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relvi ja laskemoona peab vedama valmistajapakendis v&otilde;i pakituna viisil, mis ei v&otilde;imalda nende kohest kasutuselev&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Weapons and ammunition shall be transported in the original packaging provided by the manufacturer or packaged is a manner which precludes their immediate use. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kuni 20 tulirelva v&otilde;i 10 000 padrunit v&otilde;ib vedada varjatult s&otilde;iduautoga, suurema tulirelva- v&otilde;i padrunipartii veoks tuleb kasutada kinnise veoseruumiga veoautot. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) It is permitted to transport up to 20 firearms or 10 000 cartridges in a concealed manner by passenger car, but a lorry with a closed cargo space shall be used to transport larger consignments of weapons and ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>Veoseruumi uksed peavad olema kindlalt suletud ja lukustatud. </eesti>
<inglise>The doors of the cargo space shall be securely closed and locked. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kuni 20 tulirelva v&otilde;i 10 000 padruni veol peab olema v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks relvastatud saatja, &uuml;le 20 tulirelva v&otilde;i &uuml;le 10 000 padruni veol aga v&auml;hemalt kaks relvastatud saatjat. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) At least one armed person shall escort a consignment of up to 20 firearms or 10 000 cartridges and at least two armed persons shall escort a consignment of more than 20 firearms or 10 000 cartridges. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvastatud saatjad v&otilde;ivad asuda relvi vedava veoauto kabiinis v&otilde;i relvi vedavat autot saatvas autos. </eesti>
<inglise>The armed escort may stay in the cabin of the lorry in which the weapons are being carried or in a car accompanying the car in which the weapons are being carried. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 4 ja 5 s&auml;testatu ei laiene juriidilisele isikule tema nimele registreeritud sporditulirelvade ja nende laskemoona veol lasketiiru seoses osav&otilde;tuga treeningust v&otilde;i v&otilde;istlusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The provisions of subsections (4) and (5) of this section do not apply to the transport of sporting firearms registered in the name of a legal person and to ammunition therefor to a firing range in connection with participation in training or a sports event. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul peab relvadega kaasas&otilde;itvate isikute hulgast olema m&auml;&auml;ratud relvaveo eest vastutav relvastatud isik. </eesti>
<inglise>In this case, a person shall be appointed from among the persons who accompany the transported weapons to be responsible for the transport of the weapons and this person shall be armed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 58. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 58. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja selle laskemoona kaasav&otilde;tmine &otilde;hus&otilde;idukisse </eesti>
<inglise>Taking of weapons and ammunition therefor on board aircraft </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja selle laskemoona kommertseesm&auml;rgil kasutatava &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki reisijatesalongi kaasav&otilde;tmise korra kehtestab teede- ja sideminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for taking weapons and ammunition therefor into passenger cabins of aircraft used for commercial purposes shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 59. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 59. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade ja laskemoona &uuml;le tollipiiri toimetamise m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of carriage of weapons and ammunition across customs frontier </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses m&otilde;istetakse relvade ja laskemoona &uuml;le tollipiiri toimetamise all relvade ja laskemoona sisse- ja v&auml;ljavedu, transiiti ning sissetoomist ja v&auml;ljaviimist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The carriage of weapons and ammunition across the customs frontier is defined in this Act as the import, export, transit, bringing in and taking out of weapons and ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relvade ja laskemoona &uuml;le tollipiiri toimetamine toimub k&auml;esoleva seaduse, tolliseadustiku ning strateegilise kauba sisse- ja v&auml;ljaveo ning transiidi seaduse (RT I 1999, 57, 597; 2001, 88, 531) ja nende alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Weapons and ammunition shall be carried across the customs frontier pursuant to the procedure established by this Act, the Customs Code and the Strategic Goods Import, Export and Transit Act (RT I 1999, 57, 597; 2001, 88, 531) and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relvade ja laskemoona &uuml;le tollipiiri toimetamine v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva seaduse kohaselt toimuda &uuml;ksnes Politseiameti &uuml;hekordse eriloa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Pursuant to this Act, the carriage of weapons and ammunition across the customs frontier shall be conducted solely on the basis of a single special permit granted by the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Eriloa v&auml;ljastamise ja vormistamise korra, eriloa alusel &uuml;le tollipiiri toimetatavate relvade, tulirelva oluliste osade, lisaseadiste ja laskemoona nomenklatuuri ning eriloa vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The procedure for the issue of a special permit, the list of weapons, essential components of firearms, accessories and ammunition, and the standard format for the permit shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 60. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 60. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade ja laskemoona sissevedu, v&auml;ljavedu ja transiit </eesti>
<inglise>Import, export and transit of weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relvade ja laskemoona sissevedu kaubana vabasse ringlusse lubamiseks v&otilde;ib teostada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud eriloa alusel isik, kellel on tegevusluba relvade, tulirelva oluliste osade, laskemoona v&otilde;i lasersihikute valmistamiseks v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;giks, relvade &uuml;mbertegemiseks v&otilde;i parandamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Weapons and ammunition may be imported as goods for release for free circulation on the basis of the special permit specified in subsection 59 (3) of this Act by persons holding an activity licence for the manufacture or sale of weapons, essential components of firearms, ammunition or laser sights, or for the conversion or repair of weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relvade, tulirelva oluliste osade ning lisaseadiste valmistamise, parandamise v&otilde;i &uuml;mbertegemise ning laskemoona valmistamise tegevusluba omav isik v&otilde;ib taotleda luba ainult seda liiki relvade, tulirelva oluliste osade, lasersihikute v&otilde;i laskemoona sisseveoks, mille valmistamiseks, parandamiseks v&otilde;i &uuml;mbertegemiseks tegevusluba on antud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who holds an activity licence for the manufacture, repair or conversion of weapons, essential components of firearms, or accessories, or for the manufacture of ammunition may apply solely for permission to import the particular type of weapon, essential components of firearms, laser sights or ammunition for the manufacture, repair or conversion of which the person has been issued the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;lisriigi f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik v&otilde;ib enda nimele registreeritud relva ja selle laskemoona Eestisse ajutiselt importida osalemiseks spordiv&otilde;istlusel, &otilde;ppusel, jahipidamiseks ja muudeks samalaadseteks &uuml;ritusteks, kui tal on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud eriluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A natural or legal persons of a foreign state may temporarily import the weapon and ammunition registered in the person's name into Estonia for the purposes of participating in sports competitions, training, hunting and other similar activities if the person has been granted the special permit specified in 59 (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Ajutiselt imporditud relv peab olema loal m&auml;rgitud t&auml;htajaks Eestist v&auml;lja viidud. </eesti>
<inglise>A temporarily imported weapon shall leave Estonian by the due date determined in the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lubatud on ainult selliste tulirelvade ja padrunite sissevedu, mis on saanud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 23 s&auml;testatud t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse, tingimusel, et sisseveetavate relvade ja padrunite mudelid on kantud teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registrisse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Only firearms and cartridges which have been issued the type approval provided for in &sect; 23 of this Act may be imported, on the condition that the models of the weapons and cartridges to be imported have been entered in the register of service and civilian weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatu ei laiene relvadele ja padrunitele, mis tuuakse Eestisse sisse nende katsetamise, demonstreerimise v&otilde;i n&auml;itusel v&auml;ljapaneku eesm&auml;rgil. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The provisions of subsection (4) of this section do not apply to weapons and cartridges which are brought into Estonia to be tested, demonstrated or displayed at an exhibition. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Strateegilise kauba nimekirja arvatud relvade ja laskemoona v&auml;ljavedu Eestist ja transiit l&auml;bi Eesti tolliterritooriumi toimub strateegilise kauba sisse- ja v&auml;ljaveo ning transiidi seaduse ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The export from Estonia of weapons and ammunition included in the list of strategic goods and the transit of such goods through the customs territory of Estonia shall be conducted pursuant to the procedure established by the Strategic Goods Import, Export and Transit Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Strateegilise kauba nimekirja mittekuuluvate relvade ja laskemoona v&auml;ljavedu ja transiiti v&otilde;ivad teostada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud eriloa alusel isikud, kellel on tegevusluba seda liiki relvade ja laskemoona valmistamiseks v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;giks. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The export and transit of weapons and ammunition which are not included in the list of strategic goods may be conducted on the basis of the special permit specified in subsection 59 (3) of this Act by persons holding an activity licence for the manufacture or sale of such type of weapon or ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Eestit l&auml;biva transiidi puhul tuleb j&auml;rgida k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 57 kehtestatud korda. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The procedure established in &sect; 57 of this Act shall be adhered to upon transit through Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 61. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 61. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade ja laskemoona sissetoomine ja v&auml;ljaviimine </eesti>
<inglise>Bringing in and taking out of weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik v&otilde;ib enda nimele registreeritud relva ja selle laskemoona Eestist ajutiselt v&auml;lja viia relva taassissetoomise kohustusega osalemiseks spordiv&otilde;istlusel, &otilde;ppusel, jahipidamiseks ja muudeks samalaadseteks &uuml;ritusteks, kui tal on v&auml;lisriigi isiku v&otilde;i asutuse kutse ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud eriluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A natural or legal person who has an invitation from a foreign person or agency and who holds the special permit specified in subsection 59 (3) of this Act may temporarily take a weapon registered in the name of the person and ammunition therefor out of Estonia in order to participate in a sports event, exercise, hunt or other similar event if the person assumes the obligation to bring the weapon back to Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) F&uuml;&uuml;siline isik v&otilde;ib enda nimele registreeritud relva ja selle laskemoona Eestist alatiseks v&auml;lja viia, kui ta asub elama v&auml;lisriiki ja tal on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud eriluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A natural person may take a weapon registered in his or her name and ammunition therefor out of Estonia permanently if the person is to settle in a foreign state and if he or she holds the special permit specified in subsection 59 (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;lisriigi f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik v&otilde;ib enda nimele registreeritud relva ja selle laskemoona Eestisse ajutiselt sisse tuua relva taasv&auml;ljaviimise kohustusega osalemiseks spordiv&otilde;istlusel, &otilde;ppusel, jahipidamiseks ja muudeks samalaadseteks &uuml;ritusteks, kui tal on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud eriluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A foreign natural or legal person who holds the special permit specified in subsection 59 (3) of this Act may temporarily bring a weapon registered in the name of the person and ammunition therefor into Estonia in order to participate in a sports event, exercise, hunt or other similar event if the person assumes the obligation to take the weapon out of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>Sissetoodud relv peab olema loal m&auml;rgitud t&auml;htajaks Eestist v&auml;lja viidud. </eesti>
<inglise>A weapon which is brought into Estonia shall be taken out of the country by the term indicated on the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) V&auml;lisriigi diplomaatilise v&otilde;i konsulaaresinduse t&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes on v&auml;lisriigi kodanik, samuti Eestis riiklikul tasemel k&uuml;lalisena viibiv v&auml;lisriigi kodanik ning teda saatev isik v&otilde;ivad kodakondsusj&auml;rgses riigis registreeritud relva ning selle laskemoona Eestisse sisse tuua ja Eestist v&auml;lja viia V&auml;lisministeeriumi taotlusel antava k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud eriloa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employee of a foreign diplomatic or consular representation who is a foreign citizen, and also a foreign citizen staying in Estonia as a visitor of the state and a person accompanying such person may bring a weapon registered in the country of their nationality and ammunition therefor into Estonia and take it out of Estonia on the basis of the special permit specified in subsection 59 (3) of this Act granted on the application of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) V&auml;lismaalane peab Politseiameti loal Eestist v&auml;ljaviimiseks soetatud relva ja laskemoona Eestist v&auml;lja viima k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud eriloa alusel viie p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates soetamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An alien who, with the permission of the Police Board, has acquired a weapon and ammunition for the purpose of taking it out of Estonia shall do so on the basis of the special permit specified in subsection 59 (3) of this Act within five days as of the date of acquisition. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona Eestist v&auml;ljaviimise t&auml;htaeg m&auml;rgitakse loale. </eesti>
<inglise>The term for taking the weapon and ammunition out of Estonia shall be entered on the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) V&auml;lisriigi f&uuml;&uuml;silise v&otilde;i juriidilise isiku nimele registreeritud relva ja selle laskemoona transiit v&otilde;ib toimuda k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud eriloa alusel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 54 ja 55 kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The transit of a weapon registered in the name of a foreign natural or legal person and ammunition therefor shall be conducted on the basis of a special permit specified in subsection 59 (3) of this Act and pursuant to the procedure established by &sect;&sect; 54 and 55 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 5 s&auml;testatud juhtudel saadab Politseiamet viivitamata, kuid mitte hiljem kui kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, teate relva v&auml;ljaviimise kohta sihtriigi kompetentsele asutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) In the cases provided for in subsections (2) and (5) of this section, the Police Board shall promptly, but not later than within three working days, send a notice concerning the taking of a weapon out of Estonia to a competent authority of the country of destination. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 62. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 62. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade ja laskemoona &uuml;le tollipiiri toimetamise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for carriage of weapons and ammunition across customs frontier </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relvade ja laskemoona sisse- ja v&auml;ljavedu v&otilde;ib toimuda rahvusvaheliseks liiklemiseks avatud piiripunktide kaudu, kus on toll alaliselt kohal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The import and export of weapons and ammunition shall be conducted through border checkpoints open to international travel where customs authorities are permanently present. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tulirelvade ja laskemoona saatmine Eestisse ja Eestist v&auml;lja rahvusvahelistes postisaadetistes ei ole lubatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) It is not permitted to send firearms to Estonia or out of Estonia in international postal consignments. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Sisseveetavate relvade ja laskemoona vastavust n&otilde;uetele kontrollib tollikontrolli tsoonis Vabariigi Valitsuse volitatud asutus, kes nende n&otilde;uetele vastavuse korral teeb sellekohase m&auml;rke eriloale. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The compliance of imported weapons and ammunition with the requirements shall be checked in a customs control zone by an agency authorised by the Government of the Republic which, if the requirements are complied with, shall make a notation to this effect on the special permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade v&otilde;i laskemoona mittevastavuse korral kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele koostatakse akt, kus n&auml;idatakse &auml;ra puudused, mille t&otilde;ttu k&otilde;igi v&otilde;i osa relvade v&otilde;i laskemoona sissevedu on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>If the weapons or ammunition do not comply with the established requirements, a report shall be prepared which sets out the deficiencies due to which the import of all or part of the weapons or ammunition is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Relv ja laskemoon peavad olema saatedokumentide ja loa alusel t&auml;pselt identifitseeritavad. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Weapons and ammunition shall be accurately identifiable on the basis of accompanying documents and a permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Nomenklatuur ei tohi erineda loal m&auml;rgitud nomenklatuurist ning kogus ei tohi &uuml;letada loal n&auml;idatud kogust. </eesti>
<inglise>The list shall not differ from the list specified in the permit and the actual amount shall not exceed the amount indicated in the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Sisseveetaval tulirelval ja tulirelva olulisel osal peab olema n&otilde;uetekohane markeering. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Imported firearms and essential components of firearms shall bear marking which meets the requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>Registreeritud tulirelva markeering peab vastama eriloal n&auml;idatule. </eesti>
<inglise>The marking of a registered firearm shall correspond to the marking indicated in the special permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Ilma k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud eriloata tollipiirile toimetatud relv ja laskemoon peetakse kinni kuni asjaolude selgitamiseni ja paigutatakse tollilattu. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Weapons and ammunition carried to a customs frontier without the special permit specified in subsection 59 (3) of this Act shall be retained and stored in a customs warehouse until the facts are ascertained. </inglise>
<eesti>Kinnipeetud relvade ja laskemoona s&auml;ilimise ja n&otilde;uetekohase hoidmise tagab toll. </eesti>
<inglise>The customs authorities shall ensure that retained weapons and ammunition are preserved and stored according to the requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>9. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;&otilde;randamine </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of Weapons and Ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 63. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 63. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;&otilde;randamise &uuml;ldine kord </eesti>
<inglise>General procedure for transfer of weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva ja laskemoona v&otilde;&otilde;randamise all m&otilde;istetakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses nende omandi&otilde;iguse &uuml;leandmist teisele f&uuml;&uuml;silisele v&otilde;i juriidilisele isikule v&otilde;i riigile v&otilde;i kohalikule omavalitsusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Transfer of weapons and ammunition is defined in this Act as the transfer of the right of ownership to weapons and ammunition to another natural or legal person or to the state or a local government. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relvaomanik v&otilde;i -valdaja v&otilde;ib relva v&otilde;&otilde;randada: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An owner or possessor of a weapon may transfer the weapon: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isikule, kellel on vastava relva soetamisluba; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to a person who has an acquisition permit for the corresponding weapon; </inglise>
<eesti>2) komisjonim&uuml;&uuml;gi korras relvade m&uuml;&uuml;gi tegevusluba omava isiku vahendusel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) by way of commission sale through a person who holds an activity licence for the sale of weapons and ammunition; </inglise>
<eesti>3) relvade m&uuml;&uuml;gi, valmistamise, &uuml;mbertegemise v&otilde;i parandamise tegevusluba omavale isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to a person holding an activity licence for the sale, manufacture, conversion or repair of weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Laskemoona tohib v&otilde;&otilde;randada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 2 ja 3 nimetatud isikute vahendusel v&otilde;i isikule, kellel on vastava relva relvaluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Ammunition may be transferred through persons specified in clauses (2) 2) and 3) of this section or to a person who holds a weapons permit for the corresponding weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 64. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 64. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva v&otilde;&otilde;randamine soetamisluba omavale isikule </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of weapon to person holding acquisition permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva v&otilde;&otilde;randamine soetamisluba omavale isikule toimub politseiprefektuuri p&auml;deva ametniku juuresolekul politseiprefektuuris v&otilde;i relva asukohas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A weapon shall be transferred to a person holding an acquisition permit in the presence of a competent officer of a police prefecture at the police prefecture or the location of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relva v&otilde;&otilde;randamine vormistatakse relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja kirjaliku avalduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The transfer of a weapon shall be formalised on the basis of a written application by the owner or possessor of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduses tuleb m&auml;rkida andmed relva ning isiku kohta, kellele relv v&otilde;&otilde;randatakse. </eesti>
<inglise>The application shall set out information concerning the weapon and the person to whom the weapon is to be transferred. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaldusele lisatakse relvaluba v&otilde;i muu relva seaduslikku omamist t&otilde;endav dokument. </eesti>
<inglise>The weapons permit or other document in proof of the legality of its ownership shall be annexed to the application. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 65. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 65. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva v&otilde;&otilde;randamine vastavat tegevusluba omavale isikule v&otilde;i tema vahendusel </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of weapon to person holding corresponding activity licence or through such person </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 63 l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 2 ja 3 nimetatud juhtudel toimub relva v&otilde;&otilde;randamine k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 80 s&auml;testatud loa alusel ja sellel n&auml;idatud tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>In the cases specified in clauses 63 (2) 2) and 3) of this Act, a weapon shall be transferred pursuant to the permit provided for in &sect; 80 of this Act and under the conditions set out therein. </inglise>
<eesti>10. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 10 </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba relvade ja laskemoonaga seonduvatel tegevusaladel </eesti>
<inglise>Activity Licences in Areas of Activity related to Weapons and Ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 66. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 66. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kohustuslikkus relvade ja laskemoonaga seonduval tegevusalal </eesti>
<inglise>Mandatory activity licence in areas of activity related to weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusluba on n&otilde;utav j&auml;rgmistel relvade ja laskemoonaga seonduvatel tegevusaladel: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An activity licence is mandatory in the following weapons and ammunition related areas of activity: </inglise>
<eesti>1) relvade, tulirelva oluliste osade ja laskemoona, samuti lasersihikute valmistamine ja m&uuml;&uuml;k; </eesti>
<inglise>1) manufacture and sale of weapons, essential components of firearms, ammunition, and laser sights; </inglise>
<eesti>2) relvade &uuml;mbertegemine ja parandamine teenusena; </eesti>
<inglise>2) conversion and repair of weapons as a service; </inglise>
<eesti>3) lasketiiru v&otilde;i laskepaiga kasutamine tasulise teenuse osutamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) use of a firing range or field firing range for the provision of fee-charging services; </inglise>
<eesti>4) relvade laenutamine lasketiirus teenusena; </eesti>
<inglise>4) rental of weapons as a service at a firing range; </inglise>
<eesti>5) relvade v&otilde;i laskemoona hoidmine teenusena. </eesti>
<inglise>5) storage of weapons and ammunition as a service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloaga antakse selles m&auml;rgitud isikule &otilde;igus k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja muude &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud korras ning tingimustel tegutseda kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ajavahemikus &uuml;hel v&otilde;i mitmel relvade ja laskemoonaga seonduval tegevusalal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An activity licence grants the person specified therein the right to operate in one area or more weapons and ammunition related areas of activity within a determined period pursuant to the procedure established by this Act and other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloa koopia peab olema paigutatud tegevuskohas n&auml;htavale kohale. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A copy of an activity licence shall be displayed in a visible place at the place of business. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tegevusloa vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The standard format for activity licences shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 67. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 67. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa taotlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusluba v&otilde;ib taotleda: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following persons may apply for an activity licence: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teov&otilde;imeline Eesti kodanik, kes alaliselt elab Eestis; </eesti>
<inglise>1) Estonian citizens with active legal capacity who reside permanently in Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>2) Eestis registreeritud juriidiline isik, kelle p&otilde;hikirjas on tegevusalaks m&auml;rgitud v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 66 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud tegevusala. </eesti>
<inglise>2) legal persons registered in Estonia whose articles of association or statutes include at least one of the areas of activity specified in subsection 66 (1) of this Act as an area of activity. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusluba antakse, kui taotleja: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An activity licence shall be granted if the applicant: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on m&auml;&auml;ranud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 38 ja 39 kohaselt vastutava isiku ja tema asendaja; </eesti>
<inglise>1) has appointed a person responsible and his or her substitute pursuant to &sect;&sect; 38 and 39 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) omab seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel antud &otilde;igusaktiga kehtestatud muid tingimusi tegutsemiseks tegevusloa taotlemise avalduses m&auml;rgitud tegevusalal. </eesti>
<inglise>2) has other conditions, established by law or legislation issued on the basis thereof, available for activities in the area of activity specified in the application for the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloa saamiseks esitatakse avaldus, milles m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to be granted an activity licence, an application shall be submitted which sets out the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) relvade v&otilde;i laskemoonaga seonduv tegevusala, millega taotleja soovib tegelda; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the weapons and ammunition related area of activity in which the applicant wishes to engage; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tegevuskoht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the place of business; </inglise>
<eesti>3) soovitav tegevusloa kehtivusaeg, kui see on l&uuml;hem kui viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the desired period of validity of the activity licence if shorter than five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tegevusloa taotlemise avaldusele lisatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The following shall be annexed to an application for an activity licence: </inglise>
<eesti>1) taotleja asutamisdokumentide, samuti p&otilde;hikirja v&otilde;i p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse ning registreerimistunnistuse &auml;rakirjad; </eesti>
<inglise>1) copies of the foundation documents, articles of association or statutes, and registration certificate of the applicant; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tegevusluba taotleva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu osanike ja aktsion&auml;ride, kellel on &uuml;le 5% aktsia- v&otilde;i osakapitalist, nimekiri ning &auml;ri&uuml;hingu juhatuse ja n&otilde;ukogu liikmete nimekiri, kus on m&auml;rgitud f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku ees- ja perekonnanimi, isikukood ja elukoht ning juriidilise isiku t&auml;ielik nimi, asukoht ja &auml;riregistrikood; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a list of partners and shareholders who hold over 5% of the share capital in the company applying for the activity licence, and a list of the members of the management board and supervisory board of the company which sets out the given names, surnames, personal identification codes and residences of natural persons and the full name, seat and commercial registry code of the legal person; </inglise>
<eesti>3) andmed vastutava isiku ja tema asendaja kohta (ees- ja perekonnanimi, isikukood, elukoht, kontakttelefoni number), samuti &otilde;iend vastava eksami sooritamise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) information concerning the person responsible and his or her substitute (given name, surname, personal identification code, residence and telephone number), and certification that the corresponding examination has been passed; </inglise>
<eesti>4) relvade ja laskemoona k&auml;itlemisega seotud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate nimekiri, kus on m&auml;rgitud nende ees- ja perekonnanimi, isikukood ja elukoht; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a list of employees who are involved in the handling of weapons and ammunition, which sets out their given names, surnames and personal identification codes; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &otilde;iend relvahoidla n&otilde;uetele vastavuse kohta, milles on m&auml;rgitud selle aadress, kontakttelefon ning vahendid, millega tagatakse valve ja kaitse, v&otilde;i tegevusloa kehtivusajaks relvahoidla rentimise lepingu koopia; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a certificate concerning the compliance with the requirements of the weapons storage room, which sets out the address and the telephone number of the storage room and the means used in order to ensure the security and guarding of the room, or a copy of a contract entered into for the period of validity of the activity licence for rental of a weapons storage room; </inglise>
<eesti>6) Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse &otilde;iend maksuv&otilde;lgnevuse puudumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a statement from the local Tax Board Office certifying the absence of tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>7) riigil&otilde;ivu tasumist t&otilde;endav dokument. </eesti>
<inglise>7) a document certifying payment of the state fee. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Lasketiiru v&otilde;i laskepaiga pidamise tegevusloa taotlemisel lisatakse avaldusele peale k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatu: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon application for an activity licence for maintenance of a firing range or field firing range, the following shall be annexed to the application in addition to the documents provided for in subsection (4) of this section: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kohaliku omavalitsuse poolt tervisekaitse, keskkonnakaitse ja tulet&otilde;rjej&auml;relevalve esindajate osav&otilde;tul tehtud &uuml;levaatuse akt lasketiiru v&otilde;i laskepaiga vastavuse kohta kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an inspection report concerning the compliance of the firing range or field firing range with the established requirements as verified during an inspection conducted by the local government with the participation of representatives of health protection, environmental protection and firefighting supervisory bodies; </inglise>
<eesti>2) m&uuml;ra m&otilde;&otilde;tmise akt; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a noise measurement report; </inglise>
<eesti>3) asendiplaan ja &uuml;ldvaated; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the layout and perspective view; </inglise>
<eesti>4) uue lasketiiru korral ehitise kasutusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>4) in the case of a new firing range, authorisation for use of the structure. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 68. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 68. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa v&auml;ljastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Issue of activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa v&auml;ljastab, muudab ja pikendab seda, peatab selle kehtivuse ning tunnistab kehtetuks Politseiamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Activity licences are issued, amended, extended, suspended and revoked by the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusluba relvade ja laskemoona valmistamiseks v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;giks, relvade &uuml;mbertegemiseks v&otilde;i parandamiseks ei anta isikule, kes tegeleb turvateenuste osutamise v&otilde;i eradetektiivindusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons who engage in the provision of security or private detective services shall not be issued with an activity licence for the manufacture or sale of weapons or ammunition or for the conversion or repair of weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiamet teeb otsuse tegevusloa v&auml;ljastamise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta hiljemalt 30 p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast k&otilde;igi n&otilde;utavate dokumentide laekumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Police Board shall decide on the issue of or refusal to issue an activity licence within thirty days after receipt of all the required documents. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tegevusloa v&auml;ljastamise v&otilde;i v&auml;ljastamisest keeldumise otsus peab olema motiveeritud ning viitama selle aluseks olevale seadusele v&otilde;i muule seaduse alusel antud &otilde;igusaktile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A decision concerning the issue of or refusal to issue an activity licence shall be reasoned and contain a reference to the Act or other legislation issued on the basis of an Act which constitutes the basis for the issue or refusal to issue. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Iga tegevusloa taotleja kohta vormistatakse toimik, kuhu koondatakse k&otilde;ik materjalid tegevusloa v&auml;ljastamise ja v&auml;ljastamisest keeldumise, selle muutmise, kehtivuse peatamise ja kehtetuks tunnistamise ning tegevusloa omaja tegevuse kontrollimise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A file shall be prepared concerning each applicant, in which all materials are gathered concerning the issue of or refusal to issue an activity licence, the amendment, suspension or revocation of the licence and the inspection of the activities of the holder of the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Tegevusloas m&auml;rgitakse tegevusloa omaja nimi, tegevusloa kehtivusaeg, v&auml;ljastamise kuup&auml;ev, v&auml;ljastaja rekvisiidid, v&auml;ljastamise aluseks oleva otsuse number ja kuup&auml;ev, samuti tegevusala, millega lubatakse tegelda. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The activity licence shall set out the name of the holder, the period of validity and the date of issue of the activity licence, requisite information concerning the issuer, the number and date of the decision which is the basis for issue, and also the area of activity for which the licence is issued. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloale pannakse Politseiameti pitser. </eesti>
<inglise>An activity licence shall be embossed with the seal of the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Tegevusloa omaja on kohustatud kirjalikult informeerima Politseiametit ja oma asukoha j&auml;rgset politseiprefektuuri k&otilde;igist muudatustest oma andmetes, dokumentides ja struktuuris viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates nimetatud muudatuste toimumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The holder of an activity licence is required to inform the Police Board and the police prefecture of the seat of the licence holder in writing of any changes to the data, documents or structure thereof within five days as of the date of occurrence of such changes. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 69. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 69. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kehtivus </eesti>
<inglise>Validity of activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusluba antakse &uuml;heks kuni viieks aastaks v&otilde;i ajutise kohustuse v&otilde;i &uuml;lesande t&auml;itmise ajaks, kui selleks kulub aega v&auml;hem kui &uuml;ks aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An activity licence shall be issued for a period of one up to five years or for the time it takes to perform a temporary duty or task if the amount of time taken to perform the duty or task is less than one year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloa kehtivuse pikendamiseks esitatakse avaldus k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 67 l&otilde;igetega 3 ja 4 kehtestatud korras v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kuu enne tegevusloa kehtivusaja l&otilde;ppemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order for an activity licence to be extended, an application shall be submitted at least one month prior to the expiry of the activity licence pursuant to the procedure established in subsections 67 (3) and (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloa kehtivusaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel tagastatakse tegevusluba selle v&auml;ljastajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon expiry of an activity licence, the activity licence shall be returned to the issuer of the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba tagastatakse selle v&auml;ljastajale ka juriidilise isiku l&otilde;ppemise ja tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>An activity licence shall also be returned to the issuer of the licence upon the dissolution of the legal person or the revocation of the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 70. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 70. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kehtivuse peatamise ja kehtetuks tunnistamise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for suspension and revocation of activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusluba v&otilde;idakse tunnistada kehtetuks: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An activity licence may be revoked: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kui tegevusloa omaja ei ole &uuml;helgi tegevusloas m&auml;rgitud tegevusalal alustanud tegevust 12 kuu jooksul loa v&auml;ljastamise p&auml;evast arvates; </eesti>
<inglise>1) if the holder of the activity licence does not commence activities in any of the areas of activity specified in the licence within twelve months as of the date of issue of the licence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kui tegevusloa taotlemisel on teadvalt esitatud valeandmeid, millel oli oluline t&auml;htsus loa v&auml;ljastamise k&uuml;simuse otsustamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) if, upon application for the activity licence, incorrect information has been knowingly submitted which is of material importance to the decision on whether to issue the licence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kui tegevusloa omaja on rikkunud k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) if the holder of the activity licence violates the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kui tegevusloa omaja ei vasta enam tegevusloa andmise aluseks olnud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) if the holder of the activity licence no longer complies with the requirements which were the basis for the issue of the activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kui tegevusloa omaja tegevus on katkenud rohkem kui 12 kuuks j&auml;rjest; </eesti>
<inglise>5) if the activities of the holder of the activity licence have been suspended for more than twelve consecutive months; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kui isik tegutseb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 66 nimetatud tegevusalal, milleks tal puudub tegevusluba; </eesti>
<inglise>6) if the person operates in an area of activity specified in &sect; 66 of this Act without a corresponding activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>7) muul seaduses s&auml;testatud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>7) in other cases provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise aluse ilmnemisel Politseiamet: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a basis for the revocation of a document specified in subsection (1) of this section becomes evident, the Police Board shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teeb ettekirjutuse rikkumise k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ja peatab tegevusloa kehtivuse kuni rikkumise k&otilde;rvaldamiseni v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) issue a precept for the elimination of the violation and suspend the activity licence until the violation is eliminated, or </inglise>
<eesti>2) tunnistab tegevusloa kehtetuks ja m&auml;&auml;rab tegevuse l&otilde;petamise t&auml;htaja. </eesti>
<inglise>2) revoke the activity licence and designate a term for termination of the activity. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Enne tegevusloa kehtivuse peatamise v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamise otsuse tegemist kuulatakse &auml;ra tegevusloa omaja v&otilde;i tema esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Before making a decision concerning the suspension or revocation of an activity licence, the holder of the activity licence or a representative of the holder shall be heard. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa omaja v&otilde;i tema esindaja kohale mitteilmumine ei takista otsuse tegemist. </eesti>
<inglise>The failure of the holder of the activity licence or a representative of the holder to appear does not prevent a decision from being made. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 71. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 71. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kehtivuse peatamise v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamise tagaj&auml;rjed </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of suspension or revocation of activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa kehtivuse peatamise v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamise otsuse &auml;rakiri saadetakse tegevusloa omaja asukoha j&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul otsuse tegemise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A copy of a decision concerning the suspension or revocation of an activity licence shall be sent to the police prefecture of the seat of the holder of the licence within three days as of the date of the decision being made. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relvad ja laskemoon, mis tegevusloa omajal on tegevusloa kehtivuse peatamise ajal, antakse hoiule asukohaj&auml;rgsesse politseiprefektuuri v&otilde;i tagatakse nende valve ja kaitse kuni tegevusloa kehtivuse peatatuse t&auml;htaja l&otilde;puni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Weapons and ammunition in the possession of the holder of an activity licence at the time of the suspension of the activity licence shall be deposited with the police prefecture of the residence of the holder, or the security and guarding of the weapons and ammunition shall be ensured until the end of the term of suspension of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relvad ja laskemoon, mis tegevusloa omajal on tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise ajal, antakse hoiule asukohaj&auml;rgsesse politseiprefektuuri v&otilde;i tagatakse nende n&otilde;uetekohane valve ja kaitse kuni nende v&otilde;&otilde;randamise v&otilde;i h&auml;vitamiseni k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Weapons and ammunition in the possession of the holder of an activity licence at the time of the revocation of the activity licence shall be deposited with the police prefecture of the residence of the holder, or the security and guarding of the weapons and ammunition shall be ensured to be in compliance with the requirements until the weapons and ammunition are transferred or destroyed pursuant to the procedure established by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Relvade ja laskemoona hoiuleandmine, vedu, hoidmine, valve, kaitse ning tagastamine toimub tegevusloa omaja kulul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Weapons and ammunition shall be deposited, transported, stored, guarded, protected and returned at the expense of the holder of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tegevusloa, mille kehtivus on peatatud, omaja v&otilde;ib peatatud tegevust j&auml;tkata &uuml;ksnes Politseiameti kirjalikul loal, kui on k&otilde;rvaldatud v&otilde;i on &auml;ra langenud tegevusloa kehtivuse peatamise aluseks olnud asjaolu. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The holder of a suspended activity licence may continue the suspended activities solely with the written authorisation of the Police Board and if the circumstances which were the basis for the suspension of the licence have ceased to exist or have been eliminated. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Juhul kui tegevusloa peatamise aluseks olnud asjaolu ei ole tegevusloa kehtivuse peatatuse aja jooksul k&otilde;rvaldatud v&otilde;i &auml;ra langenud, otsustab Politseiamet tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Police Board shall make a decision concerning the revocation of an activity licence if the circumstances which were the basis for the suspension of the licence have not ceased to exist or have not been eliminated during the time of suspension of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 72. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 72. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa omajate tegevuse seaduslikkuse kontrollimine </eesti>
<inglise>Inspection of legality of activities of holders of activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiamet ja politseiprefektuurid kontrollivad v&auml;hemalt kaks korda aastas tegevusloa omaja relvade ja laskemoonaga seonduva tegevuse seaduslikkust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Police Board and police prefectures shall inspect the legality of the weapons and ammunition related activities of the holders of activity licences at least twice a year. </inglise>
<eesti>Vajaduse korral v&otilde;idakse kontrollimisele kaasata ka teisi ametkondi v&otilde;i asutusi. </eesti>
<inglise>Other offices and agencies may be involved in inspections as necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volitus kontrollimiseks antakse ametnikule Politseiameti v&otilde;i politseiprefektuuri k&auml;skkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An officer is granted authorisation to carry out an inspection by a directive of the Police Board or a police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kontrollimise tulemuste kohta koostatakse akt, mille &uuml;ks eksemplar antakse tegevusloa omajale ja teine j&auml;&auml;b kontrollijale. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A report shall be prepared concerning the inspection results, one copy of which shall be given to the holder of the activity licence and the other shall remain with the person who conducts the inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>11. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 11 </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade ja laskemoona valmistamine, m&uuml;&uuml;k, parandamine, &uuml;mbertegemine, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmine, lammutamine ja h&auml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Manufacture, Sale, Repair and Conversion of Weapons and Ammunition, Rendering of Weapons and Ammunition Incapable of Firing, and Dismantling and Destruction of Weapons and Ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 73. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 73. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade ja laskemoona valmistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Manufacture of weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva, tulirelva olulise osa, laskemoona, samuti lasersihiku valmistamine toimub vastavalt tegevusloal n&auml;idatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Weapons, essential components of firearms, ammunition and laser sights shall be manufactured according to the specifications indicated on the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali sisaldavat laskemoona valmistatakse l&otilde;hkematerjaliseadusega (RT I 1997, 86, 1461; 2001, 65, 377; 85, 510; 88, 531) ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Ammunition containing explosive substances shall be manufactured pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Explosive Substances Act (RT I 1997, 86, 1461; 2001, 65, 377; 85, 510; 88, 531) and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relvade v&otilde;i tulirelva oluliste osade valmistamisega tegelev isik on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person engaging in the manufacture of weapons or essential components of firearms is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) hoidma toodangu valmistamiseks kasutatavat toorainet ja materjale, l&otilde;petamata ja valmistoodangut kohas ja tingimustes, mis tagavad nende s&auml;ilimise ja ohutuse &uuml;mbrusele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) store the basic products and materials used for the manufacture, and also unfinished and finished products in a place and in conditions which ensure their preservations and that they do not pose a danger to the surroundings; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tagama toodangu n&otilde;uetekohase kvaliteedi ja ohutuse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) ensure the quality and safety of the products according to the requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kandma tulirelvale ja tulirelva olulisele osale n&otilde;uetekohase markeeringu sellisel moel, et selle eemaldamine oleks tehniliselt raske v&otilde;i v&otilde;imatu. </eesti>
<inglise>3) mark a firearm or an essential component of a firearm with a marking according to the requirements in such a manner that the removal of the marking would be technically complicated or impossible; </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Eestis valmistatud relvade ja laskemoona n&otilde;uetele vastavuse t&otilde;endamine on kohustuslik ning toimub toote n&otilde;uetele vastavuse t&otilde;endamise seaduse (RT I 1999, 92, 825; 2001, 94, 579; 2002, 6, 20) ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The conformity assessment of weapons and ammunition manufactured in Estonia is mandatory and shall be conducted pursuant to the procedure established by the Product Conformity Attestation Act (RT I 1999, 92, 825; 2001, 94, 579; 2002, 6, 20) and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) N&otilde;uded Eestis valmistatavatele relvadele ja laskemoonale kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega v&otilde;i Vabariigi Valitsuse volitusel majandusminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The requirements for weapons and ammunition manufactured in Estonia shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic or by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs on the authorisation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi n&otilde;uded ei laiene f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku poolt kodusel teel jahipidamise eesm&auml;rgil padrunite valmistamisele padrunikomponentidest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The requirements of this section do not apply to the home production of cartridges from basic components by natural persons for the purposes of hunting. </inglise>
<eesti>Kodusel teel valmistatud padruneid ei tohi v&otilde;&otilde;randada. </eesti>
<inglise>Home-produced cartridges shall not be transferred. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Tulirelvade ja tulirelva oluliste osade markeerimise n&otilde;uded kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The requirements for the marking of firearms and essential components of firearms shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 74. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 74. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade ja laskemoona m&uuml;&uuml;k </eesti>
<inglise>Sale of weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relvade v&otilde;i laskemoona m&uuml;&uuml;gi tegevusluba omav isik on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who holds an activity licence for the sale of weapons and ammunition is required: </inglise>
<eesti>1) n&otilde;udma relva ostjalt isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi ja antud liiki relva soetamisloa esitamist, laskemoona ostjalt aga isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi ja relvaloa esitamist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to demand a purchaser of a weapon to present an identity document and an acquisition permit for the given type of weapon and to demand a purchaser of ammunition to present an identity document and a weapons permit; </inglise>
<eesti>2) n&otilde;udma komisjonim&uuml;&uuml;gile antava relva kohta selle v&otilde;&otilde;randamisluba; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to demand presentation of a transfer permit concerning a weapon which is given for commission sale; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teatama v&otilde;&otilde;randamisloa alusel m&uuml;&uuml;ki v&otilde;etud relvast loa v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuurile kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates relva m&uuml;&uuml;ki v&otilde;tmise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>3) if a weapon is taken for sale on the basis of a transfer permit, to inform the police prefecture which issued the permit within three days as of the date on which the weapon is taken for sale; </inglise>
<eesti>4) hoidma m&uuml;&uuml;giks soetatud relvi ja laskemoona kohas ja tingimustes, mis vastavad kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) to store weapons and ammunition which are taken for sale in a place and in conditions which comply with the established requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teatama soetamisloa v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuurile andmed m&uuml;&uuml;dud relva ja selle ostnud isiku kohta kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast relva m&uuml;&uuml;mist. </eesti>
<inglise>5) to forward information concerning a sold weapon and the person who purchased the weapon to the police prefecture which issued the relevant acquisition permit within three working days after the sale of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) On keelatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) It is prohibited to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) m&uuml;&uuml;a relva isikule, kes ei esita oma isikut t&otilde;endavat dokumenti ja antud liiki relva soetamisluba; </eesti>
<inglise>1) sell a weapon to a person who does not present an identity document and an acquisition permit for the given type of weapon; </inglise>
<eesti>2) m&uuml;&uuml;a piiramata tsiviilk&auml;ibega relva alla 18 aasta vanusele isikule; </eesti>
<inglise>2) sell a weapon in unrestricted commerce to a person of less than 18 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teadvalt m&uuml;&uuml;a defektset relva v&otilde;i laskemoona; </eesti>
<inglise>3) knowingly sell a defective weapon or ammunition; </inglise>
<eesti>4) m&uuml;&uuml;a relva v&otilde;i padruneid, millel ei ole t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust, v&auml;lja arvatud komisjonim&uuml;&uuml;giks v&otilde;etud relv. </eesti>
<inglise>4) sell weapons or cartridges which have not been type approved, except for weapons taken for commission sale. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tehnilised n&otilde;uded relvade ja laskemoona m&uuml;&uuml;gikohale kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Technical requirements for the points of sale of weapons and ammunition shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 75. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 75. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade ja laskemoona arvestus nende valmistamisel ja m&uuml;&uuml;misel </eesti>
<inglise>Keeping of records regarding weapons and ammunition upon sale thereof </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa alusel relvi, tulirelva olulisi osi, lasersihikuid ja laskemoona valmistav ning m&uuml;&uuml;v isik on kohustatud pidama eraldi arvestust relvade, tulirelva oluliste osade, lasersihikute ja laskemoona kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who manufactures or sells weapons, essential components of firearms, laser sights and ammunition on the basis of an activity licence is required to keep separate records of the weapons, essential components of firearms, laser sights and ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arvestust peetakse n&ouml;&ouml;ritud ja politseiprefektuuri pitseriga kinnitatud relvaraamatus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Records shall be kept in a weapons ledger bound with string and sealed with the seal of the police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvaraamatu vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The standard format for weapons ledgers shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relvaraamatu &uuml;hele poolele m&auml;rgitakse valmistatud v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;giks soetatud, teisele poolele realiseeritud relvad, tulirelva olulised osad, lasersihikud v&otilde;i laskemoon. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Weapons, essential components of firearms, laser sights and ammunition manufactured or acquired with the aim of being sold shall be specified on one side of a weapons ledger, and weapons, essential components of firearms, laser sights and ammunition sold shall be specified on the other side of the ledger. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Relvaraamatut s&auml;ilitatakse viis aastat viimase sissekande tegemise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Weapons ledgers shall be preserved for five years as of the date of the last entry being made in the ledger. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Relvaraamatusse kantud andmetest on lubatud teavitada ainult vastavat kontrollimise &otilde;igust omavat isikut ning isikut, kellele dokumentidele juurdep&auml;&auml;su &otilde;igus on antud muu seadusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Information entered in a weapons ledger may be disclosed only to persons with corresponding inspection rights or to persons who have been granted access to such documents by any other Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 76. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 76. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva parandamine </eesti>
<inglise>Repair of weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva parandamise all m&otilde;istetakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses relva defekti k&otilde;rvaldamist viisil, millega ei kaasne relva omaduste olulist muutumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The repair of weapons is defined in this Act as the elimination of a defect on a weapon in a manner which does not involve essential changes being made to the characteristics of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relva parandamiseks ei n&otilde;uta luba ja seda v&otilde;ib teha relvaomanik v&otilde;i -valdaja v&otilde;i tema tellimusel vastavat tegevusluba omav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Permission is not required to repair weapons and a weapon may be repaired by the owner or possessor thereof or by a person who holds a corresponding activity licence if the owner or possessor of the weapon places such an order. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 77. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 77. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva &uuml;mbertegemine </eesti>
<inglise>Conversion of weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva &uuml;mbertegemise all m&otilde;istetakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses relva muutmist viisil, millega kaasneb relva omaduste oluline muutumine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The conversion of weapons is defined in this Act as the changing of a weapon in a manner which involves essential changes being made to the characteristics of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relva &uuml;mbertegemine v&otilde;ib toimuda ainult k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 80 nimetatud relva &uuml;mbertegemise loa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Weapons may be converted only on the basis a weapons conversion permit provided for in &sect; 80 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiprefektuur v&otilde;ib relva &uuml;mbertegemise loa andmisest keelduda, kui taotlus on p&otilde;hjendamata v&otilde;i kui taotletakse relva &uuml;mbertegemist viisil, mille tagaj&auml;rjel &uuml;mbertehtud relv ei vasta enam oma esialgsetele liigitunnustele, juhul, kui relvaomanik v&otilde;i -valdaja ei oma vastavat relvaluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A police prefecture may refuse to issue a weapons conversion permit if the request to convert a weapon is unfounded, or if it is requested that the weapon be converted in a manner as a result of which the weapon would no longer have its original characteristics and if the owner or possessor of the weapon does not hold a corresponding weapons permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Relva &uuml;mbertegemise loal n&auml;idatakse, millises ulatuses on relva &uuml;mbertegemine lubatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The conversion permit of a weapon shall indicate the extent to which the weapon may be converted. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui relva &uuml;mbertegemisel asendati relva oluline osa, millel on relva number, tuleb sellest teatada loa v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If an essential component of a weapon bearing the number of the weapon is substituted during conversion of the weapon, the police prefecture which issued the permit shall be promptly notified thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 78. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 78. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmine </eesti>
<inglise>Rendering of weapons incapable of firing </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmine toimub tulirelva olulise osa mehaanilise t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise teel, mille tulemusena relv kaotab j&auml;&auml;davalt lasu sooritamise v&otilde;ime. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A weapon is rendered incapable of firing by the mechanical processing of any of the essential components of the firearm as a result of which the weapon permanently loses the capacity to be fired. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relva v&otilde;ib laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muuta relva parandamise v&otilde;i &uuml;mbertegemise tegevusluba omav isik ainult k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 80 nimetatud relva laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmise loa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Weapons may be rendered incapable of firing by persons who hold an activity licence for the repair or conversion of weapons solely on the basis of the permit for rendering weapons incapable of firing provided for in &sect; 80 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relva laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmise tehnilised n&otilde;uded kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The technical requirements for rendering weapons incapable of firing shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 79. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 79. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva lammutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Dismantling of weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva lammutamise all m&otilde;istetakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses relva kasutamisest loobumist ja selle lahtiv&otilde;tmist koostisosadeks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The dismantling of a weapon is defined in this Act as cessation of the use of the weapon and disassembly of the weapon into its components. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relva v&otilde;ib lammutada ainult k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 80 nimetatud relva lammutamise loa alusel relvaomanik v&otilde;i -valdaja v&otilde;i tema tellimusel relva parandamise v&otilde;i &uuml;mbertegemise tegevusluba omav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Weapons may be dismantled solely on the basis of a weapons dismantling permit provided for in &sect; 80 of this Act by the owner or possessor of the weapon or by a person who holds an activity licence for the repair or conversion of weapons and with whom the owner or possessor has placed a corresponding order. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Relva lammutamisest j&auml;relej&auml;&auml;nud kasutusk&otilde;lblikke tulirelva olulisi osi v&otilde;ib kasutada &uuml;ksnes relvade parandamiseks v&otilde;i &uuml;mbertegemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Essential components of a firearm which remain usable after the weapon has been dismantled may be used solely for the repair or conversion of weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidiline isik v&otilde;tab kasutusk&otilde;lblikud relva olulised osad arvele k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 75 kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Legal persons shall keep records of usable essential components of dismantled firearms pursuant to the procedure established in &sect; 75 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&otilde;lbmatud tulirelva olulised osad h&auml;vitatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 83 kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Unusable essential components of firearms shall be destroyed pursuant to the procedure established in &sect; 83 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 80. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 80. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva v&otilde;&otilde;randamise, &uuml;mbertegemise, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmise ja lammutamise luba </eesti>
<inglise>Weapons transfer permit, weapons conversion permit, permit for rendering weapons incapable of firing and weapons dismantling permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva v&otilde;&otilde;randamise, &uuml;mbertegemise, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmise v&otilde;i lammutamise loa (edaspidi luba) annab relvaomaniku v&otilde;i -valdaja taotlusel politseiprefektuur, kus relv on registreeritud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Weapons transfer permits, weapons conversion permits, permits for rendering weapons incapable of firing and weapons dismantling permits (hereinafter permits) shall be issued by the police prefecture where the weapon is registered on the application of the owner or possessor of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Loa taotlemise avalduses m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An application for a permit shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) omaniku v&otilde;i valdaja andmed - f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku ees- ja perekonnanimi, isikukood ja elukoht, juriidilise isiku nimi, registrikood v&otilde;i registreerimisnumber, aadress ja kontakttelefoni number; </eesti>
<inglise>1) data concerning the owner or possessor of the weapon: the given name, family name, personal identification code and residence of a natural person, or the name, registry code or registration number, address and telephone number of a legal person; </inglise>
<eesti>2) relva liik, mark, kaliiber ja markeering; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the type, mark, calibre and marking of the weapon; </inglise>
<eesti>3) relvaloa number, v&auml;ljastamise ja kehtivuse aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the number, date of issue and validity of the weapons permit; </inglise>
<eesti>4) milleks taotlus esitatakse (v&otilde;&otilde;randamine, &uuml;mbertegemine, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmine, lammutamine); </eesti>
<inglise>4) the reason for the application (transfer, conversion, rendering incapable of firing, dismantling); </inglise>
<eesti>5) loa realiseerimise viis (kellele ja mil viisil relv v&otilde;&otilde;randatakse, millises ulatuses relv &uuml;mber tehakse, kes relva &uuml;mber teeb, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muudab v&otilde;i lammutab). </eesti>
<inglise>5) the manner of realisation of the permit (to whom and in which manner the weapon is to be transferred, the extent to which the weapon is to be converted, who is to convert the weapon, render it incapable of firing or dismantle it). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avaldusele lisatakse relvaluba, selle puudumisel aga relva omamise seaduslikkust t&otilde;endav dokument. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A weapons permit or, in the absence of a weapons permit, a document in proof of the legality of the ownership of a weapon shall be annexed to an application. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud dokumendid tagastatakse p&auml;rast kontrollimist loa taotlejale. </eesti>
<inglise>Such documents shall be returned to the applicant after their verification. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Politseiprefektuur vaatab taotluse l&auml;bi hiljemalt &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates k&otilde;igi n&otilde;utavate dokumentide esitamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The police prefecture shall review an application not later than within one month as of the date of submission of all the required documents. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Luba ei anta isikule, kes kasutab relva paralleelrelvaloa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A permit shall not be granted to a person who uses a weapon on the basis of a parallel weapons permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Loa v&auml;ljastamisest keeldumise korral peab sellekohane otsus olema motiveeritud ning viitama selle aluseks oleva seaduse v&otilde;i seaduse alusel antud &otilde;igusakti vastavale s&auml;ttele. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) In the event of refusal to issue a permit, the decision to such effect shall be reasoned and contain a reference to the Act or other legislation issued on the basis of an Act which constitutes the basis therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa v&auml;ljastamisest keeldumise otsusest teatatakse taotlejale kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast sellise otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmist. </eesti>
<inglise>The applicant shall be notified of the reasons for refusal to issue a permit within three working days after the corresponding decision is made. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Luba on kehtiv &uuml;ks kuu, mille jooksul on relvaomanikul &otilde;igus relv v&otilde;&otilde;randada, anda see komisjonim&uuml;&uuml;ki, &uuml;mbertegemiseks, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmiseks v&otilde;i lammutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The permit is valid for one month during which time the owner of the weapon has the right to transfer the weapon or give it to be sold by commission sale, converted, rendered incapable of firing or dismantled. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Kui luba ei olnud v&otilde;imalik kasutada &uuml;he kuu jooksul, pikendab loa v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuur loa kehtivust&auml;htaega &uuml;he kuu v&otilde;rra, kui pikendamise taotlus on p&otilde;hjendatud ja esitatud enne loa kehtivust&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) If it is impossible to use the permit within one month, the police prefecture which issued the permit shall extend the term of validity of the permit by one month if there is good reason for the application for extension and if the application is submitted before the expiry of the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Relva v&otilde;&otilde;randamise luba ei piira relva komisjonim&uuml;&uuml;giks vajaminevat aega. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) A weapon transfer permit does not limit the time needed for the commission sale of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Relvade m&uuml;&uuml;gi tegevusloa omajal on &otilde;igus komisjonim&uuml;&uuml;ki antud relv &uuml;he kuu m&ouml;&ouml;dudes omanikule tagastada. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) The holder of an activity licence for the sale of weapons has the right to return a weapon to the owner thereof one month after the weapon was given for commission sale. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul teeb m&uuml;&uuml;ja loale m&auml;rke relva tagastamise kohta ja teatab sellest kirjalikult kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul loa v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>In this case, the seller shall make a notation concerning the return of the weapon on the permit and notify the police prefecture which issued the permit in writing within three working days. </inglise>
<eesti>(11) Kui relvaluba tunnistatakse kehtetuks ajal, millal relv on antud m&uuml;&uuml;ki v&otilde;i &uuml;mbertegemisele, annab relva asukohaj&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile &uuml;le relva m&uuml;&uuml;ja v&otilde;i &uuml;mbertegija. </eesti>
<inglise>(11) If a weapons permit is revoked during the time that the weapon is given for sale or conversion, the weapon shall be handed over to the police prefecture of the location of the weapon by the person who sells or converts the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(12) P&auml;rast tehingu sooritamist tehakse loale sellekohane m&auml;rge ja luba tagastatakse viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul loa v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuurile ning see on teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registrisse vastava m&auml;rke tegemise aluseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(12) After the conclusion of a transaction, a notation to this effect shall be made on the permit and the permit shall be returned to the police prefecture which issued the permit within five working days, and this constitutes the basis for a corresponding notation to be made in the register of service and civilian weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(13) Loa vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(13) The standard format for permits shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 81. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 81. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade parandamise ja &uuml;mbertegemisega tegeleva isiku kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of persons engaging in repair or conversion of weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relvade parandamise v&otilde;i &uuml;mbertegemise tegevusluba omav isik on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who holds an activity licence for the repair or conversion of weapons is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) n&otilde;udma relva parandamiseks toonud isikult isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi ja relvaloa esitamist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) demand a person who brings a weapon for repair to present an identity document and a weapons permit; </inglise>
<eesti>2) n&otilde;udma relva &uuml;mbertegemiseks, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmiseks v&otilde;i lammutamiseks toonud isikult isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi ja relvaloa esitamist koos relva &uuml;mbertegemise, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmise v&otilde;i lammutamise loaga; </eesti>
<inglise>2) demand a person who brings a weapon to be converted, rendered incapable of firing or dismantled to present an identity document and a weapons permit together with a weapons conversion permit, permit for rendering a weapon incapable of firing or weapons dismantling permit. </inglise>
<eesti>3) teatama &uuml;mbertehtud, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muudetud v&otilde;i lammutatud relva ja selle omaniku v&otilde;i valdaja andmed vastava loa andnud politseiprefektuurile kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast relva &uuml;mbertegemist, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmist v&otilde;i lammutamist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) communicate information concerning a converted weapon, a weapon rendered incapable of firing or a dismantled weapon and data concerning the owner or possessor of the weapon to the police prefecture which issued the corresponding permit within three working days after the weapon is converted, rendered incapable of firing or dismantled; </inglise>
<eesti>4) hoidma vastuv&otilde;etud relva ning relvade parandamiseks ja &uuml;mbertegemiseks vajalikke tulirelva olulisi osi k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras ja tingimustel ning tagama nende s&auml;ilimise; </eesti>
<inglise>4) store a received weapon and the essential components of firearms needed for the repair and conversion of weapons pursuant to the procedure and under the conditions provided for in this Act and ensure their preservation; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teatama relva vastuv&otilde;tmisest &uuml;mbertegemiseks, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmiseks v&otilde;i lammutamiseks vastava loa v&auml;ljastanud politseiprefektuurile kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates relva vastuv&otilde;tmise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>5) inform the police prefecture which issued the corresponding permit of any weapon received for conversion, rendering incapable of firing or dismantling within three working days as of the receipt of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Keelatud on vastu v&otilde;tta relva parandamiseks, &uuml;mbertegemiseks, laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmiseks v&otilde;i lammutamiseks isikult, kes ei esita isikut t&otilde;endavat dokumenti ja n&otilde;utavat luba. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) It is prohibited to receive a weapon for repair, conversion, rendering incapable of firing or dismantling from a person who fails to submit an identity document and a required permit. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 82. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 82. </inglise>
<eesti>Parandamisele, &uuml;mbertegemisele ja laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmisele toodud relvade arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Keeping of records regarding weapons brought for repair, conversion or rendering incapable of firing </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa alusel relvade parandamise, &uuml;mbertegemise ja laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmisega tegelev isik on kohustatud pidama parandamisele, &uuml;mbertegemisele ja laskek&otilde;lbmatuks muutmisele toodud relvade, samuti relvade parandamiseks ja &uuml;mbertegemiseks vajalike tulirelva oluliste osade arvestust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who, on the basis of an activity licence, engages in the repair or conversion of weapons or the rendering of weapons incapable of firing is required to keep records regarding weapons which are brought for repair, conversion or rendering incapable of firing, and also regarding the essential components of firearms needed for the repair or conversion of weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arvestust peetakse n&ouml;&ouml;ritud ja politseiprefektuuri pitseriga kinnitatud relvaraamatus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Records shall be kept in a weapons ledger bound with string and sealed with the seal of the police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvaraamatu vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The standard format for weapons ledgers shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 83. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 83. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona h&auml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Destruction of weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Relva ja laskemoona h&auml;vitamise all m&otilde;istetakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses relva kui terviku ja laskemoona f&uuml;&uuml;silist h&auml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The destruction of weapons and ammunition is defined in this Act as the physical destruction of a weapon as a whole and of ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) H&auml;vitamisele kuuluvad: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following are subject to destruction: </inglise>
<eesti>1) leitud laskek&otilde;lbmatu relv ja laskemoon; </eesti>
<inglise>1) weapons and ammunition which are found in an unserviceable state; </inglise>
<eesti>2) omaniku poolt h&auml;vitamiseks antud relv ja laskemoon; </eesti>
<inglise>2) weapons and ammunition given by the owner thereof for destruction; </inglise>
<eesti>3) muu relv ja laskemoon seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel antud &otilde;igusaktiga kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>3) other weapons and ammunition pursuant to the procedure established by law or legislation issued on the basis of law. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) H&auml;vitamisele ei kuulu ajaloo- v&otilde;i kultuuriv&auml;&auml;rtusega relv. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Weapons of historical or cultural value are not subject to destruction. </inglise>
<eesti>Ajaloo- v&otilde;i kultuuriv&auml;&auml;rtust omavaks tunnistatakse relv muinsuskaitseseadusega (RT I 1994, 24, 391; 1996, 49, 953; 86, 1538; 1997, 93, 1559) kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>A weapon is declared to have historical or cultural value pursuant to the procedure established by the Heritage Conservation Act (RT I 1994, 24, 391; 1996, 49, 953; 86, 1538; 1997, 93, 1559). </inglise>
<eesti>Ajaloo- v&otilde;i kultuuriv&auml;&auml;rtusega relv kuulub s&auml;ilitamisele relvakollektsioonis k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>A weapon of historical or cultural value is subject to preservation in a weapons collection pursuant to the procedure provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) H&auml;vitamisele kuuluva relva ja laskemoona annab relvaomanik v&otilde;i -valdaja koos sellekohase avaldusega elu- v&otilde;i asukohaj&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The owner or possessor of a weapon or ammunition subject to destruction shall hand over the weapon together with an application to this effect to the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the owner or holder of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvade ja laskemoona h&auml;vitamist korraldab Politseiamet. </eesti>
<inglise>The destruction of weapons and ammunition shall be organised by the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Relv h&auml;vitatakse &uuml;mbersulatamise v&otilde;i vastava pressi all purustamise teel sellisel moel, et relva kui terviku ja selle &uuml;ksiku osa edasine kasutamine oleks v&otilde;imatu. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A weapon shall be destroyed by being melted or by being crushed under a suitable press in a manner which precludes the further use of the weapon as a whole and of any of its components. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) L&otilde;hkematerjali sisaldav laskemoon h&auml;vitatakse l&otilde;hkematerjaliseadusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Ammunition containing explosive substances shall be destroyed pursuant to the procedure established by the Explosive Substances Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Relv ja laskemoon h&auml;vitatakse Politseiameti juhi poolt volitatud politseiametniku juuresolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Weapons and ammunition shall be destroyed in the presence of a police officer authorised by the head of the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>H&auml;vitamise juurde v&otilde;idakse kutsuda relvaomanik v&otilde;i -valdaja, samuti teiste ametkondade esindajaid. </eesti>
<inglise>The owner or possessor of the weapon or representatives of other agencies may be invited to be present at the destruction of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Relva ja laskemoona h&auml;vitamise kohta koostatakse akt, milles n&auml;idatakse relva v&otilde;i laskemoona liik, mark, mudel, kaliiber, relva markeering (selle olemasolu korral), laskemoona kogus, h&auml;vitamise koht, kuup&auml;ev ja moodus. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A report shall be prepared concerning the destruction of a weapon or ammunition which sets out the type, mark, model, calibre and marking (if there is a marking) of the weapon, the quantity of ammunition, and the location, date and manner of destruction. </inglise>
<eesti>Akt koostatakse kahes eksemplaris, millest &uuml;ks k&ouml;idetakse relvatoimikusse, teine antakse relvaomanikule v&otilde;i -valdajale. </eesti>
<inglise>The report shall be prepared in two original copies of which one shall be bound into the weapon register book and the other shall be given to the owner or possessor of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Aktile kirjutavad alla relva v&otilde;i laskemoona h&auml;vitamise juures viibinud politseiametnik ja teised isikud. </eesti>
<inglise>The report shall be signed by the police officer and other persons who were present at the destruction of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Relva h&auml;vitamise kohta tehakse teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registrisse vastav m&auml;rge. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) A notice concerning the destruction of a weapon shall be made in the register of service and civilian weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>12. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 12 </inglise>
<eesti>Lasketiir ja laskepaik </eesti>
<inglise>Firing Ranges and Field Firing Ranges </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 84. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 84. </inglise>
<eesti>Lasketiir ja laskepaik </eesti>
<inglise>Firing ranges and field firing ranges </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lasketiir on k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes laskev&otilde;istlusteks v&otilde;i -harjutusteks alaliselt kasutatav ehitis, ruum v&otilde;i territoorium. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, a firing range is a structure, space or territory permanently used for shooting competitions or practice. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laskepaik on koht, mis sobib v&otilde;i on kohandatud laskev&otilde;istluste v&otilde;i -harjutuste ajutiseks korraldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A field firing range is a place which is suitable for or adapted for the temporary organisation of shooting competitions or practice. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lasketiiru v&otilde;i laskepaiga rajamiseks peab olema selle kohaliku omavalitsuse kirjalik n&otilde;usolek, kelle territooriumile see tahetakse rajada. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to construct a firing range or field firing range, written consent shall be obtained from the local government in the territory of which the firing range or field firing range is to be constructed. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lasketiir v&otilde;i laskepaik peab asetsema, olema rajatud ja seadistatud selliselt, et selle kasutamisel on tagatud lasketiiru v&otilde;i laskepaiga kasutajate ja &uuml;mbruse ohutus ning v&auml;listatud k&otilde;rvaliste inimeste ja loomade p&auml;&auml;s laskmispiirkonda. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A firing range or field firing range shall be located, constructed and adapted in a manner which ensures the safety of the users of firing range or field firing range and its surroundings and precludes the entry of unauthorised persons and animals into the shooting area. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Lasketiir ja laskepaik, kus korraldatakse spordiv&otilde;istlusi, peab olema ehitatud ja varustatud vastava rahvusvaheliselt tunnustatud spordiorganisatsiooni n&otilde;uete kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A firing range or field firing range where sports events are organised shall be constructed and equipped according to the requirements of the corresponding internationally recognised sports organisation. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Lasketiirus ja laskepaigas peavad n&auml;htavale kohale olema v&auml;lja pandud ohutusn&otilde;uded, sisekorraeeskiri ning laskmise eest vastutava isiku nimi. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Safety requirements, internal procedure rules and the name of the person responsible for shooting activities shall be displayed in a visible place at a firing range or field firing range. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Lasketiiru ja laskepaiga ning laskev&otilde;istluse ja treeninglaskmise ohutusn&otilde;uded kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The safety requirements for firing ranges and field firing ranges and for shooting competitions and shooting practice shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi m&otilde;isted ja n&otilde;uded ei laiene kaitsej&otilde;udude harjutusv&auml;ljal paiknevale lasketiirule ja laskepaigale. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The definitions and requirements of this section do not apply to firing ranges and field firing ranges located within Defence Forces training areas. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 85. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 85. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaitsej&otilde;udude harjutusv&auml;li </eesti>
<inglise>Defence Forces training areas </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kaitsej&otilde;udude harjutusv&auml;li on maa- v&otilde;i mereala koos selle kohal oleva &otilde;huruumiga, kus korraldatakse kaitsev&auml;e ja Kaitseliidu &uuml;ksuste taktikalisi harjutusi ja &otilde;ppusi, laskmisi ja l&otilde;hket&ouml;id ning katsetatakse relvi, lahingumoona, lahingu- ja muud tehnikat. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A Defence Forces training area is an area of land or sea which includes the airspace above the area and where the Defence Forces and units of the National Defence League organise their tactical training, exercises, shooting and blasting and where weapons, munitions of war, battle equipment and other equipment is tested. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaitsej&otilde;udude harjutusv&auml;ljad on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following are deemed to be Defence Forces training areas: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kaitsev&auml;e keskpol&uuml;goon; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the Defence Forces central training area; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;huv&auml;epol&uuml;goon; </eesti>
<inglise>2) air force training areas; </inglise>
<eesti>3) merev&auml;epol&uuml;goon; </eesti>
<inglise>3) naval training areas; </inglise>
<eesti>4) v&auml;eosa harjutusv&auml;li; </eesti>
<inglise>4) unit training areas; </inglise>
<eesti>5) Kaitseliidu maleva harjutusv&auml;li. </eesti>
<inglise>5) National Defence League unit training areas. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kaitsej&otilde;udude harjutusv&auml;lja asutamise otsustab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The setting up of Defence Forces training areas shall be decided by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kaitsej&otilde;udude harjutusv&auml;ljale esitatavad n&otilde;uded ja kasutamise korra kehtestab kaitseminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The requirements and procedure for the use of Defence Forces training areas shall be established by the Minister of Defence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 86. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 86. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva laenutamine lasketiirus </eesti>
<inglise>Rental of weapons at firing ranges </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lasketiirus v&otilde;ib relva laenutada isik (edaspidi laenutaja), kellel on tegevusluba relvade laenutamiseks lasketiirus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Weapons may be rented at a firing range by a person (hereinafter lender) who has an activity licence for the rental of weapons at a firing range. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppeasutuses ja laskespordiorganisatsioonis, kus laskespordiga tegeldakse p&otilde;hikirja alusel, ei ole tegevusluba n&otilde;utav. </eesti>
<inglise>An activity licence is not required in an educational institution or a shooting sports organisation where engagement in shooting sports is included in the articles of association or statutes as an activity. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Relva laenutatakse isikule (edaspidi laenaja) isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi esitamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person (hereinafter borrower) shall be rented a weapon upon submission of an identity document. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi alusel kantakse laenaja ees- ja perekonnanimi ja isikukood relvaraamatusse. </eesti>
<inglise>The given name, surname and personal identification code of the borrower shall be entered in the weapons ledger on the basis of the identity document. </inglise>
<eesti>Laenaja, kellel vanuse t&otilde;ttu isikut t&otilde;endavat dokumenti veel ei ole, esitab &otilde;pilaspileti. </eesti>
<inglise>A borrower who does not have an identity document because of his or her age shall present his or her student card. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Enne relva laenamist peab laenaja tutvuma relva ja laskemoona k&auml;sitsemise ohutusn&otilde;uetega ja lasketiiru sisekorraeeskirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Before borrowing a weapon, a borrower shall examine the safety requirements for the handling of weapons and ammunition and the internal procedure rules of the firing range. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle kohta annab ta relvaraamatusse allkirja. </eesti>
<inglise>The borrower shall sign the weapons ledger to confirm that he or she has reviewed the requirements and rules specified above. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud n&otilde;udeid ja eeskirja tutvustab relvade laenutamise eest vastutav isik v&otilde;i laskeinstruktor. </eesti>
<inglise>The borrower shall be familiarised with these requirements and rules by the person responsible for rental or a shooting instructor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Relva laenutamine kantakse relvaraamatusse, mille kohta laenaja annab oma allkirja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The borrowing of a weapon shall be recorded in a weapons ledger, concerning which the borrower shall give his or her signature. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva laenaja vastutab relva hoidmise ning &otilde;igusp&auml;rase ja ohutu kasutamise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>The borrower of a weapon is responsible for the storing of the weapon and its legal and safe use. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Laenutatud relva v&otilde;ib kasutada ainult samas lasketiirus laskeinstruktori juhendamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A rented weapon shall be used only at the same firing range under the instruction of a shooting instructor. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Iseseisvalt v&otilde;ib laenutatud relva kasutada laenaja, kellel on relvaluba v&otilde;i laskeinstruktori, lasketreeneri v&otilde;i laskesportlase litsents. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Only borrowers who hold a weapons permit or a licence of a shooting instructor, shooting coach or shooting athlete may use a rented weapon independently. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Sporditulirelva v&otilde;ib laenutada v&auml;hemalt 16-aastasele isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Sporting firearms may be rented to persons who are of at least 16 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) &Otilde;ppeasutuse v&otilde;i p&otilde;hikirja alusel tegutseva laskespordiorganisatsiooni lasketiirus v&otilde;ib laskeinstruktori v&otilde;i relvaluba omava lapsevanema vahetu j&auml;relevalve all sporditulirelva kasutada anda v&auml;hemalt 12-aastasele isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) At a firing range of an educational institution or a shooting sports organisation operating on the basis of its articles of association or statutes, a person who is of at least 12 years of age may be issued with a shooting firearm for use under the direct supervision of a shooting instructor or the person's parent if the parent holds a weapons permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) P&auml;rast relva kasutamist tuleb laenutatud relv viivitamata tagastada laenutajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) A borrowed weapon shall be promptly returned to the lender after use. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva vastuv&otilde;tnud isik teeb relvaraamatusse m&auml;rke relva vastuv&otilde;tmise kohta ja kinnitab seda oma allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>The person who receives the weapon shall make a notation concerning the receipt of the weapon in the weapons ledger and confirm the entry with his or her signature. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva v&auml;ljaviimine lasketiirust on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited to take a weapon out of a firing range. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 87. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 87. </inglise>
<eesti>Laskemoona m&uuml;&uuml;k lasketiirus </eesti>
<inglise>Sale of ammunition at firing range </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laskemoona v&otilde;ib lasketiirus m&uuml;&uuml;a isik, kellel on tegevusluba laskemoona m&uuml;&uuml;giks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Ammunition may be sold at a firing range by a person who has an activity licence for the sale of ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laskemoona v&otilde;ib m&uuml;&uuml;a relvaomanikule v&otilde;i -valdajale relvaloa alusel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 46 l&otilde;ikega 4 kehtestatud koguses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Ammunition may be sold to owners or possessors of weapons on the basis of a weapons permit in the quantities established by subsection 46 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui laskemoona ostetakse laskmiseks lasketiirust laenatud relvaga, ei ole relvaloa esitamine n&otilde;utav. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) It is not necessary to present a weapons permit if ammunition is purchased for shooting with a weapon borrowed from a firing range. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul on laskemoona v&auml;ljaviimine lasketiirust keelatud ning lasketiirus kasutamata laskemoon kuulub tagasiostmisele. </eesti>
<inglise>In this case it is prohibited to take the ammunition out of the firing range and any ammunition not used at the firing range is subject to repurchase. </inglise>
<eesti>13. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 13 </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 88. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 88. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalve seaduse t&auml;itmise &uuml;le </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision of compliance with this Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) J&auml;relevalvet tsiviilk&auml;ibes olevate relvade ja laskemoona k&auml;itlemise &uuml;le teostavad politseiasutused ning relvade ja laskemoona &uuml;le tollipiiri toimetamise seaduslikkuse &uuml;le tolli- ja piirivalveasutused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Supervision over the handling of weapons and ammunition the use of which is permitted for civilian purposes shall be exercised by the police authorities and supervision over the legality of the carriage of weapons and ammunition across the customs frontier shall be exercised by the customs and border guard authorities. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) J&auml;relevalvet s&otilde;jav&auml;erelvade ja teenistusrelvade k&auml;itlemise &uuml;le teostavad Vabariigi Valitsuse volitatud asutused. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Supervision over the handling of military and service weapons shall be exercised by bodies authorised by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) J&auml;relevalvet k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide t&auml;itmise &uuml;le asutuste poolt teostavad ka nende k&otilde;rgemalseisvad asutused. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Supervision over the compliance of agencies with this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof shall also be exercised by their superior agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalvet teostava ametiisiku &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of supervisory officials </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevast seadusest ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidest kinnipidamise &uuml;le j&auml;relevalvet teostama volitatud ametiisikul on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>Officials authorised to exercise supervision over compliance with this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof have the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teostada relvade ja laskemoona ning nende kohtade &uuml;levaatust, kus neid hoitakse, valmistatakse, m&uuml;&uuml;akse, laenutatakse, parandatakse, &uuml;mber tehakse, lammutatakse v&otilde;i h&auml;vitatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>1) inspect weapons and ammunition and places where weapons and ammunition are stored, manufactured, sold, rented, repaired, converted, dismantled or destroyed; </inglise>
<eesti>2) n&otilde;uda f&uuml;&uuml;siliselt isikult ning juriidilise isiku esindajalt dokumentide esitamist ja kirjalikku v&otilde;i suulist informatsiooni, mis on tarvilik j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) demand natural persons and representatives of legal persons to present documents and written or oral information needed for supervision purposes; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teha ettekirjutus avastatud &otilde;igusrikkumise k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ja kontrollida ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) issue precepts for the elimination of detected violations and to verify compliance with such precepts; </inglise>
<eesti>4) v&otilde;tta k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;itmise tagamiseks tarvitusele muid abin&otilde;usid, mis on ette n&auml;htud seaduste ja nende alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega. </eesti>
<inglise>4) take other measures prescribed by Acts and legislation issued on the basis thereof in order to ensure compliance with this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>13 (1). peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 13 (1) </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Relva, tulirelva olulise osa v&otilde;i laskemoona k&auml;itlemise n&otilde;uete ning arvestuse ja registreerimise korra rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements for handling of or procedure for keeping records and registration of weapons, essential components of firearms or ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku poolt relva, tulirelva olulise osa v&otilde;i laskemoona hoidmise, &uuml;leandmise, valmistamise, &uuml;mbertegemise, parandamise, m&uuml;&uuml;gi, laenutamise, veo v&otilde;i k&auml;itlemise muude n&otilde;uete v&otilde;i arvestuse v&otilde;i registreerimise korra rikkumise eest - karistatakse kuni 50 000-kroonise rahatrahviga. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine of up to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed on a legal person for violation of the requirements for the storage, conveying, manufacture, conversion, repair, sale, rental or transport of weapons, essential components of firearms or ammunition, or for violation of other requirements for the handling of weapons, essential components of firearms or ammunition, or for violation of the procedure for keeping records and registration of weapons, essential components of firearms or ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89 (2). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>Elektri&scaron;okirelva ja tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud k&uuml;lmrelva ebaseaduslik k&auml;itlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Unlawful handling of electric shock weapons and cut-and-thrust weapons use of which for civilian purposes is prohibited </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku poolt elektri&scaron;okirelva v&otilde;i tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud k&uuml;lmrelva valmistamise, soetamise, omamise, hoidmise, m&uuml;&uuml;mise, edasitoimetamise, vedamise v&otilde;i muu ebaseadusliku k&auml;itlemise eest - karistatakse kuni 50 000-kroonise rahatrahviga. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine of up to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed on a legal person for the manufacture, acquisition, possession, storage, sale, conveying, transport or other unlawful handling of electric shock weapons and cut-and-thrust weapons the use of which for civilian purposes is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89 (3). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89 (3). </inglise>
<eesti>Gaasi-, pneumo-, heit- v&otilde;i k&uuml;lmrelva ebaseaduslik k&auml;itlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Unlawful handling of gas, pneumatic, projectile and cut-and-thrust weapons </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku poolt gaasi-, pneumo-, heit- v&otilde;i k&uuml;lmrelva, v&auml;lja arvatud tsiviilk&auml;ibes keelatud k&uuml;lmrelv, valmistamise, soetamise, omamise, hoidmise, m&uuml;&uuml;mise, edasitoimetamise, vedamise v&otilde;i muu ebaseadusliku k&auml;itlemise eest - karistatakse kuni 20 000-kroonise rahatrahviga. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine of up to 20 000 kroons shall be imposed on a legal person for the manufacture, acquisition, possession, storage, sale, conveying, transport or other unlawful handling of gas, pneumatic, projectile and cut-and-thrust weapons, except for cut-and-thrust weapons the use of which for civilian purposes is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89 (4). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89 (4). </inglise>
<eesti>Relva ja laskemoona &uuml;leandmise n&otilde;ude rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements for handing over of weapons and ammunition </inglise>
<eesti>Relva v&otilde;i laskemoona etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaja jooksul politseiasutusele &uuml;leandmata j&auml;tmise eest juriidilise isiku poolt, kelle relvasoetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa kehtivus on l&otilde;ppenud, peatatud v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistatud, - karistatakse kuni 30 000-kroonise rahatrahviga. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine of up to 30 000 kroons shall be imposed on a legal person whose acquisition permit or weapons permit has expired, has been suspended or revoked, for failure to hand over weapons or ammunition to the police authorities within the prescribed term. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89 (5). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89 (5). </inglise>
<eesti>Relvasoetamisloa ja relvaloa tagastamise n&otilde;ude rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirement of return of acquisition permit or weapons permit </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku poolt relvasoetamisloa v&otilde;i relvaloa, mille kehtivus on l&otilde;ppenud, peatatud v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistatud, etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaja jooksul politseiasutusele tagastamata j&auml;tmise eest - karistatakse kuni 10 000-kroonise rahatrahviga. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine of up to 10 000 kroons shall be imposed on a legal person for failure to return an expired, suspended or revoked acquisition permit or weapons permit to the police authorities within the prescribed term. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89 (6). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89 (6). </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet teostava ametiisiku tegevuse takistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Obstruction of activities of official exercising state supervision </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku poolt riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet teostavale ametiisikule relva, tulirelva olulise osa v&otilde;i laskemoona kontrollimiseks esitamata j&auml;tmise v&otilde;i nende hoiu- ja asukoha v&otilde;i lasketiiru v&otilde;i laskepaiga kontrollimise takistamise v&otilde;i kontrollimiseks vajalike dokumentide v&otilde;i andmete esitamisest keeldumise, samuti valeandmete esitamise eest v&otilde;i esitamise eest sellisel kujul, mis ei v&otilde;imaldanud j&auml;relevalve teostamist, - karistatakse kuni 50 000-kroonise rahatrahviga. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine of up to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed on a legal person for failure to submit weapons, essential components of firearms or ammunition for inspection to an official exercising state supervision, or for prevention of inspection of places of storage and locations thereof, or for refusal to submit documents and information necessary for inspection, or for presentation of false information, or for presentation of information in a form which did not allow inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89 (7). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89 (7). </inglise>
<eesti>Erikonfiskeerimise kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of seizure </inglise>
<eesti>Kohus v&otilde;ib kohaldada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 89 (1) -89 (4) s&auml;testatud haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste vahetuks objektiks olnud aine v&otilde;i eseme erikonfiskeerimist. </eesti>
<inglise>The court may apply seizure of the substance or object which was the direct object of an administrative offence provided for in &sect;&sect; 89 (1) -89 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89 (8). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89 (8). </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asja menetlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings of administrative offence matters of legal persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 89 (1) -89 (6) s&auml;testatud haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste asjades on &otilde;igus asja arutada: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following have the right to hear matters concerning administrative offences specified in &sect;&sect; 89 (1) -89 (6) of this Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) politseiametnikul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) police officers; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maa- v&otilde;i linnakohtu kohtunikul. </eesti>
<inglise>2) county or city court judges. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 89 (1) -89 (6) s&auml;testatud haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste asjades on haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostamise &otilde;igus politseiametnikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Police officers have the right to prepare administrative offence reports concerning administrative offence matters specified in &sect;&sect; 89 (1) -89 (6) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiametnikul on &otilde;igus haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asja arutades m&auml;&auml;rata rahatrahv. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Police officers have the right to impose fines upon hearing administrative offence matters. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asjas on vaja otsustada erikonfiskeerimise kohaldamine, arutab asja maa- v&otilde;i linnakohtu kohtunik. </eesti>
<inglise>County and city court judges shall hear matters concerning administrative offences where application of seizure must be decided. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Juriidilise isiku haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asja menetletakse haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikus (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453; 87, 524 ja 526; 97, 605; 102, 677; 2002, 18, 98; 21, 117; 29, 174 ja 175) ja t&auml;itemenetluse seadustikus (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238) s&auml;testatud korras, kui k&auml;esolevas seaduses ei s&auml;testata teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Proceedings in matters concerning administrative offences of legal persons shall be conducted pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453; 87, 524 and 526; 97, 605; 102, 677; 2002, 18, 98; 21, 117; 29, 174 and 175) and the Code of Enforcement Procedure (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238), unless otherwise provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.03.2002 j&otilde;ust.31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.03.2002 entered into force 31.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 29, 175) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89 (9). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89 (9). </inglise>
<eesti>Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokoll </eesti>
<inglise>Administrative offence report </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokollis m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The report concerning an administrative offence shall indicate: </inglise>
<eesti>1) selle koostamise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the time and place of its preparation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) asutuse nimetus ja aadress, kelle nimel protokoll koostatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name and address of the agency in whose name the report is prepared; </inglise>
<eesti>3) protokolli koostanud isiku ees- ja perekonnanimi ning ametinimetus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the given name, surname and official title of the person who prepares the report; </inglise>
<eesti>4) juriidilisest isikust &otilde;igusrikkuja nimi ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the name and address of the offender who is a legal person; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &otilde;igusrikkuja esindaja ees- ja perekonnanimi ning ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the given name and surname and position of the representative of the offender; </inglise>
<eesti>6) &otilde;igusrikkumise aeg ja koht ning rikkumise kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the time, place and description of the offence; </inglise>
<eesti>7) viide k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvile, mis n&auml;eb ette vastutuse selle &otilde;igusrikkumise eest; </eesti>
<inglise>7) a reference to the section of this Act which prescribes liability for the given offence; </inglise>
<eesti>8) tunnistajate seletused ja muud t&otilde;endid; </eesti>
<inglise>8) explanations provided by witnesses, and other evidence; </inglise>
<eesti>9) &otilde;igusrikkuja esindaja seletus ja m&auml;rge, et talle on tutvustatud &otilde;igust kasutada &otilde;igusabi; </eesti>
<inglise>9) an explanation from the representative of the offender and a notation that he or she has been advised of the right to obtain legal assistance; </inglise>
<eesti>10) vajaduse korral muud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>10) other information, if necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Protokollile kirjutavad alla selle koostanud ametnik ja &otilde;igusrikkuja esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The official who prepared the report and the representative of the offender shall sign the report. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui &otilde;igusrikkuja esindaja keeldub protokollile alla kirjutamast, tehakse selle kohta protokolli m&auml;rge. </eesti>
<inglise>If the representative of the offender refuses to sign the report, a corresponding notation shall be made in the report. </inglise>
<eesti>Protokollile lisatakse &otilde;igusrikkuja esindaja kirjalikud m&auml;rkused protokolli ja sellele allakirjutamisest keeldumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Written comments of the representatives of the offender on the report and the refusal to sign the report shall be annexed to the report. </inglise>
