<inglise>&sect; 91. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse rakendamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications for application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku nimele seni kehtinud &otilde;igusaktide alusel registreeritud relv, mis ei saa t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust, j&auml;etakse selle omanikule ja talle s&auml;ilitatakse relva senise kasutamise &otilde;igused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A weapon which is not granted type approval but has been registered in the name of a natural person on the basis of legislation which was in force prior to the entry into force of this Act shall be retained by its owner and the owner shall retain his or her existing rights to use the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellist relva ei tohi anda kasutada paralleelrelvaloa alusel ja v&otilde;ib v&otilde;&otilde;randada ainult riigi omandisse. </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited to use such weapon on the basis of a parallel weapons permit and such weapon may be transferred only into state ownership. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 25 kohaselt kollektsioneerida lubatav, kuid seni registreerimata relv tuleb registreerida elu- v&otilde;i asukohaj&auml;rgses politseiprefektuuris kuue kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An unregistered weapon the collection of which is permitted pursuant to &sect; 25 of this Act shall be registered at the police prefecture of the residence or seat of the owner or possessor within six months as of the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud relva registreerimiseks tuleb politseiprefektuurile esitada avaldus, milles on kirjas relva nimetus, liik ja number (mittestandardse relva puhul aga selle kirjeldus) ning relva saamise asjaolud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order for a weapon specified in subsection (2) of this section to be registered, an application shall be submitted to a police prefecture which sets out the name, type and number of the weapon (or, in the case of a non-standard weapon, a description thereof) and the circumstances behind the obtaining the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>Relva registreerimisel ei rakendata k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 33 l&otilde;igetes 1-4 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>The provisions of subsections 33 (1) -(4) of this Act do not apply upon the registration of the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Enne k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud relva registreerimist hindab politseiprefektuur relva saamise asjaolude t&otilde;ep&auml;rasust, kontrollib relva vastavust avalduses toodud andmetele, veendub, et avalduses m&auml;rgitud relva ei ole kasutatud seadusvastastes toimingutes ning v&otilde;rdleb relva andmeid s&otilde;jav&auml;erelvade registri ning teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registri andmetega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Before a weapon specified in subsection (2) of this section is registered, the police prefecture shall assess the truthfulness of the circumstances behind the obtaining of the weapon, verify the compliance of the weapon with the information presented in the application, verify that the weapon specified in the application has not been used in any illegal activities and compare the data concerning the weapon with the data held in the register of military weapons and the register of service and civilian weapons. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiprefektuuril on &otilde;igus k&uuml;sida eksperdi arvamust relva kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>The police prefecture has the right to obtain an expert opinion concerning the weapon. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 3 l&otilde;ikes 5 nimetatud registri kasutusele v&otilde;tmiseni j&auml;tkatakse teenistus- ja tsiviilrelvade registri pidamist Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt varem kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Maintenance of the register of service and civilian weapons shall be continued pursuant to the procedure established earlier by the Government of the Republic until the commencement of the use of the register specified in subsection 3 (5) of this Act. </inglise>
